      \"id\": 27,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that middle-level management acts as a link between top and lower levels.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 28,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that middle-level management does not act as a link between top and lower levels.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that lower-level management directly supervises workers and daily activities.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that lower-level management does not directly supervise workers and daily activities.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that administration focuses on setting policies and goals.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that administration does not focus on setting policies and goals.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that management implements policies set by administration.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that management does not implement policies set by administration.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that organization refers to the structure that defines roles and responsibilities.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that organization does not refer to the structure that defines roles and responsibilities.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that management, administration, and organization are interconnected concepts.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that management, administration, and organization are not interconnected concepts.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that management involves making decisions and taking actions to achieve goals.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that management does not involve making decisions and taking actions to achieve goals.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 41,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that management requires skills like leadership, communication, and problem-solving.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 42,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that management does not require skills like leadership, communication, and problem-solving.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 43,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that management is essential for achieving organizational success and stability.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 44,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that management is not essential for achieving organizational success and stability.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 45,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that management principles help in guiding managers to make effective decisions.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 46,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that management principles do not help in guiding managers to make effective decisions.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that management is a dynamic process that adapts to changes in the business environment.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that management is not a dynamic process.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that management involves coordinating activities to achieve organizational goals.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that management does not involve coordinating activities to achieve organizational goals.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    }\n]\n  ',14,12),(40,'1.3-Functions of Management','<div>\n    <h1>1.3 Functions of Management</h1>\n    <p>Management is essential in any organization, whether it\'s a small business, a large corporation, or even a school. It ensures that work is done efficiently and goals are achieved. There are five main functions of management:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Planning</li>\n      <li>Organizing</li>\n      <li>Leading/Directing</li>\n      <li>Staffing</li>\n      <li>Controlling</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p>Let\'s understand each function in simple terms with examples.</p>\n    \n    <h2>1. Planning</h2>\n    <p><strong>Meaning:</strong> Planning is the first and most important function of management. It involves thinking ahead and deciding what needs to be done, how it should be done, and when it should be done. It helps in setting goals and making strategies to achieve them.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Imagine you want to start a restaurant. Before opening it, you need to plan:</li>\n      <ul>\n        <li>What type of food you will serve (Indian, Chinese, Fast food, etc.).</li>\n        <li>Where your restaurant will be located.</li>\n        <li>How much money you need to invest.</li>\n        <li>How many workers you will hire.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Real-life Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A school principal plans the academic year by deciding:</li>\n      <ul>\n        <li>The syllabus for each class.</li>\n        <li>The schedule for exams and holidays.</li>\n        <li>The number of teachers required.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h2>2. Organizing</h2>\n    <p><strong>Meaning:</strong> Organizing means arranging everything in a systematic way so that work can be done smoothly. It involves distributing tasks, assigning responsibilities, and ensuring that resources (money, staff, materials) are used efficiently.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>In a restaurant, organizing includes:</li>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Assigning chefs to cook food.</li>\n        <li>Hiring waiters to serve customers.</li>\n        <li>Setting up the kitchen with proper equipment.</li>\n        <li>Arranging tables and chairs for customers.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Real-life Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A cricket team organizes itself by:</li>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Assigning roles (batsman, bowler, wicketkeeper).</li>\n        <li>Ensuring everyone practices regularly.</li>\n        <li>Managing equipment like bats, balls, and kits.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h2>3. Leading/Directing</h2>\n    <p><strong>Meaning:</strong> Leading (or Directing) means guiding and motivating employees to work efficiently. A manager should communicate clearly, inspire workers, and solve problems to keep the team motivated.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>In a restaurant, the manager must:</li>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Guide the chefs to maintain food quality.</li>\n        <li>Motivate waiters to provide good service.</li>\n        <li>Solve customer complaints quickly.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Real-life Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A football coach directs the players by:</li>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Encouraging them before a match.</li>\n        <li>Giving instructions during the game.</li>\n        <li>Correcting mistakes and suggesting improvements.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h2>4. Staffing</h2>\n    <p><strong>Meaning:</strong> Staffing means hiring the right people for the right jobs and ensuring they work effectively. It includes recruitment, training, and maintaining a good work environment.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>In a restaurant, staffing involves:</li>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Hiring skilled chefs and waiters.</li>\n        <li>Providing training to improve service.</li>\n        <li>Ensuring workers get proper salaries and rest breaks.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Real-life Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A hospital needs proper staffing:</li>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Hiring qualified doctors and nurses.</li>\n        <li>Training staff in emergency procedures.</li>\n        <li>Ensuring enough workers are available for different shifts.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h2>5. Controlling</h2>\n    <p><strong>Meaning:</strong> Controlling ensures that everything goes as planned. If mistakes happen, corrective actions should be taken immediately. Managers compare actual performance with planned goals and make necessary changes.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>In a restaurant, controlling includes:</li>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Checking if food quality is maintained.</li>\n        <li>Ensuring customers receive timely service.</li>\n        <li>Monitoring expenses to avoid losses.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Real-life Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>In a school, controlling is done by:</li>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Checking if teachers complete the syllabus on time.</li>\n        <li>Ensuring students perform well in exams.</li>\n        <li>Identifying weak students and providing extra help.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h2>Conclusion</h2>\n    <p>The five functions of management—Planning, Organizing, Leading, Staffing, and Controlling—help organizations run smoothly. Just like a football team needs a coach to plan strategies, organize players, lead the team, hire new talent, and ensure good performance, every business needs managers to perform these functions.</p>\n    <p>If a company follows these five functions properly, it will achieve success! ?</p>\n</div>\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What is the primary function of planning in management?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To set goals and strategies\",\n        \"To organize resources\",\n        \"To lead employees\",\n        \"To control performance\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"What is the purpose of organizing in management?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To arrange tasks and resources efficiently\",\n        \"To set goals and strategies\",\n        \"To lead employees\",\n        \"To control performance\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of leading in management?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To guide and motivate employees\",\n        \"To set goals and strategies\",\n        \"To organize resources\",\n        \"To control performance\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"What is the function of staffing in management?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To hire and train employees\",\n        \"To set goals and strategies\",\n        \"To organize resources\",\n        \"To control performance\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"What is the purpose of controlling in management?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To ensure performance matches planned goals\",\n        \"To set goals and strategies\",\n        \"To organize resources\",\n        \"To lead employees\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"Can management improve organizational efficiency?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Yes\",\n        \"No\",\n        \"Only with specific methods\",\n        \"Only with specific functions\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"What is the benefit of planning in management?\",\n      \"options\": [\n   