id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling does not involve comparing actual performance with planned goals.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the five functions of management are interconnected and essential for organizational success.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 26,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the five functions of management are not interconnected or essential for organizational success.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 27,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that planning helps in achieving long-term goals by setting clear strategies.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 28,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that planning does not help in achieving long-term goals.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that organizing helps in reducing confusion and chaos by assigning roles clearly.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that organizing does not help in reducing confusion and chaos.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that leading/directing involves motivating employees to perform better.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that leading/directing does not involve motivating employees.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that staffing is crucial for maintaining a skilled and efficient workforce.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that staffing is not crucial for maintaining a skilled and efficient workforce.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling helps in identifying and correcting deviations from planned goals.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling does not help in identifying and correcting deviations from planned goals.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the five functions of management are essential for achieving organizational efficiency and effectiveness.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the five functions of management are not essential for achieving organizational efficiency and effectiveness.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that planning involves forecasting future trends and challenges.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that planning does not involve forecasting future trends and challenges.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 41,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that organizing involves creating a structure that defines roles and responsibilities.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 42,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that organizing does not involve creating a structure that defines roles and responsibilities.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 43,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that leading/directing involves setting clear expectations and providing feedback to employees.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 44,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that leading/directing does not involve setting clear expectations and providing feedback to employees.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 45,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that staffing involves developing employees through training and development programs.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 46,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that staffing does not involve developing employees through training and development programs.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling involves using performance metrics to evaluate progress.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling does not involve using performance metrics to evaluate progress.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the five functions of management help in building a strong organizational culture.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the five functions of management do not help in building a strong organizational culture.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    }\n]\n  ',14,12),(41,'1.4-Types of Planning and Steps in Planning','<div>\n    <h1>1.4 Types of Planning and Steps in Planning</h1>\n    <p>Planning is the process of deciding in advance what needs to be done, how it should be done, and who should do it. It helps organizations, businesses, and individuals to set goals and achieve them efficiently.</p>\n    \n    <h2>Types of Planning</h2>\n    <p>Planning can be categorized into different types based on scope, time duration, and purpose. The main types of planning are:</p>\n    \n    <h3>1. Strategic Planning</h3>\n    <p><strong>Definition:</strong> Strategic planning is long-term planning that focuses on achieving overall organizational goals.</p>\n    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> It helps in shaping the future direction of an organization.</p>\n    <p><strong>Time Frame:</strong> Usually covers 3-5 years or more.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A smartphone company plans to expand its business into new countries over the next five years.</li>\n      <li>A university plans to introduce online degree programs to attract international students.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>2. Tactical Planning</h3>\n    <p><strong>Definition:</strong> Tactical planning is short-term planning that focuses on achieving specific objectives of different departments within an organization.</p>\n    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> It translates strategic plans into actionable steps for different teams.</p>\n    <p><strong>Time Frame:</strong> Usually covers 1-3 years.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>The marketing team of a company creates a 2-year plan to increase brand awareness through social media and online ads.</li>\n      <li>A retail store plans a discount strategy to boost sales during the holiday season.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>3. Operational Planning</h3>\n    <p><strong>Definition:</strong> Operational planning focuses on day-to-day tasks and activities required to run a business smoothly.</p>\n    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> It ensures that business operations are carried out efficiently.</p>\n    <p><strong>Time Frame:</strong> Short-term (daily, weekly, or monthly).</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A restaurant prepares a daily plan for staff shifts and ingredient supplies.</li>\n      <li>A factory schedules the production of different products based on customer orders.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>4. Financial Planning</h3>\n    <p><strong>Definition:</strong> Financial planning deals with the management of money, investments, and budgets.</p>\n    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> It ensures that a business or individual has enough funds to operate and grow.</p>\n    <p><strong>Time Frame:</strong> Can be short-term (monthly budget) or long-term (5-year investment plan).</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A company plans to invest in new technology within the next two years.</li>\n      <li>A person creates a monthly budget to save for a house purchase.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>5. Growth Planning</h3>\n    <p><strong>Definition:</strong> Growth planning focuses on expanding the business, increasing revenue, or improving market reach.</p>\n    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> It helps businesses scale and compete effectively in the market.</p>\n    <p><strong>Time Frame:</strong> Medium to long-term (2-10 years).</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A startup plans to open 10 new branches across the country in the next five years.</li>\n      <li>A software company plans to develop an AI-based chatbot to attract more customers.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h2>Steps in Planning</h2>\n    <p>Planning involves a systematic process to ensure success. The main steps in planning are:</p>\n    \n    <h3>Step 1: Identifying Goals and Objectives</h3>\n    <p>The first step in planning is to define what needs to be achieved.</p>\n    <p>Goals should be SMART (Specific, Measurable, Achievable, Relevant, and Time-bound).</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A school wants to improve student performance by 20% in the next academic year.</li>\n      <li>A company wants to increase its market share by 10% in three years.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>Step 2: Gathering Information</h3>\n    <p>Before making a plan, it is important to collect data and analyze the current situation.</p>\n    <p>This includes market research, competitor analysis, financial reports, and customer feedback.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A business collects customer reviews to improve its products.</li>\n      <li>A sports coach studies past game performances to prepare a training plan.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>Step 3: Identifying Alternatives</h3>\n    <p>Multiple solutions should be considered to achieve the goal.</p>\n    <p>Different approaches help in selecting the best strategy.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A company thinking about increasing revenue can either launch new products or expand to new locations.</li>\n      <li>A student planning to study for exams can choose between self-study, group study, or coaching classes.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>Step 4: Evaluating Alternatives</h3>\n    <p>Each option is analyzed based on cost, time, feasibility, and risks.</p>\n    <p>The most suitable approach is selected.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A company compares the costs of advertising on social media versus traditional TV ads.</li>\n      <li>A person planning a vacation checks different travel packages to find the best one.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>Step 5: Selecting the Best Plan</h3>\n    <p>After evaluation, the most effective plan is chosen.</p>\n    \n    <h3>Step 6: Implementing the Plan</h3>\n    <p>The plan is put into action by assigning tasks to teams or individuals.</p>\n    \n    <h3>Step 7: Monitoring and Reviewing the Plan</h3>\n    <p>Regular monitoring ensures the plan is on track.</p>\n    \n    <h2>Conclusion</h2>\n    <p>Planning is essential for businesses, organizations, and individuals to achieve their goals.</p>\n</div>\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What is the primary function of strategic planning in management?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To set long-term goals and strategies\",\n        \"To organize resources\",\n        \"To lead employees\",\n        \"To control performance\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"What is the purpose of tactical planning in management?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To translate strategic goals into actionable steps\",\n        \"To set long-term goals\",\n        \"To organize resources\",\n        \"To control performance\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of operational planning in management?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To manage day-to-day tasks and activities\",\n        \"T