      \"id\": 43,\n      \"question\": \"The first step in planning is to define what needs to be achieved by setting ________ goals.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"SMART\",\n        \"specific\",\n        \"measurable\",\n        \"achievable\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    }\n]  ','[\n  {\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that planning is the first and most important function of management.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 2,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that planning is not the first function of management.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 3,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that planning involves setting goals and making strategies to achieve them.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 4,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that planning does not involve setting goals and making strategies.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 5,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that organizing involves arranging resources and tasks systematically.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 6,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that organizing does not involve arranging resources and tasks systematically.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 7,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that leading/directing involves guiding and motivating employees.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 8,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that leading/directing does not involve guiding and motivating employees.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 9,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that staffing involves hiring the right people for the right jobs.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 10,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that staffing does not involve hiring the right people for the right jobs.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 11,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that controlling ensures that everything goes as planned and corrects deviations.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 12,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that controlling does not ensure that everything goes as planned.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 13,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that the five functions of management are planning, organizing, leading, staffing, and controlling.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 14,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that the five functions of management do not include planning, organizing, leading, staffing, and controlling.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 15,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that planning helps in avoiding future problems by setting clear goals.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 16,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that planning does not help in avoiding future problems.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 17,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that organizing ensures efficient use of resources like money, staff, and materials.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 18,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that organizing does not ensure efficient use of resources.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 19,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that leading/directing involves communication and problem-solving to motivate employees.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 20,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that leading/directing does not involve communication and problem-solving.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 21,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that staffing includes recruitment, training, and maintaining a good work environment.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 22,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that staffing does not include recruitment, training, and maintaining a good work environment.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 23,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that controlling involves comparing actual performance with planned goals.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 24,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that controlling does not involve comparing actual performance with planned goals.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 25,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that the five functions of management are interconnected and essential for organizational success.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 26,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that the five functions of management are not interconnected or essential for organizational success.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 27,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that planning helps in achieving long-term goals by setting clear strategies.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 28,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that planning does not help in achieving long-term goals.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 29,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that organizing helps in reducing confusion and chaos by assigning roles clearly.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 30,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that organizing does not help in reducing confusion and chaos.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 31,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that leading/directing involves motivating employees to perform better.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 32,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that leading/directing does not involve motivating employees.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 33,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that staffing is crucial for maintaining a skilled and efficient workforce.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 34,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that staffing is not crucial for maintaining a skilled and efficient workforce.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 35,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that controlling helps in identifying and correcting deviations from planned goals.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 36,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that controlling does not help in identifying and correcting deviations from planned goals.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 37,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that the five functions of management are essential for achieving organizational efficiency and effectiveness.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 38,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that the five functions of management are not essential for achieving organizational efficiency and effectiveness.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 39,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that planning involves forecasting future trends and challenges.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 40,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that planning does not involve forecasting future trends and challenges.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 41,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that organizing involves creating a structure that defines roles and responsibilities.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 42,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that organizing does not involve creating a structure that defines roles and responsibilities.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 43,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that leading/directing involves setting clear expectations and providing feedback to employees.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 44,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that leading/directing does not involve setting clear expectations and providing feedback to employees.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 45,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that staffing involves developing employees through training and development programs.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 46,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that staffing does not involve developing employees through training and development programs.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 47,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that controlling involves using performance metrics to evaluate progress.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 48,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that controlling does not involve using performance metrics to evaluate progress.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 49,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that the five functions of management help in building a strong organizational culture.\",\n    \"answer\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 50,\n    \"question\": \"It is true that the five functions of management do not help in building a strong organizational culture.\",\n    \"answer\": false\n  }\n]',14,12),(42,'1.5-Types of Organization & Steps in Organizing','<div>\n    <h1>1.5 Types of Organization & Steps in Organizing</h1>\n    <h2>A. Types of Organization</h2>\n    <p>An organization is a group of people working together to achieve a common goal. Different organizations follow different structures based on their size, goals, and work style.</p>\n    \n    <h3>1. Line Organization</h3>\n    <p><strong>Definition:</strong> In this type of organization, authority flows from the top level to the bottom level in a direct chain of command. Each employee reports to only one boss.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>In the army, the General commands the Colonel, the Colonel commands the Major, and so on.</li>\n      <li>In a small shop, the owner gives orders to the manager, the manager gives orders to workers.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Advantages:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Simple to understand</li>\n      <li>Clear roles and responsibilities</li>\n      <li>Quick decision-making</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Disadvantages:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Heavy workload on top managers</li>\n      <li>Not flexible for large businesses</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>2. Functional Organization</h3>\n    <p><strong>Definition:</strong> In this structure, the organization is divided into different departments based on functions like Marketing, Finance, HR, Production, etc. Each department has its own head.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A company may have a Sales Department, an HR Department, and a Finance Department, each managed by specialists.</li>\n      <li>A hospital has different functional units: doctors, nurses, finance, reception, and housekeeping.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Advantages:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Specialization in each department</li>\n      <li>Efficient management</li>\n      <li>Work is divided properly</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Disadvantages:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Coordination between departments can be difficult</li>\n      <li>Employees may be confused about who to report to</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>3. Line and Staff Organization</h3>\n    <p><strong>Definition:</strong> This is a combination of line organization and functional organization. Here, line managers handle decision-making and staff experts provide advice.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>In a manufacturing company, the production manager takes decisions (line authority), while technical experts suggest ways to improve efficiency (staff authority).</li>\n      <li>In a hospital, the chief surgeon (line authority) takes decisions, while medical researchers (staff authority) give advice on new treatments.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Advantages:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Expertise is used effectively</li>\n      <li>Better decision-making</li>\n      <li>Workload is shared</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Disadvantages:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Can be expensive due to hiring of experts</li>\n      <li>Conflict between line managers and staff experts</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>4. Project Organization</h3>\n    <p><strong>Definition:</strong> A temporary organizational structure created for a specific project. Once the project is completed, the team is dissolved.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A construction company forms a project team to build a bridge. After the bridge is completed, the team is dissolved.</li>\n      <li>A movie production team works together on a film, then moves to new projects after the movie is done.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Advantages:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Flexible and adaptable</li>\n      <li>Teamwork and innovation</li>\n      <li>Focused on specific goals</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Disadvantages:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Uncertain job security for employees</li>\n      <li>Coordination may be difficult</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>5. Matrix Organization</h3>\n    <p><strong>Definition:</strong> A combination of functional and project-based structures. Employees report to both a functional manager and a project manager.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>In a software company, a programmer reports to both the Technical Head (functional manager) and a Project Leader (project manager).</li>\n      <li>In a car manufacturing company, an engineer reports to both the Design Head and the Production Head.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Advantages:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Efficient resource use</li>\n      <li>More flexible</li>\n      <li>Better coordination across departments</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Disadvantages:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Employees may get confused about reporting to multiple managers</li>\n      <li>Can lead to conflicts</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h2>B. Steps in Organizing</h2>\n    <h3>Step 1: Identifying Objectives</h3>\n    <p>First, the organization must define what it wants to achieve.</p>\n    \n    <h3>Step 2: Identifying and Grouping Activities</h3>\n    <p>The next step is to list all the necessary activities and group similar tasks together.</p>\n    \n    <h3>Step 3: Assigning Responsibilities</h3>\n    <p>The organization assigns tasks to different individuals or departments.</p>\n    \n    <h3>Step 4: Establishing Authority and Responsibility</h3>\n    <p>The organization defines who will report to whom (hierarchy).</p>\n    \n    <h3>Step 5: Coordinating Efforts</h3>\n    <p>The organization ensures that different departments work together smoothly.</p>\n    \n    <h3>Step 6: Reviewing and Improving the Organization</h3>\n    <p>The organization must check its performance regularly and make improvements if needed.</p>\n    \n    <h2>Conclusion</h2>\n    <p>Different organizations follow different structures based on their needs. Organizing is an important management function that helps businesses plan, assign tasks, coordinate efforts, and achieve goals efficiently.</p>\n</div>\n  ','[\n  {\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"question\": \"What is the primary function of a hierarchical organizational structure?\",\n    \"options\": [\n      \"To provide a clear chain of command\",\n      \"To organize resources\",\n      \"To lead employees\",\n      \"To control performance\"\n    ],\n    \"answer\": 1\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 2,\n    \"question\": \"What is the purpose of a functional organizational structure?\",\n    \"options\": [\n      \"To divide the organization into departments based on functions\",\n      \"To set long-term goals\",\n      \"To organize resources\",\n      \"To control performance\"\n    ],\n    \"answer\": 1\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 3,\n    \"question\": \"Can management improve organizational efficiency?\",\n    \"options\": [\n      \"Yes\",\n      \"No\",\n      \"Only with specific methods\",\n      \"Only with specific functions\"\n    ],\n    \"answer\": 1\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 4,\n    \"question\": \"What is the benefit of a divisional organizational structure?\",\n    \"options\": [\n      \"It allows divisions to work independently\",\n      \"It reduces efficiency\",\n      \"It does nothing\",\n      \"It throws an error\"\n    ],\n    \"answer\": 1\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 5,\n    \"questi