nswer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that production management involves product design and quality control.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that production management does not involve product design and quality control.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that marketing management involves setting prices and sales strategies.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that marketing management does not involve setting prices and sales strategies.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that financial management involves investing in business growth.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that financial management does not involve investing in business growth.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that HRM involves ensuring a healthy work environment.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that HRM does not involve ensuring a healthy work environment.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 41,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that material management involves purchasing raw materials.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 42,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that material management does not involve purchasing raw materials.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 43,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that R&D management involves improving manufacturing processes.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 44,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that R&D management does not involve improving manufacturing processes.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 45,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that office management handles office supplies and equipment.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 46,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that office management does not handle office supplies and equipment.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that functional areas of management are essential for business success.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that functional areas of management are not essential for business success.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that each functional area of management contributes to achieving organizational goals.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that each functional area of management does not contribute to achieving organizational goals.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    }\n]\n  ',14,12),(44,'1.7-Managerial Skills – Detailed Explanation with Examples','<div>\n    <h1>1.7 Managerial Skills – Detailed Explanation with Examples</h1>\n    <p>\n      Managerial skills are the abilities that a manager must have to effectively lead and control an organization. \n      These skills help managers perform their duties successfully and ensure that employees work efficiently toward achieving organizational goals.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      Management expert Robert Katz categorized managerial skills into three main types:\n    </p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Technical Skills</li>\n      <li>Human (Interpersonal) Skills</li>\n      <li>Conceptual Skills</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p>Let’s understand each of these skills with simple explanations and examples.</p>\n  \n    <h2>1. Technical Skills</h2>\n    <h3>Definition</h3>\n    <p>\n      Technical skills refer to the ability to use specific knowledge, tools, techniques, and methods required to perform a particular job. \n      These skills are more important for lower-level managers (such as supervisors) because they work closely with employees.\n    </p>\n  \n    <h3>Examples of Technical Skills</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A software manager should know programming languages like Java or Python.</li>\n      <li>A factory supervisor should know how machines operate.</li>\n      <li>A chef in a restaurant should know cooking techniques.</li>\n      <li>A finance manager should understand accounting principles and financial analysis.</li>\n    </ul>\n  \n    <h3>Simple Example</h3>\n    <p>\n      Imagine a restaurant kitchen. The head chef (manager) must know how to cook different dishes, \n      use kitchen equipment, and train junior chefs. This technical expertise helps maintain food quality and service.\n    </p>\n  \n    <h2>2. Human (Interpersonal) Skills</h2>\n    <h3>Definition</h3>\n    <p>\n      Human skills involve the ability to interact, communicate, and work well with people. A manager must understand \n      employees’ needs, motivate them, and resolve conflicts to ensure a positive work environment.\n    </p>\n  \n    <h3>Examples of Human Skills</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A team leader motivating employees to work harder.</li>\n      <li>A customer service manager handling customer complaints.</li>\n      <li>A school principal resolving conflicts between teachers.</li>\n      <li>A manager building teamwork and ensuring good communication among employees.</li>\n    </ul>\n  \n    <h3>Simple Example</h3>\n    <p>\n      Imagine a football coach. A good coach does not just teach players how to kick a ball but also ensures they work \n      together as a team, resolve conflicts, and stay motivated. Similarly, a manager needs human skills to keep the team united and productive.\n    </p>\n  \n    <h2>3. Conceptual Skills</h2>\n    <h3>Definition</h3>\n    <p>\n      Conceptual skills refer to the ability to think creatively, analyze situations, and make strategic decisions for the future. \n      These skills are most important for top-level managers who plan and make policies for the organization.\n    </p>\n  \n    <h3>Examples of Conceptual Skills</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A CEO planning a new business expansion.</li>\n      <li>A hospital director deciding to introduce new healthcare services.</li>\n      <li>A government official making policies to improve the economy.</li>\n      <li>A business owner analyzing competitors and future market trends.</li>\n    </ul>\n  \n    <h3>Simple Example</h3>\n    <p>\n      Imagine a company selling mobile phones. The CEO must think about:\n    </p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Future market trends (Will people prefer foldable phones?)</li>\n      <li>Competition (What are Samsung and Apple doing?)</li>\n      <li>Company growth (Should we launch a budget-friendly smartphone?)</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p>\n      These long-term decisions require conceptual skills to ensure the company stays ahead of competitors.\n    </p>\n  \n    <h2>Importance of Managerial Skills</h2>\n    <p>A manager must balance all three skills:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Lower-level managers (e.g., supervisors) need more technical skills because they work directly with employees.</li>\n      <li>Middle-level managers (e.g., department heads) need more human skills to coordinate between employees and top management.</li>\n      <li>Top-level managers (e.g., CEOs) need strong conceptual skills for decision-making and strategic planning.</li>\n    </ul>\n  \n    <h3>Final Example</h3>\n    <p>Think of a hospital:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A junior doctor (technical skills) knows how to diagnose and treat patients.</li>\n      <li>A hospital administrator (human skills) ensures staff cooperation and patient satisfaction.</li>\n      <li>The hospital director (conceptual skills) plans for future healthcare services and investments.</li>\n    </ul>\n  \n    <p>\n      By mastering all three skills, a manager can successfully lead an organization toward success.\n    </p>\n</div>\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What are the three main types of managerial skills?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Technical, Human, and Conceptual\",\n        \"Only Technical and Human\",\n        \"Only Conceptual and Human\",\n        \"Only Technical\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of technical skills in management?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To use specific tools and techniques\",\n        \"To motivate employees\",\n        \"To plan strategically\",\n        \"To resolve conflicts\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Can management improve organizational efficiency?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Yes\",\n        \"No\",\n        \"Only with specific methods\",\n        \"Only with specific functions\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"What is the benefit of human skills in management?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It helps in motivating and communicating with employees\",\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It does nothing\",\n        \"It throws an error\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"Can management enhance employee motivation?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Yes\",\n        \"No\",\n        \"Only with specific methods\",\n        \"Only with specific functions\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of a manager in leading employees?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To guide and motivate employees\",\n        \"To only set goals\",\n        \"To only organize resources\",\n        \"To only control performance\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"Can management improve customer satisfaction?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Yes\",\n        \"No\",\n        \"Only with specific methods\",\n        \"Only with specific functions\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"What is the effect of management on organizational stability?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It ensures stability and growth\",\n        \"It reduces stability and growth\",\n        \"It does nothing\",\n        \"It throws an error\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"Can management enhance teamwork and collaboration?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Yes\",\n        \"No\",\n        \"Only with specific methods\",\n        \"Only with specific functions\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"What is the benefit of management in achieving long-term sustainability?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It ensures long-term success and sustainability\",\n        \"It reduces long-term success and sustainability\",\n        \"It does nothing\",\n        \"It throws an error\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"Can management enhance organizational culture?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Yes\",\n        \"No\",\n        \"Only with specific methods\",\n        \"Only with specific functions\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of a liaison in management?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To build relationships with people inside and outside the company\",\n        \"To only set goals\",\n        \"To only organize resources\",\n        \"To only control performance\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"Can management improve organizational growth?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Yes\",\n        \"No\",\n        \"Only with specific methods