ot help in setting goals and determining strategies.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 45,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that interpersonal skills are essential for motivating employees and resolving conflicts.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 46,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that interpersonal skills are not essential for motivating employees and resolving conflicts.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conceptual skills are more important for top-level managers.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conceptual skills are not more important for top-level managers.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that managerial skills are essential for achieving organizational success.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that managerial skills are not essential for achieving organizational success.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    }\n]\n  ',14,12),(45,'2.1-Planning by Supervisor','<div>\n    <h1>Planning at Supervisory Level</h1>\n    <h2>2.1 Planning by Supervisor</h2>\n    <h3>Introduction to Planning at the Supervisory Level</h3>\n    <p>Planning is the process of setting goals and deciding how to achieve them. At the supervisory level, planning involves short-term goals and day-to-day activities to ensure smooth workflow and efficiency in an organization. Supervisors are responsible for managing employees, ensuring tasks are completed on time, and solving daily operational challenges.</p>\n    <p>Supervisors are the bridge between higher management and employees. They take orders from senior managers and ensure workers follow them correctly. Planning at this level is very important because it helps in managing time, resources, and manpower effectively.</p>\n    \n    <h3>What is Planning by a Supervisor?</h3>\n    <p>Supervisory planning involves setting daily, weekly, or monthly targets and organizing work so that employees can complete tasks efficiently. Supervisors create a work plan by:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Understanding company goals</li>\n      <li>Breaking down goals into small tasks</li>\n      <li>Assigning work to employees</li>\n      <li>Ensuring deadlines are met</li>\n      <li>Solving problems that arise during work</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>Key Features of Planning by a Supervisor</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>Short-Term Focus:</strong> Plans at the supervisory level are usually for a few days, weeks, or months, unlike top management, which plans for years.</li>\n      <li><strong>Practical and Action-Oriented:</strong> Supervisors focus on getting things done, ensuring that employees understand their duties.</li>\n      <li><strong>Resource Allocation:</strong> Planning ensures that tools, materials, and workforce are used effectively.</li>\n      <li><strong>Team Coordination:</strong> Supervisors ensure that all employees work together efficiently.</li>\n      <li><strong>Problem Solving:</strong> If issues arise (like a worker being absent), supervisors adjust plans accordingly.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>Types of Planning Done by Supervisors</h3>\n    <h4>1. Work Scheduling (Daily Planning)</h4>\n    <p>Supervisors create work schedules to assign duties to employees and ensure work is completed on time.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> In a factory, a supervisor decides which worker will operate which machine for the day and sets production targets.</p>\n    \n    <h4>2. Resource Planning</h4>\n    <p>Supervisors must plan how to use available materials, tools, and employees efficiently.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> In a restaurant, the kitchen supervisor ensures that ingredients are available before opening time and assigns chefs to different cooking stations.</p>\n    \n    <h4>3. Task Prioritization</h4>\n    <p>Some tasks are more urgent than others. A supervisor prioritizes work to ensure that the most important tasks are done first.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> In a hospital, the nursing supervisor ensures that critical patients are attended to before routine checkups.</p>\n    \n    <h4>4. Workforce Management (Shift Planning)</h4>\n    <p>Supervisors plan work shifts, ensuring that there are enough workers at any given time.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> In a call center, the supervisor plans shifts so that there are employees available 24/7 to handle customer queries.</p>\n    \n    <h4>5. Problem Solving & Contingency Planning</h4>\n    <p>If an issue arises, supervisors must quickly adjust the plan. This includes handling employee absences, equipment failure, or urgent client requests.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> In a construction site, if a worker falls sick, the site supervisor reassigns their duties to another worker to avoid delays.</p>\n    \n    <h3>Why is Planning by a Supervisor Important?</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>✅ Improves Productivity –</strong> Work is completed faster and more efficiently.</li>\n      <li><strong>✅ Reduces Wastage –</strong> Proper planning prevents waste of time, money, and materials.</li>\n      <li><strong>✅ Ensures Timely Completion –</strong> Deadlines are met, and work does not pile up.</li>\n      <li><strong>✅ Minimizes Confusion –</strong> Employees know their roles, reducing miscommunication.</li>\n      <li><strong>✅ Boosts Employee Motivation –</strong> Well-planned work ensures fair work distribution, keeping employees satisfied.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>Conclusion</h3>\n    <p>Supervisory planning is an essential part of management that ensures smooth daily operations. A supervisor plays a key role in organizing work schedules, assigning tasks, managing resources, and solving problems. By planning effectively, a supervisor ensures that goals are achieved efficiently and employees work in a well-structured environment.</p>\n    \n    <h3>Real-Life Example:</h3>\n    <p>Imagine a supervisor at a retail store. Every morning, they plan the tasks for sales staff – assigning some employees to handle billing, others to restock shelves, and some to assist customers. They also ensure the store has enough stock for the day and solve any issues (like a faulty billing machine). This daily planning helps the store run smoothly and keeps customers satisfied.</p>\n</div>\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What is the primary role of a supervisor in planning?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To manage employees and ensure tasks are completed on time\",\n        \"To only set long-term goals\",\n        \"To only organize resources\",\n        \"To only control performance\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"What type of planning is most common at the supervisory level?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Short-term planning\",\n        \"Long-term planning\",\n        \"Only operational planning\",\n        \"Only strategic planning\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Can management improve organizational efficiency?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Yes\",\n        \"No\",\n        \"Only with specific methods\",\n        \"Only with specific functions\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"What is the benefit of resource planning by a supervisor?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It helps in using materials and tools efficiently\",\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It does nothing\",\n        \"It throws an error\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"Can management enhance employee motivation?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Yes\",\n        \"No\",\n        \"Only with specific me