   \"roles\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"Planning ensures that tools, materials, and workforce are used ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"efficiently\",\n        \"effectively\",\n        \"smoothly\",\n        \"productively\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"Supervisors ensure that all employees work together ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"efficiently\",\n        \"effectively\",\n        \"smoothly\",\n        \"cooperatively\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"If issues arise, supervisors adjust plans accordingly, which is part of ________ planning.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"contingency\",\n        \"emergency\",\n        \"crisis\",\n        \"backup\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning involves setting short-term goals and managing day-to-day activities.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning involves setting long-term goals.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisors act as a bridge between higher management and employees.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisors do not act as a bridge between higher management and employees.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning includes breaking down company goals into smaller tasks.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning does not involve breaking down company goals into smaller tasks.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisors are responsible for assigning work to employees and ensuring deadlines are met.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisors are not responsible for assigning work to employees and ensuring deadlines are met.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning focuses on practical and action-oriented tasks.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning does not focus on practical and action-oriented tasks.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that resource allocation is a key part of supervisory planning.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that resource allocation is not a key part of supervisory planning.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that team coordination is essential for supervisory planning.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that team coordination is not essential for supervisory planning.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that problem-solving is a critical aspect of supervisory planning.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that problem-solving is not a critical aspect of supervisory planning.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that work scheduling is a type of planning done by supervisors.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that work scheduling is not a type of planning done by supervisors.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that resource planning involves managing materials and tools efficiently.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that resource planning does not involve managing materials and tools efficiently.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that task prioritization is important for ensuring urgent tasks are completed first.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 22,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that task prioritization is not important for ensuring urgent tasks are completed first.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 23,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that workforce management involves planning employee shifts.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that workforce management does not involve planning employee shifts.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that contingency planning is used to handle unexpected issues.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 26,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that contingency planning is not used to handle unexpected issues.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 27,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning improves productivity by organizing tasks efficiently.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 28,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning does not improve productivity.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning reduces waste by using resources effectively.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning does not reduce waste.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning ensures timely completion of tasks.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning does not ensure timely completion of tasks.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning minimizes confusion among employees.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning does not minimize confusion among employees.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning boosts employee motivation by distributing work fairly.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning does not boost employee motivation.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning involves setting SMART objectives.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning does not involve setting SMART objectives.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning is essential for smooth daily operations.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning is not essential for smooth daily operations.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 41,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisors play a key role in implementing organizational policies.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 42,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisors do not play a key role in implementing organizational policies.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 43,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning involves coordinating with other departments.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 44,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning does not involve coordinating with other departments.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 45,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that contingency plans are developed to address potential risks or failures.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 46,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that contingency plans are not developed to address potential risks or failures.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning helps in managing time effectively.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisory planning does not help in managing time effectively.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that effective supervisory planning enhances employee satisfaction.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that effective supervisory planning does not enhance employee satisfaction.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    }\n]\n  ',14,13),(46,'2.2-Planning Activities, Detailing, and Following Each Step','<div>\n    <h1>2.2 Planning Activities, Detailing, and Following Each Step</h1>\n    \n    <h2>Introduction</h2>\n    <p>Planning is an essential part of any process, whether it is a small task like organizing an event or a large project like developing a mobile app. Without proper planning, tasks can become confusing, inefficient, and time-consuming.</p>\n    <p>This topic focuses on how to plan activities, detail each step, and follow them correctly to achieve the desired results.</p>\n    \n    <h2>1. What is Planning?</h2>\n    <p>Planning means thinking in advance about what needs to be done, how it will be done, and in what order. It helps in organizing tasks effectively so that they are completed successfully.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> Imagine you are organizing a birthday party. If you don’t plan, things might go wrong—guests may not get invitations on time, the food may not be enough, or decorations may be missing. But if you plan properly, you can ensure everything goes smoothly.</p>\n    \n    <h2>2. Steps in Planning Activities</h2>\n    \n    <h3>Step 1: Identify the Goal (What Needs to Be Done?)</h3>\n    <p>Before starting any activity, the first step is to identify what needs to be achieved.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> If you want to build a mobile app for online food delivery, your goal is: \"Develop an app that allows users to order food from restaurants easily.\"</p>\n    \n    <h3>Step 2: Gather Requirements (What is Needed?)</h3>\n    <p>After defining the goal, the next step is to find out what resources, tools, and people are required to complete the task.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> For the food delivery app, you may need:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A development team (programmers, designers)</li>\n      <li>A list of restaurants</li>\n      <li>A payment system</li>\n      <li>A database for storing orders</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>Step 3: Break the Task into Smaller Steps</h3>\n    <p>Once you know what you need, divide the task into smaller, manageable steps.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> For a birthday party, the steps could be:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Create a guest list</li>\n      <li>Send invitations</li>\n      <li>Book a venue</li>\n      <li>Order food</li>\n      <li>Arrange decorations</li>\n      <li>Organize entertainment</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>Step 4: Assign Responsibilities</h3>\n    <p>In many activities, multiple people work together. It’s important to assign who will do what to avoid confusion.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> In a wedding preparation, tasks can be divided as follows:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>One person handles guest invitations</li>\n      <li>Another arranges the food</li>\n      <li>Another takes care of decorations</li>\n      <li>Someone books the venue</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>Step 5: Set a Timeline (When Should Each Task Be Completed?)</h3>\n    <p>Setting deadlines helps in keeping track of progress.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> For an exam preparation plan:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Monday: Study Chapter 1 & 2</li>\n      <li>Tuesday: Study Chapter 3 & 4</li>\n      <li>Wednesday: Revise all chapters</li>\n      <li>Thursday: Solve past question papers</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>Step 6: Follow the Plan (Execution Phase)</h3>\n    <p>After planning, it is important to follow the steps properly to complete the task as per schedule.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> If you are renovating your house, and you planned to first paint the walls before installing new furniture, you should stick to that order to avoid mistakes.</p>\n    \n    <h3>Step 7: Monitor Progress and Make Adjustments</h3>\n    <p>Sometimes things don’t go as planned. It’s important to check progress regularly and make adjustments if needed.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> If a caterer cancels at the last moment, you should quickly find a new one to keep the event on track.</p>\n    \n    <h3>Step 8: Review and Improve</h3>\n    <p>After completing the task, review the whole process to learn from mistakes and improve for the future.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong> After hosting a corporate event, you can ask for feedback to improve future events.</p>\n    \n    <h2>Conclusion</h2>\n    <p>Planning is essential in all areas of life—be it personal tasks, business projects, or software development.</p>\n    <p><strong>Key Takeaways:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Planning helps in organizing work efficiently</li>\n      <li>Dividing tasks into smaller steps makes execution easier</li>\n      <li>Assigning responsibilities avoids confusion</li>\n      <li>Setting deadlines ensures timely completion</li>\n      <li>Following the plan and monitoring progress leads to success</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p>By following these steps, anyone can manage activities easily and effectively! ?</p>\n</div>\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What is the primary role of planning in management?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To only manage resources\",\n        \"To organize tasks efficiently\",\n        \"To control performance\",\n        \"To only set long-term goals\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"What is the benefit of gathering requirements in planning?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It only involves budgeting\",\n        \"It does nothing\",\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It helps in determining what resources are needed\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Can management improve organizational efficiency?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Only with technology\",\n        \"No\",\n        \"Only with specific methods\",\n        \"Yes\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of a manager in leading employees?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To only manage resources\",\n        \"To only set goals\",\n        \"To only control performance\",\n        \"To guide and motivate employees\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"Can management improve customer satisfaction?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Only with marketing\",\n        \"No\",\n        \"Only with specific methods\",\n        \"Yes\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"What is the effect of management on organizational stability?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It only affec