lse\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"A deposit slip includes details like account number, amount, and depositor\'s name.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"Standard forms reduce errors in data collection.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"A patient registration form is used for job applications.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"Examination forms ensure students are registered properly for their exams.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"Income Tax Return forms are used to file taxes.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"A job application form is used for hospital registration.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"Standard forms can be used for organizing and retrieving data quickly.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"The purpose of a standard form is to increase confusion in documentation.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"A loan application form helps individuals apply for financial loans.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"A library membership form includes details like student name and ID.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"A driving license application form includes details like name, address, and age.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"Forms do not require a signature for authentication.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    }\n]\n  ',14,13),(48,'2.4-Budgeting for Materials and Manpower (2.4)','<div>\n    <h1>2.4 Budgeting for Materials and Manpower</h1>\n  \n    <h2>Introduction to Budgeting for Materials and Manpower</h2>\n    <p>\n      Budgeting is the process of estimating and allocating financial resources to different aspects of a project or business. \n      When planning any project, two of the most important cost factors are materials and manpower.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      <strong>Materials</strong> refer to the physical items needed to complete a project, such as raw materials, tools, and equipment.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      <strong>Manpower</strong> refers to the human resources or labor required to execute the project, including skilled and unskilled workers, engineers, supervisors, etc.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      Proper budgeting for these two aspects ensures that the project runs smoothly, stays within financial limits, and avoids delays due to shortages or unexpected expenses.\n    </p>\n  \n    <h2>1. Budgeting for Materials</h2>\n    <p>Materials are essential for any project, whether it’s construction, manufacturing, or service-based. The budget for materials should include:</p>\n  \n    <h3>A. Identifying Required Materials</h3>\n    <p>Before setting a budget, it is important to list all materials needed for the project. This includes:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Raw materials (e.g., cement, steel, bricks for construction)</li>\n      <li>Tools and equipment (e.g., drilling machines, welding machines)</li>\n      <li>Office supplies (e.g., paper, computers for an IT project)</li>\n    </ul>\n  \n    <h4>Example 1:</h4>\n    <p>If you are building a house, you need materials like cement, bricks, wood, paint, and electrical wiring.</p>\n  \n    <h4>Example 2:</h4>\n    <p>If you are starting a bakery, you need ingredients like flour, sugar, eggs, and baking machines.</p>\n  \n    <h3>B. Estimating Material Costs</h3>\n    <p>Once the required materials are listed, their costs need to be estimated. This can be done by:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Checking market prices from suppliers.</li>\n      <li>Considering transportation and delivery costs.</li>\n      <li>Adding extra for unexpected expenses (buffer cost).</li>\n    </ul>\n  \n    <h4>Example:</h4>\n    <p>A furniture-making business needs 50 wooden planks, and each plank costs $10. The estimated material cost will be:</p>\n    <p>50 × 10 = 500 dollars.</p>\n  \n    <h3>C. Reducing Material Costs</h3>\n    <p>To keep material costs within budget, businesses can:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Buy materials in bulk for discounts.</li>\n      <li>Use alternative materials if they are cheaper and of the same quality.</li>\n      <li>Reduce wastage by proper planning.</li>\n    </ul>\n  \n    <h2>2. Budgeting for Manpower</h2>\n    <p>Manpower budgeting involves estimating the cost of labor needed to complete the project. It includes salaries, wages, benefits, and overtime pay.</p>\n  \n    <h3>A. Identifying Workforce Requirements</h3>\n    <p>To budget for manpower, we must determine:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>The number of workers needed.</li>\n      <li>The type of workers required (skilled or unskilled).</li>\n      <li>The duration they will be employed.</li>\n    </ul>\n  \n    <h4>Example 1:</h4>\n    <p>A construction project may need:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>10 skilled workers (e.g., electricians, plumbers)</li>\n      <li>20 unskilled workers (e.g., laborers for lifting bricks)</li>\n    </ul>\n  \n    <h4>Example 2:</h4>\n    <p>A software company may need:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>5 developers for coding</li>\n      <li>2 designers for UI/UX</li>\n      <li>1 project manager</li>\n    </ul>\n  \n    <h3>B. Estimating Labor Costs</h3>\n    <p>Labor costs depend on wages per hour or per project. Other costs include:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Overtime pay for extra work hours.</li>\n      <li>Bonuses for performance.</li>\n      <li>Insurance and benefits for workers.</li>\n    </ul>\n  \n    <h4>Example:</h4>\n    <p>A carpenter earns $20 per hour and works 8 hours per day for 30 days. His monthly wage would be:</p>\n    <p>20 × 8 × 30 = 4,800 dollars.</p>\n  \n    <h3>C. Controlling Manpower Costs</h3>\n    <p>To reduce manpower costs, businesses can:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Hire only essential workers.</li>\n      <li>Use technology (like machines) to replace manual work.</li>\n      <li>Improve worker efficiency through training.</li>\n    </ul>\n  \n    <h2>3. Combining Materials and Manpower Budgeting</h2>\n    <p>For a successful project, both materials and manpower costs must be balanced. If the material budget is too high, there may not be enough money left for skilled labor. Similarly, if too many workers are hired, there may not be enough funds for materials.</p>\n  \n    <h4>Example: Building a Small Office</h4>\n    <p>A small office project requires:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Materials: $50,000 (bricks, cement, glass, furniture)</li>\n      <li>Manpower: $30,000 (laborers, electricians, carpenters)</li>\n      <li>Other Expenses: $10,000 (transport, legal fees)</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><strong>Total Budget:</strong> $90,000</p>\n    <p>\n      If unexpected costs arise (e.g., material prices increase), the project manager may have to adjust either the material or manpower budget to stay within the $90,000 limit.\n    </p>\n  \n    <h2>4. Conclusion</h2>\n    <p>Budgeting for materials and manpower is essential for any project. It helps:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Avoid cost overruns.</li>\n      <li>Ensure smooth project completion.</li>\n      <li>Improve efficiency and reduce wastage.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p>\n      By planning properly, businesses can complete projects on time and within budget while maintaining quality.\n    </p>\n</div>\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What is budgeting?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"A process of spending money randomly\",\n        \"A process of estimating and allocating financial resources\",\n        \"A method of avoiding expenses\",\n        \"A way to increase project costs\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"What are the two main cost factors in budgeting for a project?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Marketing and advertising\",\n        \"Materials and manpower\",\n        \"Electricity and rent\",\n        \"Taxes and maintenance\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"What does manpower refer to in budgeting?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Raw materials and tools\",\n        \"Machines and equipment\",\n        \"Human resources or labor required for a project\",\n        \"Transport and logistics\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"Why is budgeting for materials and manpower important?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To ensure a project runs smoothly and stays within financial limits\",\n        \"To increase costs and delays\",\n        \"To reduce the need for planning\",\n        \"To eliminate the need for skilled labor\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"What is the first step in budgeting for materials?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Guessing material costs\",\n        \"Ignoring market prices\",\n        \"Identifying required materials\",\n        \"Avoiding material purchase\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is an example of raw materials?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Computers and chairs\",\n        \"Cement, steel, and bricks\",\n        \"Marketing flyers\",\n        \"Employee salaries\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"How can businesses reduce material costs?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Buy materials in bulk for discounts\",\n        \"Purchase the most expensive materials\",\n        \"Ignore material wastage\",\n        \"Avoid comparing supplier prices\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"What factors should be considered while estimating material costs?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Market prices, transportation costs, and buffer cost\",\n        \"Only the price of the most expensive material\",\n        \"Ignoring additional costs like delivery\",\n        \"Avoiding market research\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is NOT a method of reducing manpower costs?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Hiring only essential workers\",\n        \"Using technology to replace manual work\",\n        \"Increasing the number of unskilled workers unnecessarily\",\n        \"Improving worker efficiency through training\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"What is the impact of an imbalanced material and manpower budget?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Leads to project delays and inefficiencies\",\n        \"Reduces overall costs significantly\",\n        \"Ensures a perfect project outcome\",\n        \"Removes the need for budgeting\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"Budgeting is the process of estimating and allocating ________ resources to different aspects of a project.\",\n      \"options\": [\"time\", \"financial\", \"human\", \"material\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"Two important cost factors in any project are ________ and manpower.\",\n      \"options\": [\"materials\", \"marketing\", \"transportation\", \"insurance\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"Materials include physical items like raw materials, tools, and ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"transportation\", \"workers\", \"equipment\", \"electricity\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"Manpower refers to the human resources required for a project, including ________ and unskilled workers.\",\n      \"options\": [\"machines\", \"skilled\", \"transporters\", \"accountants\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"Proper budgeting ensures that a project stays within ________ limits.\",\n      \"options\": [\"technical\", \"financial\", \"geographical\", \"legal\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"Before budgeting for materials, it is important to ________ all required materials.\",\n      \"options\": [\"discard\", \"purchase\", \"list\", \"ignore\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"Material costs should include actual price, transportation, and a ________ cost.\",\n      \"options\": [\"fixed\", \"hidden\", \"buffer\", \"random\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"One way to reduce material costs is to buy in ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"small amounts\", \"bulk\", \"credit\", \"random purchases\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"The workforce required for a project can be categorized as skilled and ________ workers.\",\n      \"options\": [\"government\", \"independent\", \"unskilled\", \"freelance\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"Labor costs depend on wages per hour or per ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"month\", \"year\", \"project\", \"worker\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"Budgeting is the process of estimating and allocating financial resources to different aspects of a project or business.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Materials in a project only refer to raw materials and do not include tools or equipment.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Manpower includes all human resources required for a project, including skilled and unskilled workers.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"Proper budgeting helps a project stay within financial limits and avoid unexpected expenses.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"The first step in budgeting for materials is identifying the required materials for the project.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"Raw materials, tools, and office supplies are examples of materials required for a project.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"A bakery only needs flour and sugar for its operations and does not require any machinery.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"Estimating material costs involves checking market prices and considering delivery costs.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"Adding a buffer cost helps prevent unexpected expenses in material budgeting.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"Buying materials in bulk can increase overall costs and should always be avoided.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"Using alternative materials can help reduce project costs while maintaining quality.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"Reducing material wastage is an effective way to control project costs.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"Manpower budgeting does not include costs for salaries, wages, and benefits.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"To estimate labor costs, we must determine the number and type of workers required.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"A construction project typically requires both skilled and unskilled workers.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"A software company does not need to include designers in its manpower budget.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"Labor costs depend only on wages and do not include overtime pay or benefits.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"A worker’s total monthly salary is calculated based on daily wages and the number of days worked.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"Overtime pay is an additional cost that should be considered in manpower budgeting.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"Hiring excess workers can lead to unnecessary increases in labor costs.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"Machines and automation can help reduce manpower costs in certain projects.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 22,\n      \"question\": \"Training workers to improve efficiency can help control labor costs.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 23,\n      \"question\": \"Balancing material and manpower budgets is necessary for a successful project.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"If material costs are too high, there may not be enough budget left for skilled labor.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"Unexpected cost increases in materials should not affect manpower budgeting.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 26,\n      \"question\": \"A project with a budget of $90,000 should ensure material and labor costs are balanced within this limit.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 27,\n      \"question\": \"Ignoring material and manpower budgeting can lead to cost overruns and project delays.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 28,\n      \"question\": \"Budgeting only for materials is sufficient for a successful project.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"Manpower costs can be reduced by hiring only essential workers.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"Legal fees and transportation costs are not part of project budgeting.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"Project managers should always leave some budget flexibility for unexpected expenses.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"A budget ensures smooth project completion by preventing financial shortages.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"A project can run smoothly without proper budgeting for materials and manpower.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"If material prices increase, project managers may need to adjust the manpower budget.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"Manpower costs can never be reduced in a project.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"Every project requires some form of budgeting, regardless of its size.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"A bakery\'s budgeting includes both material costs (ingredients) and manpower costs (bakers, cashiers).\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"Project budgets should be flexible to accommodate unexpected price changes.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"Over-budgeting for materials can reduce funds available for skilled workers.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"Accurate budgeting helps businesses complete projects within deadlines.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 41,\n      \"question\": \"Unskilled workers generally have higher wages than skilled workers.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 42,\n      \"question\": \"Using outdated budgeting methods does not affect project efficiency.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 43,\n      \"question\": \"A budget should be monitored regularly to ensure financial control.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 44,\n      \"question\": \"Ignoring budgeting can lead to project failure.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 45,\n      \"question\": \"Budgeting for materials involves considering waste and surplus.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 46,\n      \"question\": \"High material costs always lead to project failure.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"Every project budget should have an emergency fund.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"Project budgeting helps in better financial planning for businesses.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"A project’s total budget includes materials, manpower, and unexpected costs.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"Budgeting only applies to large-scale projects and is not necessary for small businesses.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    }\n]\n  ',14,13);
INSERT INTO `tenanta.lessonsection` VALUES (49,'2.5-Organizing the Physical Resources','<div>\n    <h1>Organizing at the Supervisory Level</h1>\n    <p>Organizing is a crucial function of management that helps ensure smooth operations in an organization. At the supervisory level, organizing involves arranging and coordinating resources (such as manpower, materials, and machines) so that work is completed efficiently.</p>\n    <p>A supervisor is responsible for managing workers, allocating tasks, and ensuring that employees have the necessary resources to do their jobs well.</p>\n    \n    <h2>2.5 Organizing the Physical Resources</h2>\n    <p>Physical resources include machines, tools, raw materials, office supplies, workspace, and infrastructure that are needed to complete tasks. A supervisor must ensure that these resources are available, properly maintained, and efficiently utilized.</p>\n\n    <h3>Why is organizing physical resources important?</h3>\n    <ul>\n        <li>Reduces wastage of materials.</li>\n        <li>Increases efficiency by placing resources where they are needed.</li>\n        <li>Improves safety in the workplace.</li>\n        <li>Ensures a smooth workflow without unnecessary delays.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>Example:</h3>\n    <p>? Imagine a car manufacturing company. The supervisor must ensure that:</p>\n    <ul>\n        <li>Machines are working properly.</li>\n        <li>Workers have the required tools to assemble cars.</li>\n        <li>Raw materials like steel, rubber, and paint are available on time.</li>\n        <li>Finished cars are moved to the storage area efficiently.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <p>? In a restaurant, the supervisor must:</p>\n    <ul>\n        <li>Ensure that the kitchen has the necessary ingredients.</li>\n        <li>Keep the refrigerators and cooking equipment in working condition.</li>\n        <li>Arrange tables and chairs properly in the dining area.</li>\n    </ul>\n</div>','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What is the primary function of organizing in management?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To manage finances\",\n        \"To ensure smooth operations\",\n        \"To hire employees\",\n        \"To market products\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"At the supervisory level, what does organizing involve?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Only managing workers\",\n        \"Arranging and coordinating resources\",\n        \"Only allocating tasks\",\n        \"Only ensuring safety\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"What are some examples of physical resources?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Only machines and tools\",\n        \"Machines, tools, raw materials, office supplies, workspace, and infrastructure\",\n        \"Only raw materials and office supplies\",\n        \"Only workspace and infrastructure\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"Why is organizing physical resources important?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It only reduces wastage of materials\",\n        \"It only increases efficiency\",\n        \"It reduces wastage, increases efficiency, improves safety, and ensures smooth workflow\",\n        \"It only improves safety\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"What is a supervisor responsible for?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Only managing workers\",\n        \"Managing workers, allocating tasks, and ensuring necessary resources\",\n        \"Only allocating tasks\",\n        \"Only ensuring safety\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"In a car manufacturing company, what should a supervisor ensure?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Only that machines are working properly\",\n        \"That machines are working properly, workers have required tools, raw materials are available, and finished cars are moved efficiently\",\n        \"Only that raw materials are available\",\n        \"Only that finished cars are moved efficiently\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"In a restaurant, what should a supervisor ensure?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Only that the kitchen has necessary ingredients\",\n        \"That the kitchen has necessary ingredients, cooking equipment is working, and tables are arranged properly\",\n        \"Only that cooking equipment is working\",\n        \"Only that tables are arranged properly\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of a supervisor in resource allocation?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To allocate tasks only\",\n        \"To ensure resources are available and utilized efficiently\",\n        \"To manage finances only\",\n        \"To hire employees only\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important to place resources where they are needed?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It only reduces wastage\",\n        \"It increases efficiency and reduces delays\",\n        \"It only improves safety\",\n        \"It only ensures smooth workflow\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"What happens when physical resources are not properly maintained?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Efficiency increases\",\n        \"Safety improves\",\n        \"Wastage reduces\",\n        \"Workflow may be disrupted\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"What is the impact of efficient resource utilization on workflow?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It causes unnecessary delays\",\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It ensures a smooth workflow without unnecessary delays\",\n        \"It increases wastage\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"How does organizing physical resources improve safety?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"By reducing the availability of resources\",\n        \"By ensuring resources are properly maintained and used\",\n        \"By increasing the number of workers\",\n        \"By decreasing the number of machines\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"What is the benefit of reducing wastage of materials?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It increases costs\",\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It conserves resources and reduces costs\",\n        \"It disrupts workflow\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"In what type of environment is organizing physical resources crucial?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Only in manufacturing\",\n        \"Only in service industries\",\n        \"In all types of organizations\",\n        \"Only in non-profit organizations\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of a supervisor in ensuring resource availability?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To ensure resources are available on time\",\n        \"To allocate tasks only\",\n        \"To manage finances only\",\n        \"To hire employees only\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"How does organizing resources affect employee productivity?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It decreases productivity\",\n        \"It has no impact on productivity\",\n        \"It increases productivity by providing necessary resources\",\n        \"It only affects safety\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"What is an example of a physical resource in an office setting?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Only computers\",\n        \"Computers, office supplies, and workspace\",\n        \"Only office supplies\",\n        \"Only workspace\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important to maintain machines properly?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It increases wastage\",\n        \"It ensures smooth workflow and safety\",\n        \"It disrupts workflow\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"In a restaurant, what physical resource is crucial for food preparation?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Only tables and chairs\",\n        \"Only refrigerators and cooking equipment\",\n        \"Refrigerators, cooking equipment, and ingredients\",\n        \"Only ingredients\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"How does organizing resources impact customer satisfaction?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It decreases customer satisfaction\",\n        \"It has no impact on customer satisfaction\",\n        \"It increases customer satisfaction by ensuring smooth operations\",\n        \"It only affects employee productivity\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of a supervisor in maintaining infrastructure?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To ensure infrastructure is properly maintained\",\n        \"To allocate tasks only\",\n        \"To manage finances only\",\n        \"To hire employees only\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 22,\n      \"question\": \"Why is efficient resource utilization important in manufacturing?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It increases costs\",\n        \"It ensures timely production and reduces delays\",\n        \"It disrupts workflow\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 23,\n      \"question\": \"What happens when resources are not efficiently utilized?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Efficiency increases\",\n        \"Costs decrease\",\n        \"Wastage reduces\",\n        \"Delays and inefficiencies occur\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"How does organizing physical resources impact the overall performance of an organization?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It decreases performance\",\n        \"It has no impact on performance\",\n        \"It improves performance by ensuring smooth operations\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"What is an example of organizing physical resources in a service industry?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Only in manufacturing\",\n        \"In a restaurant, ensuring kitchen equipment and ingredients are available\",\n        \"Only in non-profit organizations\",\n        \"Only in retail\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 26,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important for a supervisor to ensure that raw materials are available on time?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It increases costs\",\n        \"It ensures smooth production and reduces delays\",\n        \"It disrupts workflow\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 27,\n      \"question\": \"What is the impact of proper resource maintenance on safety?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces safety\",\n        \"It has no impact on safety\",\n        \"It improves safety by preventing accidents\",\n        \"It only affects efficiency\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 28,\n      \"question\": \"How does organizing resources affect the morale of employees?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It decreases morale\",\n        \"It has no impact on morale\",\n        \"It increases morale by providing necessary resources\",\n        \"It only affects productivity\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of a supervisor in ensuring that workers have the necessary tools?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To allocate tasks only\",\n        \"To ensure workers have necessary tools and resources\",\n        \"To manage finances only\",\n        \"To hire employees only\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important to arrange tables and chairs properly in a dining area?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces customer satisfaction\",\n        \"It has no impact on customer satisfaction\",\n        \"It improves customer satisfaction by creating a welcoming environment\",\n        \"It only affects employee productivity\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"What is an example of a physical resource in a manufacturing setting?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Only raw materials\",\n        \"Machines, tools, raw materials, and workspace\",\n        \"Only machines\",\n        \"Only workspace\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"How does organizing physical resources impact the quality of products or services?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It decreases quality\",\n        \"It has no impact on quality\",\n        \"It improves quality by ensuring necessary resources are available\",\n        \"It only affects customer satisfaction\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"What is the benefit of ensuring that finished products are moved efficiently?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It increases costs\",\n        \"It ensures timely delivery and reduces delays\",\n        \"It disrupts workflow\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important for a supervisor to ensure that refrigerators are in working condition?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It increases costs\",\n        \"It ensures food safety and quality\",\n        \"It disrupts workflow\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"What happens when a supervisor fails to allocate resources efficiently?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Efficiency increases\",\n        \"Costs decrease\",\n        \"Wastage reduces\",\n        \"Delays and inefficiencies occur\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"How does organizing physical resources impact the competitive advantage of an organization?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It decreases competitive advantage\",\n        \"It has no impact on competitive advantage\",\n        \"It improves competitive advantage by ensuring efficient operations\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of a supervisor in maintaining office supplies?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To ensure office supplies are available and used efficiently\",\n        \"To allocate tasks only\",\n        \"To manage finances only\",\n        \"To hire employees only\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important to ensure that workspace is properly arranged?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It has no impact on efficiency\",\n        \"It improves efficiency and safety by reducing clutter\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"What is the impact of efficient resource utilization on costs?\",\n      \"options\": [\