 Tasks to Individuals and Establishing Relationships Among Workers</h2>\n    <p>Once the resources are organized and the right people are selected for the right jobs, the next step is to properly divide and assign tasks among employees.</p>\n    \n    <h3>Steps in Task Allotment:</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Break down work into different tasks.</li>\n      <li>Assign tasks to workers based on their skills.</li>\n      <li>Establish a chain of command (who reports to whom).</li>\n      <li>Promote teamwork by ensuring employees work together efficiently.</li>\n      <li>Monitor and adjust if tasks need to be redistributed.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>Example:</h3>\n    <p>\n      <strong>? In a construction company:</strong>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Engineers design the building.</li>\n        <li>Workers lay bricks and mix cement.</li>\n        <li>Electricians install wiring.</li>\n        <li>Supervisors ensure everything happens on time.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </p>\n    \n    <p>\n      <strong>? In a school:</strong>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Teachers are assigned subjects based on expertise.</li>\n        <li>Administrative staff handle student records and fees.</li>\n        <li>The principal oversees the entire system and ensures smooth functioning.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </p>\n    \n    <h3>Why is establishing relationships among workers important?</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>It prevents confusion about roles and responsibilities.</li>\n      <li>Encourages teamwork and cooperation.</li>\n      <li>Helps in faster decision-making.</li>\n      <li>Reduces workplace conflicts by defining clear reporting structures.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>Conclusion</h3>\n    <p>At the supervisory level, organizing ensures that physical resources, human skills, and job roles are aligned properly. A supervisor must:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>✅ Organize physical resources to ensure smooth workflow.</li>\n      <li>✅ Match employee skills with job needs to improve productivit