    \"id\": 26,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that in a school, the principal oversees the entire system to ensure smooth functioning.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 27,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that establishing relationships among workers does not help in preventing confusion about roles.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 28,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that clear reporting structures reduce workplace conflicts.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that organizing physical resources is not essential for ensuring smooth workflow.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that matching employee skills with job needs does not improve productivity.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that allotting tasks and establishing relationships is crucial for a cooperative work environment.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that when these elements are handled efficiently, employees do not remain happy.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that business goals are achieved successfully when these elements are handled efficiently.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that task allotment involves assigning tasks based on skills and qualifications.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that establishing a chain of command is not important for decision-making.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that promoting teamwork is essential for efficient task completion.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that monitoring task assignments is not necessary for adjusting them.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that in a construction company, supervisors ensure that tasks are completed on time.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that in a school, teachers should be assigned subjects randomly.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that establishing relationships among workers helps in faster decision-making by defining clear roles.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 41,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that establishing clear reporting structures does not reduce workplace conflicts.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 42,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that organizing physical resources is essential for ensuring smooth workflow.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 43,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that matching employee skills with job needs does not improve job satisfaction.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 44,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that allotting tasks and establishing relationships is not necessary for a structured work environment.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 45,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that when these elements are handled efficiently, organizations do not achieve their goals.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 46,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that efficient task allotment and relationship establishment lead to unhappy employees.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that task allotment involves assigning tasks based on employee skills and qualifications.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that establishing a chain of command is not important for defining roles and responsibilities.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that promoting teamwork is not important for efficient task completion and cooperation.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that monitoring task assignments is crucial for ensuring tasks are completed efficiently.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    }\n]\n  ',14,13),(52,'3.1-Needs for Directions and Instructions to Subordinates','<div>\n    <h1>3.1 Needs for Directions and Instructions to Subordinates</h1>\n  \n    <h2>Why Do Employees Need Directions and Instructions?</h2>\n    <p>\n      Employees need clear directions and instructions to work efficiently. If instructions are unclear, employees may get confused, leading to mistakes, delays, or poor performance.\n    </p>\n  \n    <h2>Important Aspects of Giving Directions</h2>\n  \n    <h3>Clarity</h3>\n    <p>The supervisor must communicate clearly so that employees understand what needs to be done.</p>\n  \n    <h3>Completeness</h3>\n    <p>Instructions should cover all necessary details to avoid confusion.</p>\n  \n    <h3>Feasibility</h3>\n    <p>Instructions should be practical and realistic to implement.</p>\n  \n    <h2>Example</h2>\n    <p>Imagine a factory where workers assemble mobile phones. The supervisor must:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Clearly explain how to assemble each part.</li>\n      <li>Ensure workers know the safety rules.</li>\n      <li>Give step-by-step guidance to new workers.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p>If instructions are incomplete, workers may assemble parts incorrectly, leading to defective products.</p>\n</div>\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What is the primary function of directing at the supervisory level?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Planning the company\'s long-term goals\",\n        \"Guiding and supervising employees to perform tasks correctly\",\n        \"Managing financial accounts\",\n        \"Developing marketing strategies\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Why do employees need clear directions and instructions?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To increase confusion in the workplace\",\n        \"To work efficiently and avoid mistakes\",\n        \"To reduce their workload\",\n        \"To change company policies\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is NOT a key aspect of giving directions?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Clarity\",\n        \"Completeness\",\n        \"Feasibility\",\n        \"Uncertainty\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"What happens if instructions given to employees are unclear?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"They complete tasks faster\",\n        \"They may make mistakes or delay work\",\n        \"They require less supervision\",\n        \"They become more independent\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"What does ‘completeness’ mean in the context of giving instructions?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Providing only general guidelines\",\n        \"Ensuring instructions cover all necessary details\",\n        \"Giving minimal information\",\n        \"Letting employees figure out tasks on their own\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is an example of feasible instructions?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Asking workers to complete 100 tasks in 10 minutes\",\n        \"Providing realistic deadlines and available resources\",\n        \"Giving incomplete guidelines and expecting results\",\n        \"Assigning impossible targets without proper tools\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of a supervisor in directing employees?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Setting company policies\",\n        \"Supervising, guiding, and providing clear instructions\",\n        \"Handling customer complaints\",\n        \"Hiring new employees\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"If employees receive incomplete instructions, what may happen?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"They become more efficient\",\n        \"They perform tasks incorrectly or incompletely\",\n        \"They require no further supervision\",\n        \"They work faster without any errors\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"What is the first step in giving effective directions to employees?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Providing unclear and vague instructions\",\n        \"Clearly explaining what needs to be done\",\n        \"Assuming employees already know their tasks\",\n        \"Ignoring employee feedback\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"Which factor ensures that employees can follow instructions without difficulty?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Overcomplicating the instructions\",\n        \"Giving practical and realistic instructions\",\n        \"Not providing any details\",\n        \"Ignoring employee queries\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"What is the consequence of ineffective direction in the workplace?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Increased productivity\",\n        \"Delays, mistakes, and poor performance\",\n        \"Better teamwork\",\n        \"Stronger leadership\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is an example of proper workplace direction?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"‘Finish this as soon as possible’\",\n        \"‘Use these tools and follow this process step-by-step’\",\n        \"‘Figure it out on your own’\",\n        \"‘Do whatever you think is best’\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"What should a supervisor do if employees do not understand instructions?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Ignore their concerns\",\n        \"Explain the instructions more clearly\",\n        \"Punish them for not understanding\",\n        \"Give them a different task\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following improves employee performance?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Vague instructions\",\n        \"Clear and complete instructions\",\n        \"Lack of guidance\",\n        \"Unrealistic expectations\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"What is the main objective of directing employees?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To confuse them with unnecessary details\",\n        \"To guide them towards efficiency and success\",\n        \"To make their work more difficult\",\n        \"To delay projects\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"Which of these is NOT a good practice in giving instructions?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Using clear and simple language\",\n        \"Providing all necessary details\",\n        \"Setting unrealistic deadlines\",\n        \"Ensuring instructions are practical\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"Why is clarity important in workplace instructions?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It helps employees understand their tasks clearly\",\n        \"It makes work more confusing\",\n        \"It reduces employee motivation\",\n        \"It encourages employees to guess their duties\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"How can a supervisor make instructions more feasible?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"By setting achievable goals and deadlines\",\n        \"By demanding immediate completion of tasks\",\n        \"By ignoring resource availability\",\n        \"By assigning random tasks without planning\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is NOT a role of a supervisor in directing employees?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Providing clear instructions\",\n        \"Motivating employees\",\n        \"Setting company-wide policies\",\n        \"Monitoring employee performance\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"What is the result of giving detailed and structured instructions?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Increased confusion\",\n        \"Higher efficiency and better performance\",\n        \"More workplace conflicts\",\n        \"Lower productivity\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"Budgeting is the process of estimating and allocating ________ resources to different aspects of a project.\",\n      \"options\": [\"time\", \"financial\", \"human\", \"material\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Two important cost factors in any project are ________ and manpower.\",\n      \"options\": [\"materials\", \"marketing\", \"transportation\", \"insurance\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Materials include physical items like raw materials, tools, and ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"transportation\", \"workers\", \"equipment\", \"electricity\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"Manpower refers to the human resources required for a project, including ________ and unskilled workers.\",\n      \"options\": [\"machines\", \"skilled\", \"transporters\", \"accountants\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"Proper budgeting ensures that a project stays within ________ limits.\",\n      \"options\": [\"technical\", \"financial\", \"geographical\", \"legal\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"Before budgeting for materials, it is important to ________ all required materials.\",\n      \"options\": [\"discard\", \"purchase\", \"list\", \"ignore\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"Material costs should include actual price, transportation, and a ________ cost.\",\n      \"options\": [\"fixed\", \"hidden\", \"buffer\", \"random\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"One way to reduce material costs is to buy in ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"small amounts\", \"bulk\", \"credit\", \"random purchases\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"The workforce required for a project can be categorized as skilled and ________ workers.\",\n      \"options\": [\"government\", \"independent\", \"unskilled\", \"freelance\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"Labor costs depend on wages per hour or per ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"month\", \"year\", \"project\", \"worker\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"Directing at the supervisory level involves guiding, leading, and ________ employees.\",\n      \"options\": [\"monitoring\", \"punishing\", \"firing\", \"ignoring\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"Supervisors provide directions to ensure employees perform tasks ________ and efficiently.\",\n      \"options\": [\"slowly\", \"correctly\", \"randomly\", \"partially\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"One key responsibility of a supervisor is to provide ________ instructions.\",\n      \"options\": [\"unclear\", \"delayed\", \"clear\", \"complicated\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"Incomplete instructions can lead to ________ in the workplace.\",\n      \"options\": [\"confusion\", \"efficiency\", \"motivation\", \"growth\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"Supervisors must ensure that instructions are clear, complete, and ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"feasible\", \"unrealistic\", \"confusing\", \"random\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"Feasible instructions are those that are ________ to implement.\",\n      \"options\": [\"practical\", \"impossible\", \"confusing\", \"unnecessary\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"In a factory setting, supervisors must provide workers with clear steps to ________ products.\",\n      \"options\": [\"misplace\", \"assemble\", \"damage\", \"ignore\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"Poor directions can lead to mistakes, delays, or ________ performance.\",\n      \"options\": [\"excellent\", \"poor\", \"improved\", \"unexpected\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"A supervisor should make sure that employees understand their ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"salary\", \"tasks\", \"complaints\", \"vacations\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"Step-by-step guidance is particularly important for ________ employees.\",\n      \"options\": [\"experienced\", \"new\", \"retired\", \"senior\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that budgeting helps in estimating and allocating financial resources efficiently.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that manpower refers to only unskilled workers in a project.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that raw materials, tools, and equipment are considered essential materials for a project.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that estimating material costs does not include checking market prices from suppliers.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that buying materials in bulk can help in reducing costs.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that labor costs include only basic salaries and wages.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that manpower budgeting should consider benefits, insurance, and overtime pay.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that budgeting for manpower does not require identifying the number of workers needed.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that hiring only essential workers can help reduce manpower costs.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that supervisors do not play any role in organizing physical resources.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that organizing physical resources ensures a smooth workflow and reduces wastage.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that a restaurant supervisor does not need to organize ingredients and cooking equipment.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that matching employees to suitable jobs improves productivity and job satisfaction.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that work-life balance is not a factor in matching human needs with job needs.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that a software developer should be assigned programming tasks instead of customer support duties.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that junior nurses should handle critical patient care without proper training.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that a proper chain of command helps prevent confusion and promotes teamwork.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that engineers should handle brick-laying tasks on a construction site.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that task allotment ensures each worker knows their specific role.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that supervisors should not monitor and adjust task allotment.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that directing at the supervisory level involves guiding and supervising employees.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 22,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that incomplete instructions can improve workplace efficiency.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 23,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that clear instructions help avoid mistakes and delays in a project.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that feasibility of instructions is not important for employees.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that a supervisor must ensure that mobile phone assembly workers follow proper steps.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 26,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that feasibility in instructions means making them complicated.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 27,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that supervisors should explain tasks clearly to avoid defective products.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 28,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that training workers does not contribute to cost reduction.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that motivation plays an important role in improving worker performance.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that providing fair wages is unnecessary for employee motivation.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that discipline in the workplace ensures smooth operations.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that giving detailed instructions leads to confusion among workers.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that a supervisor’s role includes correcting mistakes made by employees.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that teamwork and cooperation are unimportant in an organization.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that establishing relationships among workers can reduce conflicts.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that a disorganized workplace leads to better productivity.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that organizing and budgeting go hand in hand in project planning.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that setting a realistic budget is unnecessary for project success.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that an efficient supervisor ensures both materials and manpower are well managed.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that unnecessary hiring of workers reduces manpower costs.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 41,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that work efficiency improves when tasks match employee skills.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 42,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that businesses do not need to plan for unexpected expenses.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 43,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that a clear reporting structure speeds up decision-making.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 44,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that supervisors do not need to track worker performance.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 45,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that reducing wastage of materials helps maintain the project budget.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 46,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that workers perform best when given unclear instructions.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that proper direction ensures employees stay motivated and productive.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that discipline in the workplace negatively impacts employee performance.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that a well-organized workplace increases overall efficiency.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that organizing tasks is unnecessary for company success.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    }\n]\n  ',14,14),(53,'3.2-Personal Counselling and Advanced Predictions of Possible Mistakes','<div>\n    <h1>3.2 Personal Counselling and Advanced Predictions of Possible Mistakes</h1>\n\n    <h2>What is Personal Counselling?</h2>\n    <p>Supervisors often guide employees not only on work-related issues but also on personal matters that affect their performance. This is called personal counselling. It helps employees stay focused, motivated, and stress-free.</p>\n\n    <h2>Predicting Mistakes in Advance</h2>\n    <p>A good supervisor can foresee possible mistakes and take steps to prevent them.</p>\n\n    <h3>Example:</h3>\n    \n    <h4>Personal Counselling:</h4>\n    <p>If an employee is frequently absent due to personal problems, the supervisor can talk to them, understand their issues, and offer flexible work options.</p>\n\n    <h4>Predicting Mistakes:</h4>\n    <p>In a bakery, if workers are rushing, they might mix ingredients incorrectly. A supervisor can prevent this by reminding them to double-check measurements.</p>\n</div>','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What is personal counselling in the workplace?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Providing financial advice to employees\",\n        \"Guiding employees on both work and personal matters affecting performance\",\n        \"Helping employees find another job\",\n        \"Training employees in technical skills only\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Why is personal counselling important for employees?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It helps them focus, stay motivated, and reduce stress\",\n        \"It makes them work extra hours\",\n        \"It helps them switch to a different job\",\n        \"It increases their workload\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is NOT a purpose of personal counselling?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To improve employee performance\",\n        \"To help employees manage personal issues affecting work\",\n        \"To create conflicts among employees\",\n        \"To motivate employees\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"What can a supervisor do if an employee is frequently absent due to personal problems?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Ignore the issue\",\n        \"Talk to the employee and offer possible solutions\",\n        \"Fire the employee immediately\",\n        \"Reduce the employee\'s salary\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"How can personal counselling benefit an organization?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"By reducing employee turnover\",\n        \"By increasing employee stress\",\n        \"By making employees work overtime\",\n        \"By delaying project deadlines\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"What does predicting mistakes in advance mean?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Guessing that employees will make mistakes\",\n        \"Identifying potential errors before they happen and taking preventive actions\",\n        \"Blaming employees before they make a mistake\",\n        \"Encouraging employees to make errors\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is an example of advanced mistake prediction?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Ignoring workplace errors\",\n        \"Waiting for mistakes to happen before taking action\",\n        \"Reminding workers to double-check measurements in a bakery\",\n        \"Not providing employees with any instructions\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"Why should supervisors predict mistakes in advance?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To increase workplace errors\",\n        \"To reduce mistakes and improve efficiency\",\n        \"To punish employees\",\n        \"To make work more difficult\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of a supervisor in personal counselling?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To provide legal advice to employees\",\n        \"To support employees in resolving personal or work-related challenges\",\n        \"To encourage employees to quit their jobs\",\n        \"To avoid interacting with employees\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"What happens if a supervisor fails to predict possible mistakes?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Employees will work more efficiently\",\n        \"Errors may increase, leading to losses\",\n        \"Work quality will improve\",\n        \"Productivity will rise\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is a good approach to personal counselling?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Blaming employees for their problems\",\n        \"Listening to employees and providing support\",\n        \"Avoiding personal discussions with employees\",\n        \"Ignoring employee concerns\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"Which of these is an example of workplace mistake prediction?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Supervisors reminding workers to follow safety procedures\",\n        \"Allowing workers to complete tasks without guidance\",\n        \"Encouraging employees to work faster without checking quality\",\n        \"Avoiding training sessions\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"How can supervisors prevent errors in production?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"By not monitoring the process\",\n        \"By regularly checking the workflow and reminding workers of best practices\",\n        \"By reducing the number of employees\",\n        \"By increasing employee workloads\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"What should a supervisor do when an employee faces personal difficulties?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Ignore the employee\'s problems\",\n        \"Provide guidance and offer flexible work arrangements if possible\",\n        \"Criticize the employee for being unprofessional\",\n        \"Reduce the employee\'s salary\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is NOT an advantage of personal counselling?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Helps employees stay motivated\",\n        \"Improves employee performance\",\n        \"Increases employee stress\",\n        \"Reduces workplace conflicts\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"How does predicting mistakes in advance help a company?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"By reducing errors and improving efficiency\",\n        \"By increasing production costs\",\n        \"By making employees take longer breaks\",\n        \"By causing delays in work completion\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"What is an example of an ineffective counselling approach?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Listening to employees and offering support\",\n        \"Ignoring employee concerns\",\n        \"Providing career development advice\",\n        \"Helping employees manage work stress\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is a preventive step a supervisor can take to avoid mistakes?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Providing clear instructions before starting a task\",\n        \"Not giving any training to employees\",\n        \"Blaming employees for every small error\",\n        \"Ignoring employee suggestions\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"Why should supervisors provide personal counselling to employees?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To help employees deal with personal and work-related challenges\",\n        \"To interfere in employees\' personal lives\",\n        \"To reduce employee motivation\",\n        \"To avoid interacting with employees\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"What should a supervisor do if they predict a possible mistake in the workplace?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Ignore it and wait for the mistake to happen\",\n        \"Take proactive steps to prevent the mistake\",\n        \"Blame employees in advance\",\n        \"Increase employees\' workload as punishment\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"Personal counselling involves guiding employees on both work-related issues and ________ matters.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"financial\",\n        \"personal\",\n        \"professional\",\n        \"educational\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"The primary goal of personal counselling is to help employees stay ________ and motivated.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"stressed\",\n        \"focused\",\n        \"overworked\",\n        \"unmotivated\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"A supervisor who offers personal counselling can help employees manage ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"workload\",\n        \"stress\",\n        \"finances\",\n        \"time\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"Predicting mistakes in advance allows supervisors to take ________ measures.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"reactive\",\n        \"preventive\",\n        \"corrective\",\n        \"proactive\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"In a bakery, rushing workers might ________ ingredients incorrectly.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"measure\",\n        \"mix\",\n        \"bake\",\n        \"store\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"A supervisor can prevent mistakes by reminding workers to ________ measurements.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"ignore\",\n        \"guess\",\n        \"double-check\",\n        \"skip\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"Personal counselling helps employees deal with ________ problems that affect their performance.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"work-related\",\n        \"financial\",\n        \"personal\",\n        \"health-related\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"Supervisors use personal counselling to address issues that impact an employee\'s ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"productivity\",\n        \"motivation\",\n        \"focus\",\n        \"all of the above\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"Predicting mistakes helps supervisors maintain a ________ work environment.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"chaotic\",\n        \"safe\",\n        \"efficient\",\n        \"stressful\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"Flexible work options are often offered as part of personal counselling to help employees manage ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"workload\",\n        \"stress\",\n        \"personal issues\",\n        \"time\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"A supervisor who predicts mistakes can ________ potential problems before they occur.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"ignore\",\n        \"create\",\n        \"identify\",\n        \"solve\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"Personal counselling is beneficial for employees who are frequently absent due to ________ problems.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"health\",\n        \"financial\",\n        \"personal\",\n        \"work-related\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"Supervisors use personal counselling to improve employee ________ and motivation.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"focus\",\n        \"productivity\",\n        \"stress levels\",\n        \"all of the above\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"Predicting mistakes in advance helps supervisors ________ errors before they happen.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"create\",\n        \"ignore\",\n        \"prevent\",\n        \"fix\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"Personal counselling involves understanding an employee\'s ________ issues.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"work-related\",\n        \"financial\",\n        \"personal\",\n        \"educational\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"A supervisor can offer ________ work arrangements as part of personal counselling.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"inflexible\",\n        \"flexible\",\n        \"standard\",\n        \"rigid\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"Predicting mistakes helps supervisors maintain a ________ workflow.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"disorganized\",\n        \"smooth\",\n        \"inefficient\",\n        \"chaotic\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"Personal counselling helps employees manage ________ that affect their work performance.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"work-related stress\",\n        \"personal issues\",\n        \"financial problems\",\n        \"all of the above\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"A good supervisor can foresee ________ mistakes and take preventive measures.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"unexpected\",\n        \"common\",\n        \"possible\",\n        \"impossible\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"Personal counselling is important for maintaining a ________ work environment.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"stressful\",\n        \"supportive\",\n        \"competitive\",\n        \"hostile\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"Predicting mistakes allows supervisors to implement ________ strategies.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"reactive\",\n        \"preventive\",\n        \"corrective\",\n        \"proactive\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 22,\n      \"question\": \"Personal counselling helps employees stay ________ and focused.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"stressed\",\n        \"motivated\",\n        \"overworked\",\n        \"unmotivated\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 23,\n      \"question\": \"A supervisor who predicts mistakes can ________ potential errors before they occur.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"ignore\",\n        \"create\",\n        \"identify\",\n        \"solve\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"Personal counselling involves addressing ________ issues that impact employee performance.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"work-related\",\n        \"financial\",\n        \"personal\",\n        \"educational\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"Predicting mistakes helps supervisors maintain a ________ workplace.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"safe\",\n        \"efficient\",\n        \"stressful\",\n        \"chaotic\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 26,\n      \"question\": \"A supervisor can use personal counselling to help employees manage ________ problems.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"work-related\",\n        \"financial\",\n        \"personal\",\n        \"health-related\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 27,\n      \"question\": \"Predicting mistakes allows supervisors to take ________ action before errors occur.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"reactive\",\n        \"preventive\",\n        \"corrective\",\n        \"proactive\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 28,\n      \"question\": \"Personal counselling is beneficial for employees dealing with ________ issues.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"work-related\",\n        \"financial\",\n        \"personal\",\n        \"educational\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"A supervisor who predicts mistakes can help prevent ________ errors.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"minor\",\n        \"major\",\n        \"common\",\n        \"all of the above\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"Personal counselling helps employees stay ________ and stress-free.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"focused\",\n        \"motivated\",\n        \"overworked\",\n        \"unmotivated\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"Predicting mistakes in advance helps supervisors ________ potential problems.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"ignore\",\n        \"create\",\n        \"identify\",\n        \"solve\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"A supervisor can offer personal counselling to help employees manage ________ that affect their work.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"work-related stress\",\n        \"personal issues\",\n        \"financial problems\",\n        \"all of the above\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"Predicting mistakes helps supervisors maintain a ________ workflow by preventing errors.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"disorganized\",\n        \"smooth\",\n        \"inefficient\",\n        \"chaotic\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"Personal counselling involves guiding employees on both work-related and ________ issues.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"financial\",\n        \"personal\",\n        \"professional\",\n        \"educational\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"A supervisor who predicts mistakes can help prevent ________ in the workplace.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"errors\",\n        \"accidents\",\n        \"conflicts\",\n        \"all of the above\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"Personal counselling helps employees stay ________ and motivated by addressing personal issues.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"stressed\",\n        \"focused\",\n        \"overworked\",\n        \"unmotivated\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"Predicting mistakes allows supervisors to implement ________ measures to prevent errors.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"reactive\",\n        \"preventive\",\n        \"corrective\",\n        \"proactive\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"A supervisor can use personal counselling to help employees manage ________ problems that impact their performance.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"work-related\",\n        \"financial\",\n 