al counselling is beneficial for employees dealing with personal issues that impact their performance.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that predicting mistakes is a proactive strategy for preventing errors.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that personal counselling helps employees stay focused and stress-free.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    }\n]\n  ',14,14),(54,'3.3-Elaborating Decisions and Laying Disciplinary Standards in Overall Working','<div>\n    <h2>3.3 Elaborating Decisions and Laying Disciplinary Standards in Overall Working</h2>\n    \n    <h3>Making Decisions Clear</h3>\n    <p>A supervisor must explain the reasons behind their decisions so that employees understand their importance and follow them willingly.</p>\n    \n    <h3>Laying Disciplinary Standards</h3>\n    <p>Every workplace has rules that employees must follow. A supervisor ensures that:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Employees come to work on time.</li>\n      <li>Work is done as per company guidelines.</li>\n      <li>There is no misconduct like stealing, dishonesty, or poor behavior.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>Example:</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>In a call center, if an employee speaks rudely to a customer, the supervisor must explain the company’s customer service rules and take disciplinary action if needed.</li>\n      <li>In a hospital, nurses must follow strict hygiene rules. If someone doesn’t, the supervisor must correct them immediately to ensure patient safety.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>Conclusion</h3>\n    <p>Directing at the supervisory level is about guiding employees properly, predicting and preventing mistakes, and ensuring discipline in the workplace.</p>\n    <p>A good supervisor communicates clearly, supports employees, and enforces company rules effectively.</p>\n</div>\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What is a key responsibility of a supervisor when making decisions?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To make decisions without explanation\",\n        \"To explain the reasons behind their decisions\",\n        \"To ignore employee feedback\",\n        \"To make decisions based on personal preference\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important for a supervisor to explain their decisions?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"So employees can question them\",\n        \"So employees understand and follow them willingly\",\n        \"So employees can ignore them\",\n        \"So employees can complain about them\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"What is one of the disciplinary standards that a supervisor ensures?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Employees can be late to work\",\n        \"Employees must come to work on time\",\n        \"Employees can take long breaks\",\n        \"Employees can leave early\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"What type of behavior is considered misconduct in the workplace?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Honesty and integrity\",\n        \"Stealing, dishonesty, or poor behavior\",\n        \"Punctuality and respect\",\n        \"Teamwork and cooperation\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"In a call center, what action should a supervisor take if an employee speaks rudely to a customer?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Ignore the behavior\",\n        \"Explain the company’s customer service rules and take disciplinary action if needed\",\n        \"Fire the employee immediately\",\n        \"Promote the employee\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important for nurses to follow strict hygiene rules in a hospital?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To maintain hospital decor\",\n        \"To ensure patient safety\",\n        \"To reduce costs\",\n        \"To increase workload\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"What is a key aspect of directing at the supervisory level?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Ignoring employee needs\",\n        \"Guiding employees properly and enforcing discipline\",\n        \"Focusing solely on productivity\",\n        \"Disregarding company rules\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"How should a supervisor communicate decisions to employees?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Clearly and with explanation\",\n        \"Vaguely and without explanation\",\n        \"Only to certain employees\",\n        \"Not at all\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"What is the purpose of laying disciplinary standards in the workplace?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To create a hostile work environment\",\n        \"To ensure employees follow company rules and maintain a professional environment\",\n        \"To reduce employee morale\",\n        \"To increase employee turnover\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"What should a supervisor do if an employee does not follow company guidelines?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Ignore the behavior\",\n        \"Correct the employee and ensure they follow guidelines\",\n        \"Fire the employee immediately\",\n        \"Promote the employee\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important for a supervisor to support employees?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"So employees can work independently without guidance\",\n        \"So employees feel valued and supported in their roles\",\n        \"So employees can ignore company rules\",\n        \"So employees can work less efficiently\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"What is a characteristic of a good supervisor?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"They communicate poorly and do not support employees\",\n        \"They communicate clearly, support employees, and enforce company rules effectively\",\n        \"They focus solely on productivity\",\n        \"They disregard employee feedback\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"In what setting is following strict hygiene rules particularly important?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Office environment\",\n        \"Hospital setting\",\n        \"Retail store\",\n        \"Restaurant\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"What action should a supervisor take if an employee is consistently late?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Ignore the behavior\",\n        \"Address the issue and ensure the employee understands the importance of punctuality\",\n        \"Fire the employee immediately\",\n        \"Promote the employee\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"Why is explaining decisions important for employee engagement?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It makes employees feel undervalued\",\n        \"It helps employees understand and follow decisions willingly\",\n        \"It reduces employee morale\",\n        \"It increases employee turnover\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"What type of behavior is expected from employees in a professional setting?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Misconduct like stealing or dishonesty\",\n        \"Professionalism and respect\",\n        \"Poor behavior and rudeness\",\n        \"Laziness and lack of effort\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"How should a supervisor handle misconduct 