 \"It is false that predicting mistakes is crucial for maintaining a safe workplace.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that a supervisor should support employees to enhance their focus and productivity.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that a supervisor should ignore misconduct in the workplace.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that explaining decisions helps employees understand the importance behind them.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that a supervisor should enforce company rules to maintain professionalism.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that predicting mistakes is a proactive strategy for preventing errors.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that a supervisor should correct an employee who does not follow hygiene rules in a hospital.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that effective supervisory direction involves guiding employees properly and enforcing discipline effectively.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that a supervisor should communicate clearly to ensure employees understand decisions.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 41,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that laying disciplinary standards helps prevent misconduct in the workplace.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 42,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that a supervisor should ignore an employee who speaks rudely to a customer.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 43,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that a supervisor should handle misconduct promptly and take disciplinary action if necessary.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 44,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that a supervisor’s role involves guiding employees poorly and ignoring company rules.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 45,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that predicting mistakes in advance helps maintain a smooth workflow.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 46,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that explaining decisions clearly reduces employee satisfaction.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that a supervisor should communicate clearly to ensure employees understand and follow decisions willingly.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that a supervisor should correct an employee who does not follow company guidelines.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that laying disciplinary standards helps maintain a professional and respectful work environment.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that predicting mistakes is not important for maintaining a safe and efficient work environment.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    }\n]\n  ',14,14),(55,'3.4-Managerial Control','<div>\n    <h2>3.4 Managerial Control</h2>\n    <h3>Understanding Teams and the Link Between Various Departments</h3>\n    <p>Every company has multiple departments, such as production, sales, finance, human resources, and customer service. For an organization to function smoothly, all these departments must work together.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A mobile phone manufacturing company has:</li>\n      <ul>\n        <li>A design team that creates the phone model.</li>\n        <li>A production team that assembles the phone.</li>\n        <li>A quality control team that checks if the phone meets standards.</li>\n        <li>A sales team that markets and sells the phone.</li>\n        <li>A customer service team that handles complaints.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </ul>\n    <p>If the quality control team finds defects in the phone, they must inform the production team to fix them before selling. This link between departments ensures quality products and customer satisfaction.</p>\n    \n    <h3>Process and Quality Standards</h3>\n    <p>Every company sets standards to maintain quality and efficiency. These standards define how products or services should be delivered.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A fast-food chain like McDonald\'s has strict standards:</li>\n      <ul>\n        <li>A burger must be made in 5 minutes.</li>\n        <li>The temperature of the patty must be at least 70°C.</li>\n        <li>Customer waiting time should not exceed 3 minutes.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </ul>\n    <p>If employees fail to meet these standards, the supervisor must take corrective action.</p>\n    \n    <h3>Steps in the Control Process</h3>\n    <p>The control process has four main steps:</p>\n    \n    <h4>1. Setting Performance Standards</h4>\n    <p>A standard is a benchmark that employees must follow. It can be related to quality, quantity, cost, or time.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A car manufacturing company may set a standard that:</li>\n      <ul>\n        <li>A worker must assemble 10 car engines per day.</li>\n        <li>The rejection rate (defective products) should be less than 2%.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h4>2. Measuring Performance</h4>\n    <p>The next step is to track actual performance and see if employees are meeting the set standards.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>A supervisor in a call center checks how many calls each agent attends in a day and whether they resolve customer issues.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h4>3. Comparing Performance with Standards</h4>\n    <p>After measuring performance, managers compare the results with the set standards.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>If the target is 10 car engines per day and a worker makes only 7, there is a shortfall.</li>\n      <li>If a call center expects agents to solve 90% of customer complaints but they solve only 75%, performance is low.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h4>4. Correcting Unfavorable Deviations</h4>\n    <p>If actual performance is below the standard, corrective action is needed.</p>\n    <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>If a worker assembles only 7 car engines instead of 10, the supervisor may provide training or add more workers.</li>\n      <li>If a call center agent is not solving complaints properly, they may receive extra coaching.</li>\n    </ul>\n</div>\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What is the primary purpose of controlling in management?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To plan organizational goals\",\n        \"To organize resources\",\n        \"To ensure activities are carried out as per the plan\",\n        \"To direct employee tasks\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"At the supervisory level, what does controlling focus on?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Only monitoring employees\",\n        \"Only maintaining quality\",\n        \"Monitoring employees, maintaining quality, and ensuring work is completed on time and within budget\",\n        \"Only ensuring work is completed on time\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"What is the first step in the control process?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Measuring performance\",\n        \"Comparing performance with standards\",\n        \"Setting performance standards\",\n        \"Correcting unfavorable deviations\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"Why is setting performance standards important?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It has no impact on efficiency\",\n        \"It provides a benchmark for evaluating performance\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"What happens when performance is not measured regularly?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Efficiency increases\",\n        \"Deviation from standards decreases\",\n        \"Deviation from standards increases and efficiency decreases\",\n        \"Work quality improves\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"In a car manufacturing company, what might be a performance standard?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Assembling 5 car engines per day\",\n        \"Assembling 10 car engines per day with a rejection rate below 2%\",\n        \"Assembling 15 car engines per day\",\n        \"Assembling car engines without any standards\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"Why is comparing actual performance with standards important?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It has no impact on efficiency\",\n        \"It helps identify deviations and take corrective actions\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"What happens if actual performance is below the standard?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"No action is needed\",\n        \"Corrective action is needed\",\n        \"Performance standards are lowered\",\n        \"Employee morale increases\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"In a call center, what might be a performance standard?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Solving 50% of customer complaints\",\n        \"Solving 90% of customer complaints\",\n        \"Solving 100% of customer complaints\",\n        \"No standard for solving complaints\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"Why is maintaining quality important in controlling?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces customer satisfaction\",\n        \"It has no impact on customer satisfaction\",\n        \"It improves customer satisfaction by ensuring products meet standards\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"How does controlling impact organizational goals?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It decreases the likelihood of achieving goals\",\n        \"It has no impact on achieving goals\",\n        \"It increases the likelihood of achieving goals by ensuring activities align with plans\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of a supervisor in controlling?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To plan organizational goals\",\n        \"To organize resources\",\n        \"To monitor performance and take corrective actions\",\n        \"To direct employee tasks only\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important to ensure work is completed within budget?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It has no impact on efficiency\",\n        \"It ensures financial sustainability and resource optimization\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"What happens when departments do not work together effectively?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Efficiency increases\",\n        \"Quality improves\",\n        \"Efficiency decreases and quality is compromised\",\n        \"Customer satisfaction increases\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"In a mobile phone manufacturing company, why is it important for the quality control team to inform the production team about defects?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To reduce quality standards\",\n        \"To increase production speed\",\n        \"To ensure quality products and customer satisfaction\",\n        \"To eliminate the quality control team\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"What is the benefit of setting strict standards in a fast-food chain like McDonald\'s?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It has no impact on efficiency\",\n        \"It ensures consistent quality and customer satisfaction\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important to take corrective action when performance deviates from standards?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It has no impact on efficiency\",\n        \"It ensures that activities align with plans and goals\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"How does controlling impact employee morale?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It decreases morale\",\n        \"It has no impact on morale\",\n        \"It increases morale by providing clear expectations and feedback\",\n        \"It only affects productivity\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of a supervisor in maintaining quality standards?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To reduce quality standards\",\n        \"To have no impact on quality standards\",\n        \"To ensure products or services meet quality standards\",\n        \"To eliminate quality control\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important to monitor performance regularly?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It has no impact on efficiency\",\n        \"It helps identify deviations and take corrective actions\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"What happens when corrective actions are not taken when performance deviates from standards?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Efficiency increases\",\n        \"Deviation from standards decreases\",\n        \"Deviation from standards increases and efficiency decreases\",\n        \"Work quality improves\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 22,\n      \"question\": \"How does controlling impact organizational culture?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It decreases positive culture\",\n        \"It has no impact on culture\",\n        \"It improves culture by promoting accountability and efficiency\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 23,\n      \"question\": \"What is the benefit of ensuring that work is completed on time?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It has no impact on efficiency\",\n        \"It improves efficiency and customer satisfaction\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important for departments to work together effectively?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It has no impact on efficiency\",\n        \"It improves efficiency and quality by ensuring coordinated efforts\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"What is an example of controlling in a call center?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Not monitoring agent performance\",\n        \"Monitoring agent performance and taking corrective actions\",\n        \"Reducing quality standards\",\n        \"Eliminating performance standards\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 26,\n      \"question\": \"How does controlling impact organizational reputation?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It decreases reputation\",\n        \"It has no impact on reputation\",\n        \"It improves reputation by ensuring quality and efficiency\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 27,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important to ensure that products meet quality standards?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces customer satisfaction\",\n        \"It has no impact on customer satisfaction\",\n        \"It improves customer satisfaction by ensuring quality products\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 28,\n      \"question\": \"What happens when quality standards are not maintained?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Customer satisfaction increases\",\n        \"Efficiency increases\",\n        \"Customer satisfaction decreases and efficiency is compromised\",\n        \"Work quality improves\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"How does controlling impact employee productivity?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It decreases productivity\",\n        \"It has no impact on productivity\",\n        \"It increases productivity by providing clear expectations and feedback\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of a supervisor in ensuring that work is completed within budget?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To have no impact on budget\",\n        \"To ensure work is completed within budget to maintain financial sustainability\",\n        \"To reduce quality standards\",\n        \"To eliminate budget constraints\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important to compare actual performance with standards?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It has no impact on efficiency\",\n        \"It helps identify deviations and take corrective actions\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"What happens when performance standards are not set clearly?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Efficiency increases\",\n        \"Deviation from standards decreases\",\n        \"Deviation from standards increases and efficiency decreases\",\n        \"Work quality improves\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"How does controlling impact organizational adaptability?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It decreases adaptability\",\n        \"It has no impact on adaptability\",\n        \"It improves adaptability by ensuring flexibility in response to deviations\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"What is the benefit of ensuring that departments work together effectively?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It has no impact on efficiency\",\n        \"It improves efficiency and quality by ensuring coordinated efforts\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important to take corrective actions promptly?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It has no impact on efficiency\",\n        \"It ensures that activities align with plans and goals\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"What happens when corrective actions are delayed?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Efficiency increases\",\n        \"Deviation from standards decreases\",\n        \"Deviation from standards increases and efficiency decreases\",\n        \"Work quality improves\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"How does controlling impact employee retention?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It decreases retention\",\n        \"It has no impact on retention\",\n        \"It increases retention by providing clear expectations and feedback\",\n        \"It only affects productivity\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of a supervisor in maintaining performance standards?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To reduce performance standards\",\n        \"To have no impact on performance standards\",\n        \"To ensure performance standards are met and maintained\",\n        \"To eliminate performance standards\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important to ensure that work is completed on time and within budget?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It has no impact on efficiency\",\n        \"It improves efficiency and financial sustainability\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"What happens when quality control is not effective?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Customer satisfaction increases\",\n        \"Efficiency increases\",\n        \"Customer satisfaction decreases and efficiency is compromised\",\n        \"Work quality improves\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 41,\n      \"question\": \"How does controlling impact organizational sustainability?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It decreases sustainability\",\n        \"It has no impact on sustainability\",\n        \"It improves sustainability by ensuring efficient resource use\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 42,\n      \"question\": \"What is the benefit of having a structured control process?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It has no impact on efficiency\",\n        \"It improves efficiency by ensuring activities align with plans\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 43,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important for a supervisor to monitor employee performance regularly?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces efficiency\",\n        \"It has no impact on efficiency\",\n        \"It helps identify deviations and take corrective actions\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 44,\n      \"question\": \"What happens when performance is not compared with standards?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Efficiency increases\",\n        \"Deviation from standards decreases\",\n        \"Deviation from standards increases and efficiency decreases\",\n        \"Work quality improves\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 45,\n      \"question\": \"How does controlling impact employee engagement?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It decreases engagement\",\n        \"It has no impact on engagement\",\n        \"It increases engagement by providing clear expectations and feedback\",\n        \"It only affects productivity\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 46,\n      \"question\": \"What is the role of a supervisor in ensuring that corrective actions are taken promptly?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To delay corrective actions\",\n        \"To have no impact on corrective actions\",\n        \"To ensure corrective actions are taken promptly to address deviations\",\n        \"To eliminate corrective actions\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important to maintain quality standards in a fast-food chain?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It reduces customer satisfaction\",\n        \"It has no impact on customer satisfaction\",\n        \"It improves customer satisfaction by ensuring consistent quality\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"What happens when departments do not communicate effectively?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Efficiency increases\",\n        \"Quality improves\",\n        \"Efficiency decreases and quality is compromised\",\n        \"Customer satisfaction increases\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"How does controlling impact organizational innovation?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It decreases innovation\",\n        \"It has no impact on innovation\",\n        \"It improves innovation by ensuring flexibility and adaptability\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"What is the overall impact of effective controlling on organizational performance?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It decreases performance\",\n        \"It has no impact on performance\",\n        \"It improves performance by ensuring activities align with plans and goals\",\n        \"It only affects employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"Controlling in management is the process of ensuring that all activities are carried out as per the ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"budget\",\n        \"plan\",\n        \"schedule\",\n        \"policy\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"At the supervisory level, controlling focuses on monitoring employees, maintaining ________, and ensuring work is completed on time.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"quantity\",\n        \"quality\",\n        \"cost\",\n        \"efficiency\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"The controlling process helps managers take ________ actions if there are any mistakes or deviations.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"preventive\",\n        \"corrective\",\n        \"proactive\",\n        \"reactive\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"In a company with multiple departments, controlling ensures that all departments work together ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"independently\",\n        \"separately\",\n        \"cooperatively\",\n        \"competitively\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"A mobile phone manufacturing company has a ________ team that checks if the phone meets standards.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"design\",\n        \"production\",\n        \"quality control\",\n        \"sales\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"If the quality control team finds defects, they must inform the ________ team to fix them.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"design\",\n        \"production\",\n        \"sales\",\n        \"customer service\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"Companies set ________ to maintain quality and efficiency in delivering products or services.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"policies\",\n        \"standards\",\n        \"procedures\",\n        \"guidelines\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"A fast-food chain like McDonald\'s has strict standards for making a burger, including a time limit of ________ minutes.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"3\",\n        \"5\",\n        \"10\",\n        \"15\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"If employees fail to meet standards, the supervisor must take ________ action.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"preventive\",\n        \"corrective\",\n        \"proactive\",\n        \"reactive\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"The control process involves setting ________ that employees must follow.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"policies\",\n        \"standards\",\n        \"procedures\",\n        \"guidelines\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"A car manufacturing company may set a standard that a worker must assemble ________ car engines per day.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"5\",\n        \"7\",\n        \"10\",\n        \"15\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"The next step in the control process is to ________ actual performance against set standards.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"measure\",\n        \"compare\",\n        \"correct\",\n        \"ignore\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"A supervisor in a call center checks how many calls each agent attends in a day to ________ performance.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"measure\",\n        \"compare\",\n        \"correct\",\n        \"ignore\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"After measuring performance, managers ________ the results with the set standards.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"compare\",\n        \"measure\",\n        \"correct\",\n        \"ignore\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"If actual performance is below the standard, managers take ________ action.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"preventive\",\n        \"corrective\",\n        \"proactive\",\n        \"reactive\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"If a worker assembles only 7 car engines instead of 10, the supervisor may provide ________ or add more workers.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"training\",\n        \"equipment\",\n        \"staff\",\n        \"resources\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"Controlling ensures that organizational resources are used ________ and efficiently.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"ineffectively\",\n        \"effectively\",\n        \"inefficiently\",\n        \"efficiently\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"The control process measures the deviation of actual performance from the ________ performance.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"standard\",\n        \"expected\",\n        \"planned\",\n        \"desired\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"Controlling helps in identifying the causes of deviations and taking ________ actions.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"preventive\",\n        \"corrective\",\n        \"proactive\",\n        \"reactive\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"Effective controlling creates an orderly and ________ atmosphere in the workplace.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"disciplined\",\n        \"relaxed\",\n        \"chaotic\",\n        \"unstructured\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"Controlling ensures that all departments are monitored according to ________ standards.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"predetermined\",\n        \"predefined\",\n        \"pre-established\",\n        \"all of the above\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 22,\n      \"question\": \"Controlling is a function that helps managers identify areas of ________ and celebrate successes.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"improvement\",\n        \"failure\",\n        \"success\",\n        \"growth\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 23,\n      \"question\": \"The primary goal of controlling is to ensure that organizational goals are achieved by guiding the team towards ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"objectives\",\n        \"goals\",\n        \"targets\",\n        \"standards\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"Controlling involves setting processes to guide the team towards ________ and monitoring performance.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"goals\",\n        \"objectives\",\n        \"targets\",\n        \"standards\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"The control process is highly intertwined with the ________ phase of management.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"planning\",\n        \"organizing\",\n        \"staffing\",\n        \"directing\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 26,\n      \"question\": \"Controlling is a systematic exercise that involves checking actual performance against ________ standards or plans.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"pre-determined\",\n        \"pre-defined\",\n        \"pre-established\",\n        \"all of the above\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 27,\n      \"question\": \"Controlling is a pervasive function because it is performed by managers at all ________ of the organization.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"levels\",\n        \"departments\",\n        \"teams\",\n        \"divisions\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 28,\n      \"question\": \"Controlling is a dynamic process that requires taking ________ methods and making changes as needed.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"preventive\",\n        \"corrective\",\n        \"proactive\",\n        \"revival\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"Controlling is related to ________ because both functions are inseparable in management.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"planning\",\n        \"organizing\",\n        \"staffing\",\n        \"directing\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"The steps in the controlling function include establishing ________, measuring performance, comparing actual with standard performance, and taking remedial measures.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"standards\",\n        \"policies\",\n        \"procedures\",\n        \"guidelines\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"In a mobile phone manufacturing company, the design team creates the phone model, while the production team ________ the phone.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"designs\",\n        \"assembles\",\n        \"markets\",\n        \"sells\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"The quality control team checks if the phone meets ________ standards.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"quality\",\n        \"production\",\n        \"sales\",\n        \"customer service\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"If defects are found, the quality control team informs the ________ team to fix them.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"design\",\n        \"production\",\n        \"sales\",\n        \"customer service\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"Companies set standards to maintain ________ and efficiency in delivering products or services.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"quality\",\n        \"quantity\",\n        \"cost\",\n        \"time\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"A fast-food chain like McDonald\'s has strict standards for making a burger within a time limit of ________ minutes.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"3\",\n        \"5\",\n        \"10\",\n        \"15\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"If employees fail to meet standards, the supervisor must take ________ action to correct the issue.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"preventive\",\n        \"corrective\",\n        \"proactive\",\n        \"reactive\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"The control process involves setting ________ that employees must follow to ensure quality and efficiency.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"policies\",\n        \"standards\",\n        \"procedures\",\n        \"guidelines\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"A car manufacturing company may set a standard that a worker must assemble ________ car engines per day to meet production targets.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"5\",\n        \"7\",\n        \"10\",\n        \"15\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"The next step in the control process is to ________ actual performance against set standards to identify deviations.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"measure\",\n        \"compare\",\n        \"correct\",\n        \"ignore\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"A supervisor in a call center checks how many calls each agent attends in a day to ________ performance and identify areas for improvement.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"measure\",\n        \"compare\",\n        \"correct\",\n        \"ignore\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 41,\n      \"question\": \"After measuring performance, managers ________ the results with the set standards to determine if corrective action is needed.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"compare\",\n        \"measure\",\n        \"correct\",\n        \"ignore\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 42,\n      \"question\": \"If actual performance is below the standard, managers take ________ action to address the deviation.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"preventive\",\n        \"corrective\",\n        \"proactive\",\n        \"reactive\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 43,\n      \"question\": \"If a worker assembles only 7 car engines instead of 10, the supervisor may provide ________ or add more resources.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"training\",\n        \"equipment\",\n        \"staff\",\n        \"resources\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 44,\n      \"question\": \"Controlling ensures that organizational resources are used ________ to achieve planned goals.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"ineffectively\",\n        \"effectively\",\n        \"inefficiently\",\n        \"efficiently\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 45,\n      \"question\": \"The control process measures the deviation of actual performance from the ________ performance to identify areas for improvement.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"standard\",\n        \"expected\",\n        \"planned\",\n        \"desired\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 46,\n      \"question\": \"Controlling helps in identifying the causes of deviations and taking ________ actions to correct them.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"preventive\",\n        \"corrective\",\n        \"proactive\",\n        \"reactive\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"Effective controlling creates an orderly and ________ atmosphere in the workplace by ensuring adherence to standards.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"disciplined\",\n        \"relaxed\",\n        \"chaotic\",\n        \"unstructured\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"Controlling ensures that all departments are monitored according to ________ standards to maintain consistency.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"predetermined\",\n        \"predefined\",\n        \"pre-established\",\n        \"all of the above\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"Controlling is a function that helps managers identify areas of ________ and celebrate successes to improve overall performance.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"improvement\",\n        \"failure\",\n        \"success\",\n        \"growth\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"The primary goal of controlling is to ensure that organizational ________ are achieved by guiding the team towards objectives.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"objectives\",\n        \"goals\",\n        \"targets\",\n        \"standards\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling in management ensures that all activities are carried out as per the plan.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling at the supervisory level does not involve monitoring employees.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling focuses on maintaining quality and ensuring work is completed on time and within budget.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling does not involve taking corrective actions for mistakes or deviations.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that every company has only one department for smooth functioning.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that multiple departments must work together for an organization to function smoothly.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that a quality control team does not need to inform the production team about defects.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that companies set standards to maintain quality and efficiency.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that a fast-food chain like McDonald\'s does not have strict standards for food preparation.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that setting performance standards is not a step in the control process.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that measuring performance involves tracking actual results against set standards.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that comparing performance with standards is not necessary in the control process.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that correcting unfavorable deviations is not a part of the control process.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that a supervisor may provide training if a worker does not meet performance standards.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling is not a dynamic process that requires continuous monitoring and adjustment.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling involves setting standards, measuring performance, comparing results, and taking corrective action.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling does not ensure effective and efficient utilization of organizational resources.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling helps in identifying areas of improvement and celebrating successes.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling is not related to planning in management.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling involves verifying whether everything occurs in conformity with plans and principles.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling is not performed at all levels of management.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 22,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling is a backward-looking function only.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 23,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling is a pervasive function performed by managers at all levels.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling does not involve recording experiences for future needs.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling is not a systematic exercise to check actual performance against standards.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 26,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling helps in maintaining stability and preventing wide fluctuations in output.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 27,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling does not involve guiding the team towards goals.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 28,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling involves monitoring performance towards goals.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling is not essential for ensuring that organizational goals are met.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling involves identifying deviations from standards and taking corrective actions.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling does not create an orderly and disciplined atmosphere in the workplace.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling streamlines the process of coordinating actions across departments.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling is not a goal-oriented function of management.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling involves comparing actual performance with predetermined benchmarks.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling does not require regular evaluation and revision of performance criteria.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling is a dynamic process that requires adaptable controls to changing conditions.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling is not related to ensuring that events do not deviate from their predetermined course of action.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling involves setting standards related to quality, quantity, cost, or time.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling does not involve measuring actual performance against set standards.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling helps in ensuring that all operations are carried out per the plan.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 41,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling does not involve taking remedial action if necessary.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 42,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling is essential for improving performance and maintaining high standards.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 43,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling is not a function that ensures effective and efficient utilization of resources.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 44,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling involves verifying whether everything occurs in conformity with plans and principles.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 45,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling does not involve recording experiences for future improvements.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 46,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling is a systematic exercise to check actual performance against standards.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling does not help in maintaining stability and preventing wide fluctuations in output.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling involves guiding the team towards goals and monitoring performance.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling is not essential for ensuring that organizational goals are achieved.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling involves identifying deviations from standards and taking corrective actions to ensure goal achievement.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    }\n]\n  ',14,14),(56,'3.5-Controlling Methods','<div>\n    <h1>3.5 Controlling Methods</h1>\n    <p>Managers use different methods to control performance in an organization. These methods focus on quality, quantity, time, and cost.</p>\n  \n    <h2>1. Controlling Quality</h2>\n    <p>Quality control ensures that the product or service meets the required standard.</p>\n    <p><strong>? Example:</strong></p>\n    <p>A company manufacturing soft drinks checks if every bottle has the right amount of liquid and is properly sealed. If any bottle is underfilled, it is rejected.</p>\n  \n    <h2>2. Controlling Quantity of Production</h2>\n    <p>Quantity control ensures that production meets the required target.</p>\n    <p><strong>? Example:</strong></p>\n    <p>A bakery must produce 1,000 loaves of bread daily. If only 800 loaves are made, the supervisor must increase efficiency by adjusting working hours or using better equipment.</p>\n  \n    <h2>3. Controlling Time (Timely Completion of Work)</h2>\n    <p>Time control ensures that tasks are completed on schedule.</p>\n    <p><strong>? Example:</strong></p>\n    <p>A courier company promises 24-hour delivery. If deliveries take more than 24 hours, the manager may investigate delays and change the route planning.</p>\n  \n    <h2>4. Controlling Cost</h2>\n    <p>Cost control ensures that expenses remain within the budget.</p>\n    <p><strong>? Example:</strong></p>\n    <p>A hotel sets a budget of ₹500 per meal. If the cost rises to ₹600, the supervisor must find ways to reduce waste or buy cheaper ingredients.</p>\n  \n    <h2>Measuring Performance, Comparing with Standards, and Correcting Deviations</h2>\n    <p>To maintain high performance, managers follow these three steps:</p>\n  \n    <h3>Measuring Performance</h3>\n    <p>Checking output, quality, time taken, or cost spent.</p>\n    <p><strong>? Example:</strong> A bank tracks how many loans an employee processes daily.</p>\n  \n    <h3>Comparing with Standards</h3>\n    <p>Checking if performance meets the required standard.</p>\n    <p><strong>? Example:</strong> If an employee should process 20 loans per day but only processes 15, performance is below standard.</p>\n  \n    <h3>Correcting Deviations</h3>\n    <p>Taking action to fix mistakes.</p>\n    <p><strong>? Example:</strong> The bank may introduce faster software or train employees to improve loan processing speed.</p>\n  \n    <h2>Conclusion</h2>\n    <p>Controlling at the supervisory level ensures that employees meet their targets in quality, quantity, time, and cost. By monitoring performance, comparing results with standards, and taking corrective action, managers ensure smooth operations and customer satisfaction.</p>\n </div>\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What are the main areas that controlling methods focus on?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Only quality and quantity\",\n        \"Only time and cost\",\n        \"Quality, quantity, time, and cost\",\n        \"Only employee morale\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"What is the purpose of quality control?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To reduce production costs\",\n        \"To increase production quantity\",\n        \"To ensure products meet required standards\",\n        \"To delay task completion\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Why is it important to check if every bottle of soft drink 