in within the ________ to avoid financial losses and maintain profitability.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"budget\",\n        \"schedule\",\n        \"plan\",\n        \"policy\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"A hotel sets a budget of ₹500 per meal. If the cost rises to ₹600, the supervisor must find ways to ________ waste or optimize resources to reduce expenses.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"increase\",\n        \"reduce\",\n        \"ignore\",\n        \"delay\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"Measuring performance involves checking ________ such as output, quality, time taken, or cost spent to evaluate organizational efficiency.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"standards\",\n        \"policies\",\n        \"procedures\",\n        \"metrics\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"A bank tracks how many loans an employee processes daily to ________ performance and identify areas for improvement to enhance productivity.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"measure\",\n        \"compare\",\n        \"correct\",\n        \"ignore\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"Comparing with standards involves checking if performance meets the required ________ to ensure quality, efficiency, and customer satisfaction.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"quantity\",\n        \"quality\",\n        \"time\",\n        \"standard\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling methods focus only on quality and quantity.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling methods focus on quality, quantity, time, and cost.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that quality control does not ensure that products meet required standards.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that a company manufacturing soft drinks should not check if every bottle is properly sealed.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that quantity control ensures that production meets the required target.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that a bakery should not adjust working hours if it fails to meet its daily production target.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that time control ensures that tasks are completed on schedule.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that a courier company should not investigate delays if deliveries take more than 24 hours.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that cost control ensures that expenses remain within the budget.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that a hotel should not find ways to reduce waste if meal costs exceed the budget.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that measuring performance involves checking output, quality, time taken, or cost spent.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that comparing performance with standards is not necessary for controlling.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that correcting deviations involves taking action to fix mistakes.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that a bank should not track how many loans an employee processes daily.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that if an employee processes fewer loans than expected, no action is needed.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling at the supervisory level ensures that employees meet targets in quality, quantity, time, and cost.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that monitoring performance, comparing results with standards, and taking corrective action are not necessary for smooth operations.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling methods do not impact customer satisfaction.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that quality control is not essential for ensuring customer satisfaction.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that quantity control helps in meeting production targets efficiently.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that time control does not affect the timely completion of tasks.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 22,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that cost control ensures that expenses are managed effectively.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 23,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that measuring performance involves only checking output.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that comparing performance with standards helps in identifying areas for improvement.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that correcting deviations does not involve taking action to fix mistakes.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 26,\n      \"questi