 true that correcting deviations does not involve training employees to improve performance.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling methods are essential for maintaining high performance and customer satisfaction.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling at the supervisory level does not involve ensuring smooth operations.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that monitoring performance, comparing results with standards, and taking corrective action are crucial for achieving business goals.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 41,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that quality control is not necessary for ensuring product reliability.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 42,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that quantity control helps in meeting production targets efficiently by adjusting resources.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 43,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that time control does not affect the timely completion of tasks and meeting deadlines.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 44,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that cost control ensures that expenses are managed effectively to stay within budget.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 45,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that measuring performance involves checking output, quality, time taken, or cost spent regularly.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 46,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that comparing performance with standards is not necessary for identifying areas for improvement.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that correcting deviations involves taking corrective action to meet standards and improve performance.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling methods are not essential for maintaining high performance and customer satisfaction.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that controlling at the supervisory level involves ensuring smooth operations and customer satisfaction.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that monitoring performance, comparing results with standards, and taking corrective action are crucial for achieving business goals and maintaining customer satisfaction.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    }\n]\n  ',14,14),(57,'1.1-Features of Python','<div>\n  <h1>1.1 Features of Python</h1>\n  <p>\n    Python is a powerful, easy-to-learn, and widely used programming language.\n    It is popular because of its simplicity and flexibility, making it a great\n    choice for both beginners and experienced programmers.\n  </p>\n\n  <h2>1. Easy to Learn and Use</h2>\n  <p>\n    Python has a simple and easy-to-read syntax, making it beginner-friendly.\n    Unlike other programming languages like C or Java, Python code is more like\n    English, which makes it easy to understand.\n  </p>\n  <pre><code>print(\"Hello, World!\")</code></pre>\n\n  <h2>2. Interpreted Language</h2>\n  <p>\n    Python does not require compilation like Java or C++. Instead, it runs code\n    line by line, which makes debugging easier.\n  </p>\n  <pre><code>a = 5\n  b = 3\n  print(a + b)  # Output: 8</code></pre>\n\n  <h2>3. Free and Open Source</h2>\n  <p>\n    Python is free to download and use. It is also open-source, meaning anyone\n    can contribute to its development.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Download Python from:\n    <a href=\"https://www.python.org\">https://www.python.org</a>\n  </p>\n\n  <h2>4. High-Level Language</h2>\n  <p>\n    Python is a high-level language, meaning you don’t need to worry about\n    hardware details like memory management.\n  </p>\n  <pre><code>a = 10</code></pre>\n\n  <h2>5. Platform Independent (Cross-Platform)</h2>\n  <p>\n    Python programs can run on different operating systems like Windows, macOS,\n    and Linux without modification.\n  </p>\n  <pre><code>print(\"This will run on any OS!\")</code></pre>\n\n  <h2>6. Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)</h2>\n  <p>\n    Python supports object-oriented programming, meaning you can use objects and\n    classes to organize code efficiently.\n  </p>\n  <pre><code>class Car:\n      def __init__(self, brand, color):\n          self.brand = brand\n          self.color = color\n      \n      def show_details(self):\n          print(f\"Car Brand: {self.brand}, Color: {self.color}\")\n  \n  car1 = Car(\"Toyota\", \"Red\")\n  car1.show_details()</code></pre>\n\n  <h2>7. Large Standard Library</h2>\n  <p>\n    Python comes with a huge collection of built-in modules and functions, so\n    you don’t have to write everything from scratch.\n  </p>\n  <pre><code>import math\n  print(math.sqrt(16))  # Output: 4.0</code></pre>\n\n  <h2>8. Dynamically Typed</h2>\n  <p>\n    You don’t need to declare the data type of a variable in Python. It\n    automatically detects the type.\n  </p>\n  <pre><code>x = 10      # Integer\n  y = \"Hello\" # String\n  z = 3.14    # Float</code></pre>\n\n  <h2>9. Extensible and Embeddable</h2>\n  <p>\n    Python can be combined with other programming languages like C, C++, and\n    Java to extend its functionality.\n  </p>\n\n  <h2>10. Supports GUI Programming</h2>\n  <p>\n    Python allows you to create Graphical User Interfaces (GUIs) using libraries\n    like Tkinter, PyQt, or Kivy.\n  </p>\n  <pre><code>from tkinter import *\n  root = Tk()\n  label = Label(root, text=\"Hello, Python GUI!\")\n  label.pack()\n  root.mainloop()</code></pre>\n\n  <h2>11. Used for Many Applications</h2>\n  <p>Python is used in various fields, including:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Web Development (Django, Flask)</li>\n    <li>Data Science (Pandas, NumPy)</li>\n    <li>Machine Learning & AI (TensorFlow, Scikit-learn)</li>\n    <li>Game Development (Pygame)</li>\n    <li>Cybersecurity & Hacking (Kali Linux tools)</li>\n  </ul>\n  <pre><code>from flask import Flask\n  app = Flask(__name__)\n  \n  @app.route(\"/\")\n  def home():\n      return \"Hello, Flask!\"\n  \n  if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n      app.run(debug=True)</code></pre>\n\n  <h2>Conclusion</h2>\n  <p>\n    Python is a powerful, easy-to-learn, and flexible language with numerous\n    features that make it suitable for beginners and experts. Whether you want\n    to build websites, analyze data, or create games, Python has something for\n    everyone!\n  </p>\n</div>','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What makes Python beginner-friendly?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Complex syntax\",\n        \"Simple and easy-to-read syntax\",\n        \"Requires manual memory management\",\n        \"Needs compilation before execution\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Which function is used to display text in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"display()\",\n        \"echo()\",\n        \"print()\",\n        \"show()\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"What type of language is Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Interpreted\",\n        \"Compiled\",\n        \"Assembly\",\n        \"Machine\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"Where can you download Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"www.python.com\",\n        \"www.py.org\",\n        \"www.python.org\",\n        \"www.downloadpython.com\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"Which of these is a high-level language feature of Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Requires manual memory management\",\n        \"Needs pointers for memory access\",\n        \"No need to worry about hardware details\",\n        \"Has complex syntax like Assembly\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"Why is Python considered cross-platform?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It only runs on Windows\",\n        \"It has an interpreter for each platform\",\n        \"It requires different versions for each OS\",\n        \"Python code needs OS-specific changes\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"What is an example of Object-Oriented Programming in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Using variables\",\n        \"Defining classes and objects\",\n        \"Using loops\",\n        \"Writing functions without objects\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"Which module is used for mathematical operations in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"math\",\n        \"numbers\",\n        \"calculate\",\n        \"arithmetic\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"What does dynamically typed mean in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"You must declare variable types\",\n        \"Variable types are automatically determined\",\n        \"Only integer types are supported\",\n        \"Variable types are fixed once assigned\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"Which of these is NOT a Python GUI library?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Tkinter\",\n        \"PyQt\",\n        \"NumPy\",\n        \"Kivy\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"What is Python commonly used for?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Web Development\",\n        \"Data Science\",\n        \"Machine Learning\",\n        \"All of the above\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"What framework is used for web development in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"React\",\n        \"Django\",\n        \"Angular\",\n        \"Spring\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"Which Python feature allows it to work with other languages?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Extensible and Embeddable\",\n        \"Platform dependent\",\n        \"Statically typed\",\n        \"Compiled\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"Which function is used to find the square root in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"math.square()\",\n        \"sqrt()\",\n        \"math.sqrt()\",\n        \"square_root()\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"Which of these is a Python game development library?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Pandas\",\n        \"Pygame\",\n        \"NumPy\",\n        \"Matplotlib\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"Which statement is true about Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Python is only for beginners\",\n        \"Python requires manual memory management\",\n        \"Python is an interpreted language\",\n        \"Python only supports Windows OS\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"What does the Flask framework help with?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Game development\",\n        \"Web development\",\n        \"Machine learning\",\n        \"Networking\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    }\n  ]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"Python is a ________, easy-to-learn, and widely used programming language.\",\n      \"options\": [\"complex\", \"powerful\", \"weak\", \"limited\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Python has a simple and easy-to-read ________, making it beginner-friendly.\",\n      \"options\": [\"syntax\", \"compiler\", \"algorithm\", \"hardware\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Unlike Java or C++, Python runs code ________ line by line.\",\n      \"options\": [\"simultaneously\", \"in reverse\", \"randomly\", \"sequentially\"],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"Python is an ________ language, meaning it does not require compilation before execution.\",\n      \"options\": [\"interpreted\", \"compiled\", \"assembled\", \"encrypted\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"Python is ________, meaning it can be downloaded and used for free.\",\n      \"options\": [\"paid\", \"proprietary\", \"open-source\", \"subscription-based\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"Python is a ________-level language, meaning it does not require managing memory manually.\",\n      \"options\": [\"low\", \"mid\", \"high\", \"assembly\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"Python programs can run on Windows, macOS, and Linux without modifications, making it ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"system-dependent\", \"platform-independent\", \"OS-restricted\", \"hardware-limited\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"Python supports ________ programming, allowing the use of classes and objects.\",\n      \"options\": [\"structured\", \"functional\", \"object-oriented\", \"imperative\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"Python comes with a large ________, providing built-in modules and functions.\",\n      \"options\": [\"compiler\", \"standard library\", \"database\", \"server\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"Python is ________ typed, meaning it does not require specifying data types.\",\n      \"options\": [\"statically\", \"dynamically\", \"strongly\", \"weakly\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"Python can be ________ with C, C++, or Java to extend its functionality.\",\n      \"options\": [\"embedded\", \"ignored\", \"removed\", \"restricted\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"Python supports creating GUI applications using libraries like ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"Tkinter\", \"Jupyter\", \"SQLite\", \"NumPy\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"A Python GUI window can be created using the ________ module.\",\n      \"options\": [\"math\", \"sys\", \"tkinter\", \"random\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"Python is widely used in ________, allowing developers to build web applications.\",\n      \"options\": [\"game development\", \"web development\", \"cybersecurity\", \"data science\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"The ________ framework is used in Python for web development.\",\n      \"options\": [\"Flask\", \"TensorFlow\", \"PyQt\", \"Matplotlib\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"Python is extensively used in ________ for building AI models.\",\n      \"options\": [\"networking\", \"machine learning\", \"system administration\", \"gaming\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"In Python, we use the ________ function to display output.\",\n      \"options\": [\"echo\", \"cout\", \"display\", \"print\"],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"To find the square root of 16 in Python, we use the ________ module.\",\n      \"options\": [\"random\", \"math\", \"sys\", \"os\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"In Python, ________ refers to using the same code on multiple operating systems without modification.\",\n      \"options\": [\"cross-platform\", \"single-platform\", \"restricted\", \"exclusive\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"Python has an ________ that executes code directly without compilation.\",\n      \"options\": [\"assembler\", \"interpreter\", \"compiler\", \"processor\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"Python\'s syntax is similar to the English language, making it ________ to understand.\",\n      \"options\": [\"difficult\", \"simple\", \"complex\", \"inaccessible\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    }\n  ]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"Python is a low-level programming language.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Python has a simple and easy-to-read syntax, making it beginner-friendly.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Python requires compilation before execution.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"Python code is executed line by line.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"Python is a paid programming language.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"Python is open-source and free to use.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"Python supports object-oriented programming (OOP).\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"Python programs can only run on Windows.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"Python is a dynamically typed language.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"In Python, variables must be explicitly declared with their data types.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"Python provides a large standard library with many built-in modules.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"Python cannot be combined with other programming languages like C or Java.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"Python allows GUI development using Tkinter, PyQt, and Kivy.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"Python is commonly used for web development.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"Python does not support machine learning or data science applications.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"Python is a high-level language, so programmers do not need to manage memory manually.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"Python syntax is more complicated than C or Java.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"The print() function is used to display output in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"Python can only handle integer data types.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"Python code written on Windows will also work on macOS and Linux.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"Python is not used in cybersecurity applications.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 22,\n      \"question\": \"The math module in Python provides functions for mathematical operations.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 23,\n      \"question\": \"Python requires semicolons at the end of each statement.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"Python does not allow the creation of classes and objects.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"Python supports both structured and object-oriented programming.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 26,\n      \"question\": \"Python variables do not require explicit data type declarations.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 27,\n      \"question\": \"Python programs must be compiled before running.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 28,\n      \"question\": \"Python is widely used in artificial intelligence and machine learning.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"Python cannot interact with databases.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"Python supports the development of mobile applications.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"Python is case-sensitive.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"Python uses indentation to define blocks of code.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"Python does not support functional programming.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"Python can be used for game development.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"The Flask framework is used for machine learning in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"The ‘import’ keyword is used to include modules in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"Python does not support networking applications.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"Python can handle exceptions using try-except blocks.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"Python requires a main() function to execute a script.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"Python supports file handling operations like reading and writing files.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    }\n  ]\n  ',15,15),(58,'1.2-Python Building Blocks','<div>\n  <h2>1.2 Python Building Blocks</h2>\n  <p>\n    When writing Python programs, we need to follow some rules and use certain\n    elements correctly. These fundamental elements are called building blocks of\n    Python. They include Identifiers, Keywords, Indentation, Variables, and\n    Comments.\n  </p>\n\n  <h3>1. Identifiers</h3>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Definition:</strong> An identifier is the name given to variables,\n    functions, classes, and other objects in Python. It helps the program\n    recognize and use them.\n  </p>\n  <p><strong>Rules for Identifiers:</strong></p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>\n      ✅ Can contain letters (A-Z, a-z), digits (0-9), and underscore (_).\n    </li>\n    <li>✅ Must not start with a digit (e.g., 1name is invalid).</li>\n    <li>\n      ✅ Cannot use Python keywords as identifiers (e.g., def, class, if).\n    </li>\n    <li>✅ Case-sensitive (e.g., Name and name are different).</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Examples of Valid Identifiers:</strong></p>\n  <pre>\n      name = \"Alice\"       # Valid\n      age_25 = 25          # Valid\n      _employeeID = 101    # Valid\n    </pre\n  >\n  <p><strong>Examples of Invalid Identifiers:</strong></p>\n  <pre>\n      1name = \"Bob\"        # Invalid (cannot start with a digit)\n      class = \"Student\"    # Invalid (class is a keyword)\n      my-name = \"John\"     # Invalid (hyphens are not allowed)\n    </pre\n  >\n\n  <h3>2. Keywords</h3>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Definition:</strong> Keywords are special reserved words in Python\n    that have predefined meanings and cannot be used as variable names.\n  </p>\n  <table border=\"1\">\n    <tr>\n      <th>Keyword</th>\n      <th>Use in Python</th>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>if</td>\n      <td>Conditional statement</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>else</td>\n      <td>Alternative condition</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>for</td>\n      <td>Loop</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>while</td>\n      <td>Loop</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>def</td>\n      <td>Define a function</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>return</td>\n      <td>Return a value from a function</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>import</td>\n      <td>Import a module</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>class</td>\n      <td>Define a class</td>\n    </tr>\n  </table>\n  <p><strong>Example of Keywords in Use:</strong></p>\n  <pre>\n      if True:\n          print(\"This is a keyword example\")\n    </pre\n  >\n\n  <h3>3. Indentation</h3>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Definition:</strong> Indentation in Python refers to the spaces or\n    tabs at the beginning of a line to define code blocks. Python uses\n    indentation instead of {} (like in C or Java) to group statements.\n  </p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>✅ Python requires indentation (unlike other languages).</li>\n    <li>✅ Typically, 4 spaces per indentation level is recommended.</li>\n    <li>✅ Incorrect indentation causes errors.</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Example of Proper Indentation:</strong></p>\n  <pre>\n      if True:\n          print(\"Indented correctly\")\n          print(\"Still inside the if-block\")\n      print(\"Outside the if-block\")\n    </pre\n  >\n  <p><strong>Example of Incorrect Indentation (Error):</strong></p>\n  <pre>\n      if True:\n      print(\"This will cause an error\")  # Incorrect indentation\n    </pre\n  >\n  <p>\n    <strong>? Output:</strong> IndentationError: expected an indented block\n  </p>\n\n  <h3>4. Variables</h3>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Definition:</strong> A variable is a name that stores data (like\n    numbers, text, lists, etc.). Variables allow us to use and manipulate data\n    in a program.\n  </p>\n  <p><strong>Rules for Variables:</strong></p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>✅ Can contain letters, numbers, and underscores (_).</li>\n    <li>✅ Must start with a letter or underscore, not a number.</li>\n    <li>✅ No special characters (@, $, %) allowed.</li>\n    <li>✅ Python automatically detects the type of data stored.</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n  <pre>\n      x = 10        # Integer variable\n      name = \"Tom\"  # String variable\n      price = 99.99 # Float variable\n    </pre\n  >\n  <p><strong>Dynamic Typing in Python:</strong></p>\n  <pre>\n      x = 5       # Integer\n      x = \"Hello\" # Now it\'s a string\n      print(x)    # Output: Hello\n    </pre\n  >\n\n  <h3>5. Comments</h3>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Definition:</strong> Comments are used to add explanations to the\n    code, making it easier to understand. Python ignores comments when executing\n    the program.\n  </p>\n  <p><strong>Types of Comments in Python:</strong></p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>1️⃣ Single-line comment: Starts with #</li>\n    <li>2️⃣ Multi-line comment: Uses triple quotes (\"\"\" \"\"\" or \'\'\' \'\'\')</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><strong>Example of a Single-line Comment:</strong></p>\n  <pre>\n      # This is a comment\n      print(\"Hello, World!\")  # This prints a message\n    </pre\n  >\n  <p><strong>Example of a Multi-line Comment:</strong></p>\n  <pre>\n      \"\"\"\n      This is a multi-line comment.\n      Python will ignore everything inside these triple quotes.\n      \"\"\"\n      print(\"Python is fun!\")\n    </pre\n  >\n</div>','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What is an identifier in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"A reserved keyword\",\n        \"A name given to variables, functions, or classes\",\n        \"A special symbol used in loops\",\n        \"A function that prints output\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is a valid identifier in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"1name\",\n        \"class\",\n        \"_employeeID\",\n        \"my-name\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Which rule is NOT correct for Python identifiers?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Can contain letters, digits, and underscores\",\n        \"Cannot start with a digit\",\n        \"Can use Python keywords\",\n        \"Are case-sensitive\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is NOT a Python keyword?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"if\",\n        \"else\",\n        \"print\",\n        \"def\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"How does Python define code blocks?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Using curly braces {}\",\n        \"Using indentation\",\n        \"Using square brackets []\",\n        \"Using semicolons\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"What will happen if indentation is incorrect in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"The code will run normally\",\n        \"Python will add the correct indentation automatically\",\n        \"An IndentationError will occur\",\n        \"The program will skip that line\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"How many spaces are typically recommended for indentation in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"2\",\n        \"4\",\n        \"6\",\n        \"8\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is a valid variable name in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"2var\",\n        \"my-variable\",\n        \"_myVar\",\n        \"@value\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"Which statement about Python variables is correct?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"They must be declared with a data type\",\n        \"They are case-sensitive\",\n        \"They must start with a number\",\n        \"They can include special characters like @ and $\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"What is the purpose of comments in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To execute additional code\",\n        \"To improve code readability\",\n        \"To increase program speed\",\n        \"To define functions\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is a valid single-line comment in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"// This is a comment\",\n        \"/* This is a comment */\",\n        \"-- This is a comment\",\n        \"# This is a comment\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"How do you write a multi-line comment in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"/* comment */\",\n        \"-- comment --\",\n        \"\' \' \' comment \' \' \'\",\n        \"// comment\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"What is dynamic typing in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Manually defining variable types\",\n        \"Automatically detecting variable types\",\n        \"Declaring variables before use\",\n        \"Using special characters in variable names\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following variable assignments is valid in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"int x = 10\",\n        \"x := 10\",\n        \"x = 10\",\n        \"x <- 10\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is NOT allowed in Python variable names?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Underscores\",\n        \"Digits (not at the start)\",\n        \"Hyphens\",\n        \"Letters\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"An identifier in Python can contain letters, digits, and ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"hyphens\", \"underscores\", \"spaces\", \"special characters\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Python identifiers must not start with a ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"letter\", \"digit\", \"underscore\", \"keyword\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"The identifier \'class\' is invalid because it is a ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"function\", \"variable\", \"keyword\", \"constant\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"Python identifiers are ________, meaning \'Name\' and \'name\' are different.\",\n      \"options\": [\"case-insensitive\", \"case-sensitive\", \"immutable\", \"reserved\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"A Python keyword cannot be used as a ________ name.\",\n      \"options\": [\"function\", \"variable\", \"class\", \"All of the above\"],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is a valid identifier in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\"1variable\", \"_data\", \"class\", \"my-name\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"The Python keyword \'def\' is used to define a ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"class\", \"variable\", \"function\", \"module\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"Python uses ________ instead of curly braces to define code blocks.\",\n      \"options\": [\"semicolons\", \"parentheses\", \"indentation\", \"brackets\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"The recommended number of spaces for indentation in Python is ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"2\", \"4\", \"6\", \"8\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"Incorrect indentation in Python results in a ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"SyntaxError\", \"IndentationError\", \"RuntimeError\", \"TypeError\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"Variables in Python are used to store ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"only numbers\", \"only text\", \"only lists\", \"different types of data\"],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"Python variables are ________ typed, meaning their type can change dynamically.\",\n      \"options\": [\"statically\", \"dynamically\", \"strongly\", \"weakly\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is a valid variable name in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\"2data\", \"my variable\", \"_result\", \"if\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"A variable name in Python cannot contain ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"letters\", \"digits\", \"underscores\", \"spaces\"],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"Python ignores everything written after the ________ symbol in a line of code.\",\n      \"options\": [\"*\", \"#\", \"//\", \"--\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"The \'import\' keyword is used to include ________ in a Python program.\",\n      \"options\": [\"functions\", \"classes\", \"modules\", \"variables\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"A Python block of code starts after a ________ and an indented line.\",\n      \"options\": [\"colon (:)\", \"semicolon (;)\", \"comma (,)\", \"dot (.)\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"A Python function is defined using the ________ keyword.\",\n      \"options\": [\"define\", \"function\", \"def\", \"func\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"The \'return\' keyword is used to return a ________ from a function.\",\n      \"options\": [\"class\", \"value\", \"variable\", \"loop\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that an identifier can start with a digit in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that Python keywords can be used as variable names.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that Python is case-sensitive when it comes to identifiers.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that indentation is optional in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that Python requires proper indentation to execute code.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that \'for\', \'while\', and \'if\' are not keywords in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that Python allows the use of special characters like @ and $ in identifiers.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that variable names in Python must always start with an underscore (_).\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that comments in Python can be single-line or multi-line.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that Python ignores comments when executing a program.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that an identifier can contain letters, numbers, and underscores (_).\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that indentation errors in Python do not cause execution failures.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that Python uses indentation instead of curly braces {} for code blocks.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that \'print\' is not a keyword in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that variables in Python can change their data type during execution.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that Python enforces strict static typing for variables.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that \'import\' is a keyword used to bring external modules into a Python program.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that variables in Python must be declared with a specific data type.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that identifiers cannot contain spaces in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that Python allows the use of hyphens (-) in identifiers.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that Python keywords have predefined meanings and cannot be used as variable names.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 22,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that Python ignores indentation when executing code.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 23,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that Python automatically detects the type of data stored in a variable.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that all Python statements must be written on separate lines.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that multi-line comments in Python can be written using triple quotes (\'\'\' or \\\"\\\").\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    }\n  ]\n  ',15,15),(59,'1.3-Python Environment Setup Installation and Working of IDE','<div>\n    <h1>1.3 Python Environment Setup: Installation and Working of IDE</h1>\n    <p>Python is a user-friendly programming language, and setting up the Python environment is simple. In this guide, we will explain step-by-step how to install Python, set up an Integrated Development Environment (IDE), and write your first Python program.</p>\n    \n    <h2>1. What is a Python Environment?</h2>\n    <p>The Python environment is the setup that allows us to write, execute, and test Python programs. It includes:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Python Interpreter – The engine that runs Python code.</li>\n      <li>Text Editor/IDE – A software tool for writing and executing Python code.</li>\n      <li>Libraries & Packages – Additional tools for Python programming.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h2>2. How to Install Python?</h2>\n    <h3>Step 1: Download Python</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Go to the official Python website: <a href=\"https://www.python.org\">https://www.python.org</a></li>\n      <li>Click on \"Downloads\" and choose your operating system (Windows, macOS, or Linux).</li>\n      <li>Download the latest version (e.g., Python 3.11).</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h3>Step 2: Install Python</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Open the downloaded file and follow the installation steps.</li>\n      <li>Important: Check the box \"Add Python to PATH\" before clicking \"Install Now.\" </li>\n      <li>After installation, open Command Prompt (Windows) or Terminal (Mac/Linux) and type:</li>\n    </ul>\n    <code>python --version</code>\n    <p>If Python is installed, it will show the version number (e.g., Python 3.11.2).</p>\n    \n    <h2>3. Python IDEs and Code Editors</h2>\n    <p>An IDE (Integrated Development Environment) is software that makes writing and running Python programs easier.</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>IDLE – Comes with Python (best for beginners).</li>\n      <li>PyCharm – Advanced, feature-rich (for professionals).</li>\n      <li>VS Code – Lightweight and powerful.</li>\n      <li>Jupyter Notebook – Best for data science.</li>\n      <li>Spyder – Used in scientific computing.</li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h2>4. Writing and Running Python Code in Different IDEs</h2>\n    \n    <h3>Method 1: Using IDLE (Comes with Python)</h3>\n    <ol>\n      <li>Open IDLE (Installed with Python).</li>\n      <li>Click on \"File\" > \"New File\" and type:</li>\n    </ol>\n    <code>print(\"Hello, Python!\")</code>\n    <p>Save the file as hello.py and run it by pressing F5 or clicking Run > Run Module.</p>\n    \n    <h3>Method 2: Using PyCharm (Best for Projects)</h3>\n    <ol>\n      <li>Download and install PyCharm from <a href=\"https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm/\">https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm/</a>.</li>\n      <li>Open PyCharm and create a new project.</li>\n      <li>Inside the project, create a new Python file and type:</li>\n    </ol>\n    <code>\n      name = input(\"Enter your name: \")\n      print(\"Hello, \" + name + \"!\")\n    </code>\n    <p>Click Run to execute the program.</p>\n    \n    <h3>Method 3: Using VS Code (Best for Beginners)</h3>\n    <ol>\n      <li>Download VS Code from <a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/\">https://code.visualstudio.com/</a>.</li>\n      <li>Install the Python Extension from the VS Code marketplace.</li>\n      <li>Open a folder, create a Python file (example.py), and type:</li>\n    </ol>\n    <code>\n      for i in range(5):\n          print(\"Python is fun!\")\n    </code>\n    <p>Click on the Run button or use the terminal:</p>\n    <code>python example.py</code>\n    \n    <h3>Method 4: Running Python Code in the Terminal</h3>\n    <p>If you don\'t want to use an IDE, you can write Python code directly in the command line (Windows) or terminal (Mac/Linux).</p>\n    <ol>\n      <li>Open Command Prompt or Terminal.</li>\n      <li>Type <code>python</code> and press Enter.</li>\n      <li>Type the following Python code:</li>\n    </ol>\n    <code>print(\"Hello, Terminal!\")</code>\n    <p>Press Enter and see the output.</p>\n    \n    <h2>5. Setting Up a Virtual Environment (For Advanced Users)</h2>\n    <p>A virtual environment allows you to create a separate Python workspace for each project.</p>\n    <p>Steps to Create a Virtual Environment:</p>\n    <code>python -m venv my_project_env</code>\n    <p>Activate the virtual environment:</p>\n    <p>Windows:</p>\n    <code>my_project_env\\Scripts\\activate</code>\n    <p>macOS/Linux:</p>\n    <code>source my_project_env/bin/activate</code>\n    <p>Now you can install project-specific packages using:</p>\n    <code>pip install &lt;package_name&gt;</code>\n    \n    <h2>6. Installing and Using Python Libraries</h2>\n    <p>Python has thousands of pre-built libraries to simplify coding.</p>\n    <p>Example: Installing and Using the requests Library</p>\n    <code>pip install requests</code>\n    <code>\n      import requests\n      response = requests.get(\"https://www.python.org\")\n      print(response.status_code)\n    </code>\n    <p>This fetches the Python website’s homepage status.</p>\n    \n    <h2>Conclusion</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Installing Python is simple and requires only a few steps.</li>\n      <li>Using an IDE like IDLE, PyCharm, or VS Code makes coding easier.</li>\n      <li>Python can be run in a terminal, IDE, or text editor.</li>\n      <li>Virtual environments help manage different projects separately.</li>\n    </ul>\n</div>\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What is the Python environment?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"A tool for designing websites\",\n        \"A setup that allows writing, executing, and testing Python programs\",\n        \"A software used for hacking\",\n        \"An advanced game engine\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"What is the function of the Python interpreter?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It translates and executes Python code\",\n        \"It acts as a music player\",\n        \"It stores data permanently\",\n        \"It compiles Java programs\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is NOT part of the Python environment?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Python Interpreter\",\n        \"Libraries & Packages\",\n        \"Text Editor/IDE\",\n        \"Gaming Console\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"Where can you download Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"https://www.python.org\",\n        \"https://www.java.com\",\n        \"https://www.microsoft.com\",\n        \"https://www.github.com\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"What should you check during Python installation?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Uncheck \'Add Python to PATH\'\",\n        \"Check \'Add Python to PATH\'\",\n        \"Click \'Skip Installation\'\",\n        \"Choose Java installation\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"How do you verify if Python is installed?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Open a browser and search \'Python Installed\'\",\n        \"Check the Start Menu\",\n        \"Type \'python --version\' in the Command Prompt or Terminal\",\n        \"Restart the computer\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"Which IDE comes pre-installed with Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"PyCharm\",\n        \"IDLE\",\n        \"VS Code\",\n        \"Jupyter Notebook\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"Which IDE is best suited for Data Science?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Jupyter Notebook\",\n        \"PyCharm\",\n        \"VS Code\",\n        \"Notepad++\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"Which step is required to run a Python file in IDLE?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Click \'File\' > \'New File\', write code, save, and press F5\",\n        \"Type code and close the window\",\n        \"Restart the computer after writing code\",\n        \"Write code in Microsoft Word\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"Which IDE is best for professional Python developers?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"IDLE\",\n        \"PyCharm\",\n        \"Notepad\",\n        \"WordPad\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"How do you install PyCharm?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"From the Microsoft Store\",\n        \"Download it from https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm/\",\n        \"Using pip install pycharm\",\n        \"Using the Python terminal\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"Which extension should a Python script be saved with?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \".exe\",\n        \".txt\",\n        \".py\",\n        \".java\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"Which command is used to run a Python script from the terminal?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"python filename.py\",\n        \"run filename\",\n        \"execute filename\",\n        \"start filename.py\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"Which IDE is best for beginners?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"IDLE\",\n        \"PyCharm\",\n        \"VS Code\",\n        \"Eclipse\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"What is the main advantage of using an IDE?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It only allows writing code but not running it\",\n        \"It provides features like debugging, syntax highlighting, and code execution\",\n        \"It is slower than text editors\",\n        \"It requires no installation\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"The Python ________ is the engine that runs Python code.\",\n      \"options\": [\"Editor\", \"Interpreter\", \"Library\", \"Compiler\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"IDLE, PyCharm, and VS Code are examples of Python ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"Compilers\", \"IDEs\", \"Frameworks\", \"Libraries\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"To check the installed Python version, use the command ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"python --check\", \"python --version\", \"check python\", \"python -v\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"Before installing Python, we download it from ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"python.org\", \"github.com\", \"pypi.org\", \"jetbrains.com\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"The command used to install Python libraries is ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"install\", \"python install\", \"pip install\", \"pkg install\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"A Python file is saved with the extension ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\".py\", \".pyt\", \".python\", \".txt\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"The default IDE that comes with Python is called ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"VS Code\", \"IDLE\", \"Jupyter\", \"PyCharm\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"PyCharm is developed by ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"Microsoft\", \"Google\", \"JetBrains\", \"IBM\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"A virtual environment in Python is created using the command ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"python -m venv\", \"create env\", \"python create venv\", \"python virtualenv\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"The ________ command is used to activate a virtual environment on Windows.\",\n      \"options\": [\"activate\", \"venv start\", \"my_env/Scripts/activate\", \"venv_run\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"To deactivate a virtual environment, we use the command ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"deactivate\", \"stop venv\", \"exit env\", \"close venv\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"To install PyCharm, we visit ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"pycharm.org\", \"jetbrains.com\", \"python.org\", \"microsoft.com\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"Jupyter Notebook is mainly used for ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"Game Development\", \"Data Science\", \"Web Development\", \"Cybersecurity\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"To run a Python script in the terminal, use the command ________ filename.py.\",\n      \"options\": [\"execute\", \"run\", \"python\", \"compile\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"The first step in setting up Python is to ________ it.\",\n      \"options\": [\"compile\", \"download\", \"delete\", \"debug\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"The box that must be checked while installing Python is ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"Add Python to PATH\", \"Enable Debug Mode\", \"Install Compiler\", \"Enable Logging\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"To open the Python interactive shell, simply type ________ in the terminal.\",\n      \"options\": [\"python\", \"shell\", \"py execute\", \"cmd python\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"The IDE recommended for beginners in Python is ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"PyCharm\", \"IDLE\", \"Jupyter\", \"VS Code\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"The Python package manager is called ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"pip\", \"npm\", \"pkg\", \"brew\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"The requests library is used for ________ in Python.\",\n      \"options\": [\"Web Scraping\", \"Networking\", \"Making HTTP Requests\", \"GUI Development\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"Python Interpreter is responsible for executing Python code.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"IDLE is not included with the standard Python installation.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"PyCharm is a lightweight and minimalistic code editor for Python.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"Jupyter Notebook is commonly used for data science and machine learning.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"To check if Python is installed, you can run the command \'python --version\' in the terminal.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"Python virtual environments allow developers to manage dependencies for different projects separately.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"The command \'pip install requests\' is used to uninstall the requests library.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"VS Code requires a Python extension to support Python development.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"Python code can be executed directly in the command line or terminal.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"The \'Add Python to PATH\' option during installation is not necessary for running Python from the terminal.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"Python libraries can be installed using the command \'python install <package_name>\'.\", \n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"A virtual environment in Python can be activated using \'source my_project_env/bin/activate\' on macOS/Linux.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"The Python environment consists of the interpreter, text editor/IDE, and libraries.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"Running \'python\' in the terminal starts the Python interactive shell.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"IDLE is an advanced IDE that is used mainly by professional developers.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"Python virtual environments help in avoiding conflicts between different project dependencies.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"PyCharm is available in both free (Community) and paid (Professional) versions.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"The command \'python -m venv my_env\' creates a virtual environment named \'my_env\'.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"Jupyter Notebook is mainly used for developing mobile applications.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"The Python Interpreter converts Python code into machine code directly.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"Spyder is an IDE specifically designed for scientific computing.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 22,\n      \"question\": \"PyCharm is developed by Microsoft.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 23,\n      \"question\": \"Python scripts can be saved with the .py file extension.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"Python cannot be installed on macOS.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"The Python standard library provides a rich set of modules and functions.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 26,\n      \"question\": \"To run a Python script from the terminal, you can use the command \'python script.py\'.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 27,\n      \"question\": \"The command \'pip list\' displays all installed Python packages.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 28,\n      \"question\": \"Python can only be used for web development and data science.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"An IDE like PyCharm provides features like debugging, code completion, and version control integration.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"Python code must be compiled before execution.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"A Python virtual environment helps to create isolated environments for different projects.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"The \'requests\' library in Python is used for making HTTP requests.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"Python is an interpreted language.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"Python scripts cannot be executed without an IDE.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"To execute a Python file, we use the command \'run filename.py\'.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    }\n]\n  ',15,15),(60,'1.4-Running Simple Python Scripts to Display a ‘Welcome’ Message','<div>\n  <h1>1.4 Running Simple Python Scripts to Display a ‘Welcome’ Message</h1>\n  <p>\n    Python is a user-friendly programming language that allows you to write and\n    run programs easily. In this section, we will learn how to write and run a\n    simple Python script to display a ‘Welcome’ message on the screen.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    This guide is designed for absolute beginners, so no prior programming\n    knowledge is required. ?\n  </p>\n\n  <h2>What is a Python Script?</h2>\n  <p>\n    A Python script is a file that contains Python code. It is saved with the\n    .py extension. When we run the script, Python executes the instructions\n    written in the file.\n  </p>\n  <pre><code>print(\"Welcome to Python Programming!\")</code></pre>\n  <p>When this script is executed, it will display the message:</p>\n  <pre><code>Welcome to Python Programming!</code></pre>\n\n  <h2>Ways to Run a Python Script</h2>\n  <h3>1. Using the Python Interactive Shell (IDLE)</h3>\n  <p>Steps to run Python in IDLE:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Open Python IDLE (Python’s built-in editor).</li>\n    <li>Type the following command:</li>\n  </ul>\n  <pre><code>print(\"Welcome to Python!\")</code></pre>\n  <p>Press Enter. The output will appear immediately:</p>\n  <pre><code>Welcome to Python!</code></pre>\n\n  <h3>2. Running a Python Script from a File</h3>\n  <p>Steps to create and run a Python script file:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Open Notepad (or any text editor like VS Code, PyCharm).</li>\n    <li>Type the following Python code:</li>\n  </ul>\n  <pre><code>print(\"Welcome to Python Programming!\")</code></pre>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Save the file as <b>welcome.py</b>.</li>\n    <li>Open Command Prompt or Terminal.</li>\n    <li>Navigate to the folder where the file is saved:</li>\n  </ul>\n  <pre><code>cd Desktop</code></pre>\n  <p>Run the script by typing:</p>\n  <pre><code>python welcome.py</code></pre>\n  <p>You will see the output:</p>\n  <pre><code>Welcome to Python Programming!</code></pre>\n\n  <h3>3. Running Python Script in an Online Compiler</h3>\n  <p>\n    If you don’t have Python installed on your computer, you can use an online\n    Python compiler.\n  </p>\n  <p>Steps to run the script online:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>\n      Go to\n      <a href=\"https://www.programiz.com/python-programming/online-compiler\"\n        >this online Python compiler</a\n      >.\n    </li>\n    <li>Type the following code:</li>\n  </ul>\n  <pre><code>print(\"Welcome to Python!\")</code></pre>\n  <p>Click the Run button. The output will appear on the screen.</p>\n\n  <h2>Additional Examples of Displaying ‘Welcome’ Messages</h2>\n  <h3>1. Displaying Multiple Messages</h3>\n  <pre><code>print(\"Welcome to Python!\")\nprint(\"This is your first Python script.\")</code></pre>\n  <p>Output:</p>\n  <pre><code>Welcome to Python!\nThis is your first Python script.</code></pre>\n\n  <h3>2. Using Variables for a Welcome Message</h3>\n  <pre><code>message = \"Welcome to Python Programming!\"\nprint(message)</code></pre>\n  <p>Output:</p>\n  <pre><code>Welcome to Python Programming!</code></pre>\n\n  <h3>3. Displaying a Welcome Message with a User\'s Name</h3>\n  <pre><code>name = input(\"Enter your name: \")\nprint(\"Welcome, \" + name + \"!\")</code></pre>\n  <p>Example Output:</p>\n  <pre><code>Enter your name: John\nWelcome, John!</code></pre>\n\n  <h3>4. Displaying a Welcome Message with Fancy Formatting</h3>\n  <pre><code>print(\"*\" * 30)\nprint(\"      WELCOME TO PYTHON      \")\nprint(\"*\" * 30)</code></pre>\n  <p>Output:</p>\n  <pre><code>******************************\n      WELCOME TO PYTHON      \n******************************</code></pre>\n\n  <h3>5. Displaying a Welcome Message Multiple Times</h3>\n  <pre><code>for i in range(3):\n    print(\"Welcome to Python!\")</code></pre>\n  <p>Output:</p>\n  <pre><code>Welcome to Python!\nWelcome to Python!\nWelcome to Python!</code></pre>\n\n  <h2>Conclusion</h2>\n  <p>\n    Python makes it very easy to run simple scripts and display messages on the\n    screen. You can use Python IDLE, command prompt, or an online compiler to\n    execute your code. Try out different examples to explore Python further!\n    ??\n  </p>\n</div>','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What is a Python script?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"A document file containing Python notes\",\n        \"A file containing Python code saved with a .py extension\",\n        \"A shortcut to open Python\",\n        \"A system application to manage Python versions\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"What will the following Python code output?\\nprint(\\\"Welcome to Python Programming!\\\")\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"An error message\",\n        \"Nothing will be displayed\",\n        \"Welcome to Python Programming!\",\n        \"Python installation instructions\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is NOT a way to run a Python script?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Using Python Interactive Shell (IDLE)\",\n        \"Running the script from a file\",\n        \"Using an online compiler\",\n        \"Opening the script in a web browser\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"How do you run a Python script from the command prompt?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Type \'python filename.py\'\",\n        \"Double-click the file\",\n        \"Open it in Notepad\",\n        \"Email the script to Python support\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following steps is required to run a Python script using IDLE?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Click \'File\' > \'New File\', write code, save, and press F5\",\n        \"Write code directly in Notepad\",\n        \"Open Microsoft Word and save the file as .py\",\n        \"Restart the computer after writing code\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"What is the advantage of using an online compiler for Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It requires Python installation on the computer\",\n        \"It allows running Python code without installing Python\",\n        \"It only supports C programming\",\n        \"It automatically writes code for the user\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"Which website provides an online Python compiler?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"https://www.programiz.com/python-programming/online-compiler\",\n        \"https://www.microsoft.com\",\n        \"https://www.java.com\",\n        \"https://www.wikipedia.org\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"What will be the output of the following Python script?\\nprint(\\\"*\\\" * 10)\\nprint(\\\"WELCOME\\\")\\nprint(\\\"*\\\" * 10)\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"WELCOME\",\n        \"**********\\nWELCOME\\n**********\",\n        \"Error: Invalid syntax\",\n        \"Only the stars will be printed\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"Which command is used to navigate to the Desktop in the command prompt before running a script?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"cd Desktop\",\n        \"dir Desktop\",\n        \"open Desktop\",\n        \"run Desktop\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following code snippets correctly asks for user input and displays a personalized welcome message?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"print(\\\"Enter your name: \\\")\\nname\\nprint(\\\"Welcome, \\\" + name + \\\"!\\\")\",\n        \"name = input(\\\"Enter your name: \\\")\\nprint(\\\"Welcome, \\\" + name + \\\"!\\\")\",\n        \"input(\\\"Enter your name: \\\")\\nprint(\\\"Welcome!\\\")\",\n        \"name = input()\\nprint(\\\"Welcome!\\\")\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"A Python script is a file that contains Python code and is saved with the ______ extension.\",\n      \"options\": [\".txt\", \".py\", \".java\", \".exe\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"To display a \'Welcome\' message in Python, we use the ______ function.\",\n      \"options\": [\"display\", \"show\", \"print\", \"echo\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"The built-in Python editor that allows us to write and execute Python commands interactively is called ______.\",\n      \"options\": [\"Notepad\", \"IDLE\", \"PyCharm\", \"Terminal\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"To run a Python script from the command line, we use the command ______.\",\n      \"options\": [\"run script.py\", \"python script.py\", \"execute script.py\", \"start script.py\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"To run a Python script online, we can use the website ______.\",\n      \"options\": [\"w3schools.com\", \"python.org\", \"programiz.com\", \"github.com\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"A Python script can be written and saved using a simple text editor like ______.\",\n      \"options\": [\"Notepad\", \"MS Paint\", \"Excel\", \"Photoshop\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"The command to check if Python is installed on a system is ______.\",\n      \"options\": [\"check python\", \"python --version\", \"verify python\", \"python -check\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"When running a Python script, the output of print(\\\"Welcome to Python!\\\") is ______.\",\n      \"options\": [\"Welcome to Python!\", \"Python to Welcome!\", \"Error\", \"None\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"In a Python script, a string value is enclosed within ______.\",\n      \"options\": [\"Curly braces\", \"Parentheses\", \"Quotation marks\", \"Square brackets\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"To accept user input in Python, we use the ______ function.\",\n      \"options\": [\"input()\", \"read()\", \"get()\", \"accept()\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"In Python, we can repeat a \'Welcome\' message multiple times using a ______ loop.\",\n      \"options\": [\"while\", \"if\", \"for\", \"switch\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"To create a fancy border around a message, we use the ______ operator to repeat a character.\",\n      \"options\": [\"+\", \"-\", \"*\", \"&\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"The command used to navigate to the Desktop in the command prompt is ______.\",\n      \"options\": [\"goto Desktop\", \"cd Desktop\", \"open Desktop\", \"Desktop\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"A Python script is executed by the ______.\",\n      \"options\": [\"Python Compiler\", \"Python Interpreter\", \"C++ Compiler\", \"Java Virtual Machine\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"A file containing Python code should be saved with the file extension ______.\",\n      \"options\": [\".exe\", \".py\", \".html\", \".cpp\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"PyCharm, VS Code, and IDLE are examples of ______.\",\n      \"options\": [\"Operating Systems\", \"Programming Languages\", \"IDEs\", \"Databases\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"In a Python script, the line name = input(\\\"Enter your name: \\\") allows the user to input ______.\",\n      \"options\": [\"A number\", \"A string\", \"A file\", \"A function\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"The result of running the script print(\'Hello\' + \' Python!\') is ______.\",\n      \"options\": [\"HelloPython!\", \"Hello Python!\", \"Hello + Python!\", \"Error\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"In Python, the print function outputs text to the ______.\",\n      \"options\": [\"Screen\", \"File\", \"Database\", \"Clipboard\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"To display a message in Python, we enclose the text in ______.\",\n      \"options\": [\"Single or double quotes\", \"Curly braces\", \"Square brackets\", \"Angle brackets\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"A Python script is a file that contains Python code and is saved with the .py extension.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"The Python Interactive Shell (IDLE) does not allow users to execute Python commands immediately.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Python scripts can only be run using an installed Python interpreter and not through an online compiler.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"The command `python welcome.py` is used to run a Python script from the command line.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"Python requires a semicolon at the end of every print statement.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"The function `print()` is used to display messages on the screen in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"In Python, the `input()` function is used to receive user input.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"Python scripts must always contain a `main()` function to execute properly.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"A Python script saved with the .txt extension can be executed directly by the Python interpreter.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"A Python script can be created using Notepad, VS Code, or PyCharm.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"In Python, `print(\\\"Hello, World!\\\")` will display an error because it lacks a semicolon.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"The command `cd Desktop` is used to change the directory to the Desktop before running a script.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"Python scripts cannot be executed from the terminal or command prompt.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"A Python script must always be named `script.py` to run successfully.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"In Python, using `*` in a print statement can be used to repeat characters.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"Python allows users to format output messages using variables and string concatenation.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"To run a Python script online, we can use platforms like Programiz and Replit.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"A Python script can contain multiple print statements to display multiple messages.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"To execute a Python script in IDLE, we must press F5 or click \'Run Module\'.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"Python does not support user input through the `input()` function.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"Python scripts require compilation before execution.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 22,\n      \"question\": \"The command `python --version` is used to check the installed Python version.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 23,\n      \"question\": \"Python programs can only be executed in PyCharm.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"The print statement `print(\\\"Welcome to Python!\\\")` will output: Welcome to Python!\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"Python scripts can include loops, such as a `for` loop, to repeat messages multiple times.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 26,\n      \"question\": \"Python scripts can only be run on Windows operating systems.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 27,\n      \"question\": \"Python programs can only be written in an IDE and not in a text editor.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 28,\n      \"question\": \"In Python, a variable can be assigned a string value and used in a print statement.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"Python uses indentation instead of brackets `{}` for code blocks.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"Running `print(Welcome to Python!)` without quotes will result in an error.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"Python scripts do not require a specific file extension.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"Online Python compilers allow users to execute Python scripts without installing Python on their system.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"The `print()` function can display numbers, text, and variables.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"Python programs can run without being saved to a file using the interactive shell.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"Python scripts cannot contain more than one print statement.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"In Python, the `#` symbol is used to write comments in scripts.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"The `input()` function in Python requires an argument inside the parentheses.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"A Python script can be executed multiple times without modification.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"A Python script must contain at least one variable declaration.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"Python is a case-sensitive language, so `Print()` is different from `print()`.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 41,\n      \"question\": \"The `print()` function can only display text and not numbers.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 42,\n      \"question\": \"Python requires double quotes for strings and does not support single quotes.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 43,\n      \"question\": \"Python scripts can be modified and re-executed without re-installing Python.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 44,\n      \"question\": \"Python allows multiple variables to be declared in a single line.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 45,\n      \"question\": \"A Python script cannot be executed inside a Jupyter Notebook.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 46,\n      \"question\": \"To run a Python script in PyCharm, you must create a new Python project.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"Python programs always require an internet connection to run.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"A Python script can contain functions and loops.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"The command `python3 script.py` can be used on Linux and macOS to run a Python script.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"Python scripts must always start with a comment describing the program.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    }\n]\n  ',15,15),(61,'1.5-Python Data Types','<div>\n  <h1>1.5 Python Data Types</h1>\n  <h2>Introduction to Python Data Types</h2>\n  <p>\n    Data types in Python define the kind of data a variable can store. For\n    example, a variable can hold numbers, text, or a collection of values.\n    Python provides several built-in data types, and understanding them is\n    essential for programming.\n  </p>\n  <p>The main data types in Python include:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Numbers (int, float, complex)</li>\n    <li>String (str)</li>\n    <li>Tuple (tuple)</li>\n    <li>List (list)</li>\n    <li>Dictionary (dict)</li>\n    <li>Set (set)</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>1. Numbers (int, float, complex)</h3>\n  <p>Python supports three types of numbers:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li><b>Integers (int)</b> – Whole numbers (e.g., 10, -5, 200)</li>\n    <li>\n      <b>Floating-point numbers (float)</b> – Numbers with decimal points (e.g.,\n      3.14, -0.99)\n    </li>\n    <li>\n      <b>Complex numbers (complex)</b> – Numbers with real and imaginary parts\n      (e.g., 2+3j)\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n  <pre>\n      <code>\n  # Integer\n  x = 10\n  y = -25\n  print(type(x))  # Output: &lt;class \'int\'&gt;\n  \n  # Float\n  a = 3.14\n  b = -7.5\n  print(type(a))  # Output: &lt;class \'float\'&gt;\n  \n  # Complex Number\n  c = 2 + 3j\n  d = -4j\n  print(type(c))  # Output: &lt;class \'complex\'&gt;\n      </code>\n    </pre>\n\n  <h3>2. String (str)</h3>\n  <p>\n    A string is a sequence of characters enclosed in single (\' \'), double (\" \"),\n    or triple quotes (\'\'\' \'\'\'). Strings are used to store text.\n  </p>\n  <pre>\n      <code>\n  # Single-line strings\n  name = \"Alice\"\n  greeting = \'Hello, World!\'\n  \n  # Multi-line string\n  message = \"\"\"This is a \n  multi-line string.\"\"\"\n  print(message)\n      </code>\n    </pre>\n\n  <h3>3. Tuple (tuple)</h3>\n  <p>\n    A tuple is an ordered and immutable (unchangeable) collection of values,\n    written inside parentheses ().\n  </p>\n  <pre>\n      <code>\n  # Creating a tuple\n  fruits = (\"apple\", \"banana\", \"cherry\")\n  numbers = (10, 20, 30)\n      </code>\n    </pre>\n\n  <h3>4. List (list)</h3>\n  <p>\n    A list is an ordered, mutable (changeable) collection of values, written\n    inside square brackets [].\n  </p>\n  <pre>\n      <code>\n  # Creating a list\n  colors = [\"red\", \"blue\", \"green\"]\n  numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n      </code>\n    </pre>\n\n  <h3>5. Dictionary (dict)</h3>\n  <p>\n    A dictionary is an unordered collection of key-value pairs, written inside\n    curly braces {}.\n  </p>\n  <pre>\n      <code>\n  # Creating a dictionary\n  student = {\n      \"name\": \"John\",\n      \"age\": 20,\n      \"marks\": 85\n  }\n      </code>\n    </pre>\n\n  <h3>6. Set (set)</h3>\n  <p>\n    A set is an unordered collection of unique values, written inside curly\n    braces {}. It does not allow duplicate values.\n  </p>\n  <pre>\n      <code>\n  # Creating a set\n  fruits = {\"apple\", \"banana\", \"cherry\", \"apple\"}\n  print(fruits)  # Output: {\'banana\', \'apple\', \'cherry\'}\n      </code>\n    </pre>\n\n  <h2>Conclusion</h2>\n  <p>\n    Python provides a variety of data types to store different kinds of\n    information.\n  </p>\n  <ul>\n    <li><b>Numbers</b> are used for mathematical calculations.</li>\n    <li><b>Strings</b> store text data.</li>\n    <li><b>Tuples</b> are immutable collections.</li>\n    <li><b>Lists</b> are mutable collections.</li>\n    <li><b>Dictionaries</b> store key-value pairs.</li>\n    <li><b>Sets</b> store unique values and allow mathematical operations.</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p>\n    By understanding and using these data types correctly, you can write more\n    efficient and organized Python programs.\n  </p>\n</div>','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What is a Python script?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"A file containing Python code\",\n        \"A type of programming language\",\n        \"An interactive shell command\",\n        \"A web-based Python tool\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Which extension is used to save a Python script?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \".txt\",\n        \".exe\",\n        \".py\",\n        \".java\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is NOT a way to run a Python script?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Using Python IDLE\",\n        \"Running from a text file\",\n        \"Using an online compiler\",\n        \"Executing from the command line\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"What is the output of print(\\\"Welcome to Python!\\\")?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Welcome to Python!\",\n        \"print(Welcome to Python!)\",\n        \"Welcome to Python\",\n        \"Error\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"Which function is used to display output in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"echo()\",\n        \"printf()\",\n        \"print()\",\n        \"display()\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is NOT a valid numeric data type in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Integer\",\n        \"Float\",\n        \"Double\",\n        \"Complex\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"What is the data type of 3.14 in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"int\",\n        \"float\",\n        \"complex\",\n        \"double\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"Which data type is used to store a sequence of characters?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"int\",\n        \"float\",\n        \"str\",\n        \"tuple\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"What will be the output of print(type(10))?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"<class \'int\'>\",\n        \"<class \'float\'>\",\n        \"<class \'str\'>\",\n        \"<class \'tuple\'>\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is NOT a valid way to create a string in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"\'Hello\'\",\n        \"\\\"Hello\\\"\",\n        \"\'\'\'Hello\'\'\'\",\n        \"Hello\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"How do you access the first character of a string stored in variable \'name\'?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"name[0]\",\n        \"name(0)\",\n        \"name{0}\",\n        \"name<0>\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following data types is immutable?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"List\",\n        \"Tuple\",\n        \"Dictionary\",\n        \"Set\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"How do you create a list in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"[1, 2, 3]\",\n        \"(1, 2, 3)\",\n        \"{1, 2, 3}\",\n        \"1, 2, 3\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"Which method is used to add an element to a list?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"insert()\",\n        \"append()\",\n        \"add()\",\n        \"update()\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"What is the correct way to create a dictionary?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"{ \'name\': \'Alice\', \'age\': 25 }\",\n        \"[ \'name\': \'Alice\', \'age\': 25 ]\",\n        \"( \'name\': \'Alice\', \'age\': 25 )\",\n        \"{ \'name\'; \'Alice\', \'age\'; 25 }\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"Which method is used to remove a key-value pair from a dictionary?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"remove()\",\n        \"pop()\",\n        \"delete()\",\n        \"discard()\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"What is the primary characteristic of a set in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It allows duplicate values\",\n        \"It is unordered and contains unique values\",\n        \"It maintains insertion order\",\n        \"It allows indexing\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"Which symbol is used to perform the union operation on sets?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"&\",\n        \"|\",\n        \"-\",\n        \"^\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"In Python, a variable that stores text is called a ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"list\",\n        \"tuple\",\n        \"string\",\n        \"dictionary\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"A Python ________ is an ordered and mutable collection of values.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"set\",\n        \"list\",\n        \"tuple\",\n        \"dictionary\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"A ________ in Python is used to store key-value pairs.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"list\",\n        \"dictionary\",\n        \"tuple\",\n        \"set\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"An unordered collection of unique values in Python is called a ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"list\",\n        \"tuple\",\n        \"set\",\n        \"dictionary\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"A Python list is defined using ________ brackets.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"curly\",\n        \"square\",\n        \"round\",\n        \"angle\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"A tuple in Python is ________, meaning it cannot be changed once created.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"mutable\",\n        \"ordered\",\n        \"immutable\",\n        \"unordered\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"Python stores numbers as _______, _______, or _______ types.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"int, float, complex\",\n        \"list, tuple, dictionary\",\n        \"string, set, tuple\",\n        \"char, string, boolean\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"The function used to find the data type of a variable in Python is ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"data()\",\n        \"typeof()\",\n        \"type()\",\n        \"datatype()\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"The output of type(3.14) in Python will be ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"int\",\n        \"float\",\n        \"complex\",\n        \"string\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"In a Python dictionary, values are accessed using their ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"position\",\n        \"index\",\n        \"key\",\n        \"value\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"Python allows users to define their own data types.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"The \'int\' data type in Python is used to store whole numbers.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Floating-point numbers in Python cannot store negative values.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"Complex numbers in Python consist of real and imaginary parts.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"Strings in Python can be defined using single, double, or triple quotes.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"Tuples in Python are mutable, meaning their elements can be changed after creation.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"Lists in Python are ordered collections that allow modifications.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"A dictionary in Python stores elements in the form of key-value pairs.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"Sets in Python allow duplicate values.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"The \'print\' function in Python is used to take user input.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"A Python script is saved with the .py extension.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"We can execute a Python script using the command line.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"Python does not allow running scripts using an online compiler.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"IDLE is an interactive shell provided by Python.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"Tuples in Python allow adding and removing elements dynamically.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"Lists in Python are defined using curly braces {}.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"Dictionaries store elements in an ordered manner.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"We can retrieve a dictionary value using its key.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"Sets in Python allow performing mathematical operations such as union and intersection.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"The function \'type()\' in Python is used to check the data type of a variable.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"Python strings are immutable, meaning they cannot be changed after creation.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 22,\n      \"question\": \"We can concatenate two strings using the \'+\' operator in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 23,\n      \"question\": \"The \'input()\' function in Python is used to display output to the user.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"We can extract a substring from a string using slicing.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"A tuple can contain different data types such as strings, numbers, and lists.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 26,\n      \"question\": \"List slicing allows us to extract specific portions of a list.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 27,\n      \"question\": \"Dictionaries can have duplicate keys.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 28,\n      \"question\": \"The remove() function is used to delete a specific element from a list.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"Adding elements to a set using the add() method allows duplicate values.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"A dictionary can store another dictionary as its value.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"Python supports negative indexing for lists and strings.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"We cannot use a loop to iterate over a list in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"In Python, a variable must be declared before assigning a value to it.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"A single variable in Python can store different types of data at different times.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"Sets in Python maintain the order of elements as they are inserted.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"A dictionary\'s keys must be unique and immutable.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"Python automatically converts between different number types when needed.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"A tuple can be converted into a list using the list() function.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"The \'clear()\' method removes all elements from a dictionary.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"Lists in Python can contain duplicate values.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    }\n]\n  ',15,15),(62,'2.1-Basic Operators','<div>\n    <h2>2.1 Basic Operators</h2>\n    <p>In Python, operators are special symbols that perform operations on variables and values. These operations can be mathematical, logical, or even related to checking the identity or membership of objects.</p>\n    <h3>Types of Operators</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Arithmetic Operators</li>\n      <li>Comparison (Relational) Operators</li>\n      <li>Assignment Operators</li>\n      <li>Logical Operators</li>\n      <li>Bitwise Operators</li>\n      <li>Membership Operators</li>\n      <li>Identity Operators</li>\n      <li>Array Operators</li>\n      <li>Operator Precedence</li>\n    </ul>\n  \n    <h3>1. Arithmetic Operators</h3>\n    <table>\n      <tr><th>Operator</th><th>Symbol</th><th>Example</th></tr>\n      <tr><td>Addition</td><td>+</td><td>5 + 3 = 8</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>Subtraction</td><td>-</td><td>10 - 4 = 6</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>Multiplication</td><td>*</td><td>6 * 2 = 12</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>Division</td><td>/</td><td>8 / 2 = 4.0</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>Floor Division</td><td>//</td><td>9 // 2 = 4</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>Modulus</td><td>%</td><td>10 % 3 = 1</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>Exponentiation</td><td>**</td><td>2 ** 3 = 8</td></tr>\n    </table>\n  \n    <h3>2. Comparison (Relational) Operators</h3>\n    <table>\n      <tr><th>Operator</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Example</th></tr>\n      <tr><td>==</td><td>Equal to</td><td>5 == 5 → True</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>!=</td><td>Not equal to</td><td>5 != 3 → True</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>></td><td>Greater than</td><td>7 > 3 → True</td></tr>\n      <tr><td><</td><td>Less than</td><td>4 < 10 → True</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>>=</td><td>Greater than or equal to</td><td>5 >= 5 → True</td></tr>\n      <tr><td><=</td><td>Less than or equal to</td><td>6 <= 8 → True</td></tr>\n    </table>\n  \n    <h3>3. Assignment Operators</h3>\n    <table>\n      <tr><th>Operator</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Example</th></tr>\n      <tr><td>=</td><td>Assign</td><td>x = 5</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>+=</td><td>Add and assign</td><td>x += 3</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>-=</td><td>Subtract and assign</td><td>x -= 2</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>*=</td><td>Multiply and assign</td><td>x *= 4</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>/=</td><td>Divide and assign</td><td>x /= 2</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>%=</td><td>Modulus and assign</td><td>x %= 3</td></tr>\n    </table>\n  \n    <h3>4. Logical Operators</h3>\n    <table>\n      <tr><th>Operator</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Example</th></tr>\n      <tr><td>and</td><td>Returns True if both conditions are true</td><td>(x > 5 and x < 10)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>or</td><td>Returns True if at least one condition is true</td><td>(x < 5 or x > 15)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>not</td><td>Reverses the condition</td><td>not(x > 10)</td></tr>\n    </table>\n  \n    <h3>5. Bitwise Operators</h3>\n    <table>\n      <tr><th>Operator</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Example</th></tr>\n      <tr><td>&</td><td>AND</td><td>5 & 3 = 1</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>|</td><td>OR</td><td>5 | 3 = 7</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>^</td><td>XOR</td><td>5 ^ 3 = 6</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>~</td><td>NOT</td><td>~5 = -6</td></tr>\n    </table>\n  \n    <h3>6. Membership Operators</h3>\n    <table>\n      <tr><th>Operator</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Example</th></tr>\n      <tr><td>in</td><td>Returns True if value exists</td><td>\"a\" in \"apple\"</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>not in</td><td>Returns True if value does not exist</td><td>\"b\" not in \"apple\"</td></tr>\n    </table>\n  \n    <h3>7. Identity Operators</h3>\n    <table>\n      <tr><th>Operator</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Example</th></tr>\n      <tr><td>is</td><td>Returns True if objects are the same</td><td>x is y</td></tr>\n      <tr><td>is not</td><td>Returns True if objects are different</td><td>x is not y</td></tr>\n    </table>\n  \n    <h3>8. Operator Precedence</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li><b>()</b> - Parentheses (Highest)</li>\n      <li><b>**</b> - Exponentiation</li>\n      <li><b>*, /, //, %</b> - Multiplication, Division, Floor Division, Modulus</li>\n      <li><b>+, -</b> - Addition, Subtraction</li>\n      <li><b>==, !=, >, <, >=, <=</b> - Comparison</li>\n      <li><b>and</b> - Logical AND</li>\n      <li><b>or</b> - Logical OR (Lowest)</li>\n    </ul>\n  \n    <h3>Conclusion</h3>\n    <p>Python has a variety of operators that make it easy to perform calculations, comparisons, and logical operations. By understanding these operators, you can write more efficient and readable Python code! ?</p>\n</div>','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"Which operator is used for exponentiation in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"^\",\n        \"**\",\n        \"//\",\n        \"%%\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"What will be the output of `10 % 3` in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"3\",\n        \"1\",\n        \"0\",\n        \"10\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Which operator is used to check if two variables refer to the same memory location?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"==\",\n        \"!=\",\n        \"is\",\n        \"in\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"What will be the result of `5 // 2` in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"2.5\",\n        \"3\",\n        \"2\",\n        \"5\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is a logical operator in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"&&\",\n        \"||\",\n        \"!\",\n        \"and\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"Which operator has the highest precedence in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"+\",\n        \"and\",\n        \"()\",\n        \"**\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is an assignment operator?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"=\",\n        \"==\",\n        \"!=\",\n        \">=\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"What will be the output of `not (True and False)`?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"True\",\n        \"False\",\n        \"None\",\n        \"Error\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"Which operator is used for floor division?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"/\",\n        \"//\",\n        \"%\",\n        \"**\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"What will be the result of `3 & 2` (bitwise AND)?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"2\",\n        \"1\",\n        \"3\",\n        \"0\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"Which operator is used to check membership in a list?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"==\",\n        \"is\",\n        \"in\",\n        \"not\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"What is the result of `~5` (bitwise NOT)?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"-5\",\n        \"4\",\n        \"-6\",\n        \"5\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"Which operator is used for bitwise OR?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"&\",\n        \"|\",\n        \"^\",\n        \"~\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"Which comparison operator checks if two values are not equal?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"!=\",\n        \"<=\",\n        \"==\",\n        \">=\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"Which operator is used for left shift in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \">>\",\n        \"<<\",\n        \"^\",\n        \"**\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"The ________ operator is used for exponentiation in Python.\",\n      \"options\": [\"^\", \"**\", \"//\", \"%%\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"The modulus operator (%) returns the ________ of a division operation.\",\n      \"options\": [\"quotient\", \"remainder\", \"product\", \"exponent\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Which operator is used for floor division in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\"/\", \"//\", \"%\", \"^\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"The ________ operator is used to check if two values are equal.\",\n      \"options\": [\"=\", \"==\", \"!=\", \"<>\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is a logical operator in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\"+\", \"-\", \"and\", \"*\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"The bitwise AND operator is represented by ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"|\", \"&\", \"^\", \"~\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"The ________ operator in Python checks if a value exists in a sequence.\",\n      \"options\": [\"in\", \"is\", \"not\", \"or\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"The identity operator ________ checks if two variables refer to the same object.\",\n      \"options\": [\"in\", \"is\", \"==\", \"or\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"Which operator has the highest precedence in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\"+\", \"**\", \"or\", \"and\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"The ________ operator is used to reverse a condition in Python.\",\n      \"options\": [\"and\", \"or\", \"not\", \"is\"],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following assignment operators is used to perform exponentiation?\",\n      \"options\": [\"+=\", \"**=\", \"//=\", \"%=\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"The expression (5 + 2 * 3) evaluates to ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"21\", \"11\", \"15\", \"9\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"The Python operator precedence rule states that ________ operators are evaluated first.\",\n      \"options\": [\"arithmetic\", \"logical\", \"comparison\", \"bitwise\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"The \'not in\' operator returns True if a value ________ in a sequence.\",\n      \"options\": [\"exists\", \"does not exist\", \"is equal\", \"is greater\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"The operator used to check if two values are NOT equal is ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"==\", \"!=\", \"is\", \"and\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"Which operator shifts bits to the left in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\">>\", \"<<\", \"&\", \"^\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"The expression \'5 | 3\' using bitwise OR evaluates to ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"1\", \"7\", \"5\", \"3\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is an example of an identity operator?\",\n      \"options\": [\"is\", \"in\", \"not in\", \"or\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"Which assignment operator is used for floor division?\",\n      \"options\": [\"/=\", \"//=\", \"**=\", \"%=\"],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"The result of \'9 // 2\' is ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\"4\", \"4.5\", \"5\", \"5.0\"],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the addition operator (+) in Python is used to add two numbers.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that the exponentiation operator (**) is used for division.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"The modulus operator (%) returns the quotient of two numbers.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"The floor division operator (//) in Python removes the decimal part of a division result.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that the multiplication operator (*) cannot be used with strings.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"The comparison operator (==) checks if two values are exactly the same.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"The operator (!=) returns True if both values are equal.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"The logical AND operator (and) returns True if both conditions are True.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"The logical OR operator (or) returns True only if both conditions are True.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"The NOT operator (not) inverts the Boolean value of a condition.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"Bitwise operators work at the binary level in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"The bitwise AND operator (&) returns 1 if either bit is 1.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"The bitwise OR operator (|) returns 1 if either bit is 1.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"The membership operator \'in\' checks if a value is present in a sequence.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"The membership operator \'not in\' returns True if the value exists in the sequence.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"Identity operators check whether two variables refer to the same object in memory.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"The \'is\' operator returns True if two variables store the same values, regardless of memory location.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"Operator precedence determines the order in which expressions are evaluated in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"Parentheses () have the lowest precedence among all Python operators.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"The expression 2 + 3 * 4 evaluates to 14 because multiplication has higher precedence.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"Using parentheses in an expression changes the order of evaluation.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 22,\n      \"question\": \"The exponentiation operator (**) has a lower precedence than multiplication (*).\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 23,\n      \"question\": \"In Python, x += 5 is equivalent to x = x + 5.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"The assignment operator \'=\' is used for comparison between two values.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"Python supports array operators as built-in functionality.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 26,\n      \"question\": \"NumPy is commonly used for array operations in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 27,\n      \"question\": \"Using \'is not\' returns True when two variables refer to the same object in memory.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 28,\n      \"question\": \"The floor division operator (//) returns a float result always.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"The modulus operator (%) can be used to determine if a number is even or odd.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"The NOT (~) operator inverts Boolean values but does not work on integers.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"Using parentheses in expressions can override operator precedence.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"Python supports the use of multiple assignment operators in a single statement.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"The logical AND operator (and) has higher precedence than the logical OR operator (or).\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"The expression 5 == \'5\' evaluates to True in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"The greater than operator (>) and the less than operator (<) have the same precedence.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    }\n]\n  ',15,16),(63,'2.2-Control Flow','<div>\n    <h1>2.2 Control Flow</h1>\n    <p>\n      Control flow in Python refers to the order in which statements and instructions\n      are executed in a program. By default, Python runs code line by line from top to bottom,\n      but control flow statements allow us to make decisions, repeat actions, and jump to specific\n      parts of the program based on conditions.\n    </p>\n    \n    <h2>Types of Control Flow in Python</h2>\n    <p>Python provides three main types of control flow statements:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>\n        <strong>Conditional Statements (Decision Making)</strong> – Used to make choices in a program\n        (e.g., if, if-else, if-elif-else).\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <strong>Loops (Iteration Statements)</strong> – Used to repeat a block of code multiple times\n        (e.g., for loop, while loop).\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <strong>Jump Statements</strong> – Used to control the flow inside loops (e.g., break, continue, pass).\n      </li>\n    </ul>\n    \n    <h2>Why is Control Flow Important?</h2>\n    <p>Control flow allows Python programs to:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>\n        ✅ Make decisions (e.g., Check if a user is eligible to vote).\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        ✅ Repeat tasks efficiently (e.g., Print numbers from 1 to 10).\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        ✅ Skip or exit loops when needed (e.g., Stop searching when a value is found).\n      </li>\n    </ul>\n</div>\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What does control flow determine in a Python program?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"The order in which statements are executed\",\n        \"The speed of execution\",\n        \"The number of variables used\",\n        \"The type of programming paradigm\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is NOT a type of control flow statement in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Conditional Statements\",\n        \"Loop Statements\",\n        \"Jump Statements\",\n        \"Class Statements\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Which control flow statement is used for decision-making?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Loop Statements\",\n        \"Conditional Statements\",\n        \"Jump Statements\",\n        \"Assignment Statements\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"Which Python statement is used to execute a block of code only if a certain condition is met?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"if\",\n        \"for\",\n        \"while\",\n        \"continue\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"What will be the output of the following code?\\n\\nx = 10\\nif x > 5:\\n    print(\'Greater\')\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Greater\",\n        \"Error\",\n        \"Nothing\",\n        \"5\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"Which keyword is used for an alternative condition if the first condition in an if statement is False?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"elif\",\n        \"else\",\n        \"otherwise\",\n        \"except\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following loops in Python executes a block of code a specific number of times?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"while\",\n        \"for\",\n        \"do-while\",\n        \"loop\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"Which loop executes as long as a condition is True?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"for\",\n        \"while\",\n        \"do-while\",\n        \"switch\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"What does the break statement do in a loop?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Skips one iteration\",\n        \"Stops the loop entirely\",\n        \"Repeats the loop\",\n        \"Executes the next iteration\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"Which statement is used to skip the current iteration of a loop and move to the next iteration?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"break\",\n        \"continue\",\n        \"pass\",\n        \"return\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"What will be the output of the following code?\\n\\nfor i in range(3):\\n    if i == 2:\\n        break\\n    print(i)\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"0 1\",\n        \"0 1 2\",\n        \"2\",\n        \"None\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"Which keyword is used as a placeholder in a function, loop, or class that does nothing when executed?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"continue\",\n        \"pass\",\n        \"skip\",\n        \"halt\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"Which control flow statement allows repeating a block of code multiple times?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Loops\",\n        \"Conditional Statements\",\n        \"Jump Statements\",\n        \"None of the above\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"Which Python loop is more suitable when the number of iterations is unknown?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"for loop\",\n        \"while loop\",\n        \"do-while loop\",\n        \"nested loop\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is NOT a jump statement in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"break\",\n        \"continue\",\n        \"pass\",\n        \"switch\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following statements is true about the else clause in loops?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It runs only if the loop condition is initially False.\",\n        \"It runs only if the loop completes normally without a break.\",\n        \"It runs before the loop body.\",\n        \"It is mandatory in all loops.\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following best describes the use of \'continue\' in a loop?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Stops the loop entirely\",\n        \"Skips the current iteration and moves to the next one\",\n        \"Exits the loop after one iteration\",\n        \"Pauses execution for a specific time\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"What will be the output of the following code?\\n\\nfor i in range(5):\\n    if i == 3:\\n        continue\\n    print(i)\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"0 1 2 3 4\",\n        \"0 1 2 4\",\n        \"1 2 3 4\",\n        \"0 2 4\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"Which statement is used to exit a loop immediately?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"break\",\n        \"continue\",\n        \"exit\",\n        \"return\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"Which Python construct allows executing a different set of statements based on conditions?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Loops\",\n        \"Functions\",\n        \"Conditional Statements\",\n        \"Jump Statements\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"Control flow in Python determines the ________ in which statements are executed.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"data type\",\n        \"order\",\n        \"length\",\n        \"syntax\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"By default, Python executes code from ________ to bottom.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"bottom\",\n        \"randomly\",\n        \"top\",\n        \"sideways\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"The three main types of control flow statements in Python are Conditional Statements, ________, and Jump Statements.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Operators\",\n        \"Loops\",\n        \"Functions\",\n        \"Variables\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"Conditional statements in Python are used for ________ in a program.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"looping\",\n        \"decision making\",\n        \"assigning values\",\n        \"storing data\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is NOT a conditional statement in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"if\",\n        \"else\",\n        \"while\",\n        \"elif\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"The if-elif-else structure allows a program to check ________ conditions.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"multiple\",\n        \"one\",\n        \"zero\",\n        \"undefined\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"Loops in Python help in ________ a block of code multiple times.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"executing\",\n        \"skipping\",\n        \"storing\",\n        \"printing\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"A for loop is mainly used to iterate over a ________ in Python.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"list\",\n        \"number\",\n        \"string\",\n        \"boolean\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"The while loop runs until a specified ________ is met.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"data type\",\n        \"condition\",\n        \"function\",\n        \"variable\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"Jump statements in Python are used to ________ the normal loop execution.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"stop\",\n        \"pause\",\n        \"control\",\n        \"skip\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"The break statement is used to ________ a loop immediately.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"continue\",\n        \"pause\",\n        \"exit\",\n        \"print\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"The continue statement in Python skips the current iteration and moves to the ________ iteration.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"previous\",\n        \"first\",\n        \"next\",\n        \"last\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"The pass statement is used as a ________ when a statement is syntactically required but no action is needed.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"placeholder\",\n        \"operator\",\n        \"keyword\",\n        \"loop\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"Control flow helps a program to make ________ based on conditions.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"syntax\",\n        \"loops\",\n        \"decisions\",\n        \"functions\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"The else block in an if-else statement executes when the if condition is ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"True\",\n        \"False\",\n        \"Empty\",\n        \"Looping\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that Python executes code line by line from top to bottom by default.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that Python can only execute code in a linear sequence without control flow statements.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conditional statements in Python include if, if-else, and if-elif-else.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that conditional statements are not used for decision-making in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that loops in Python are used to repeat a block of code multiple times.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that loops are not used for repetition in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that jump statements in Python include break, continue, and pass.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that jump statements are not used to control the flow inside loops.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the break statement exits a loop entirely.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that the break statement skips to the next iteration of a loop.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the continue statement skips the current iteration and moves to the next one.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that the continue statement exits a loop entirely.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that control flow allows Python programs to make decisions based on conditions.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that control flow is not necessary for decision-making in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that control flow allows programs to repeat tasks efficiently.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that loops are not used for efficient repetition.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that control flow allows programs to skip or exit loops when needed.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that jump statements are not used to skip or exit loops.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that Python provides three main types of control flow statements.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that Python only provides two main types of control flow statements.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conditional statements are used to make choices in a program.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n      {\n      \"id\": 22,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that conditional statements are not used for making choices.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 23,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that loops are used to repeat actions.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that loops are not used for repeating actions.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that jump statements are used to control the flow inside loops.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 26,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that jump statements are not used inside loops.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 27,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that control flow allows programs to make decisions like checking if a user is eligible to vote.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 28,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that control flow does not allow checking user eligibility.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that control flow allows programs to repeat tasks efficiently, such as printing numbers from 1 to 10.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that loops are not used for printing sequences like numbers from 1 to 10.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that control flow allows programs to skip or exit loops when needed, such as stopping a search when a value is found.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that jump statements are not used to stop searching when a value is found.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that control flow statements include conditional statements, loops, and jump statements.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that control flow statements do not include conditional statements.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conditional statements are one of the three main types of control flow statements.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that conditional statements are not one of the main types of control flow statements.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that loops are one of the three main types of control flow statements.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that loops are not one of the main types of control flow statements.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that jump statements are one of the three main types of control flow statements.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that jump statements are not one of the main types of control flow statements.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 41,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that control flow allows programs to make decisions and repeat actions.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 42,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that control flow does not allow decision-making and repetition.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 43,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that control flow is important for managing loop execution.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 44,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that control flow is not important for loop management.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 45,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that control flow statements enable dynamic execution of code.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 46,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that control flow statements do not enable dynamic code execution.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that control flow allows programs to jump to specific parts of the code based on conditions.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that control flow does not allow jumping to specific parts of the code.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that control flow is essential for efficient programming in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"It is false that control flow is not essential for efficient Python programming.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    }\n]\n  ',15,16),(64,'2.3-Conditional Statements in Python','<div>\n  <h1>2.3 Conditional Statements in Python</h1>\n  <p>\n    Conditional statements in Python allow a program to make decisions based on\n    conditions. These statements help the program execute different code blocks\n    depending on whether a condition is True or False.\n  </p>\n  <p>Think of it like this:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>? If it\'s raining, take an umbrella.</li>\n    <li>? If it\'s sunny, wear sunglasses.</li>\n    <li>? If the weather is cloudy, you may or may not take an umbrella.</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p>\n    In Python, conditional statements work in the same way—making decisions\n    based on conditions.\n  </p>\n\n  <h2>1. if Statement</h2>\n  <p>\n    The if statement allows a program to execute a block of code only if a\n    certain condition is True.\n  </p>\n  <pre>\nif condition:\n    # Code to execute if condition is True</pre\n  >\n  <h3>Example 1: Checking if a number is positive</h3>\n  <pre>\nnum = 10\n\nif num > 0:\n    print(\"The number is positive.\")</pre\n  >\n\n  <h2>2. if … else Statement</h2>\n  <p>The if … else statement allows two possibilities:</p>\n  <pre>\nif condition:\n    # Code if condition is True\nelse:\n    # Code if condition is False</pre\n  >\n  <h3>Example 2: Checking if a number is positive or negative</h3>\n  <pre>\nnum = -5\n\nif num > 0:\n    print(\"The number is positive.\")\nelse:\n    print(\"The number is negative.\")</pre\n  >\n\n  <h2>3. if … elif … else Statement</h2>\n  <p>\n    Sometimes, we have multiple conditions. Instead of writing multiple if\n    statements, we use elif (short for else if) to check additional conditions.\n  </p>\n  <pre>\nif condition1:\n    # Code if condition1 is True\nelif condition2:\n    # Code if condition2 is True\nelse:\n    # Code if none of the conditions are True</pre\n  >\n  <h3>Example 3: Checking if a number is positive, negative, or zero</h3>\n  <pre>\nnum = 0\n\nif num > 0:\n    print(\"The number is positive.\")\nelif num < 0:\n    print(\"The number is negative.\")\nelse:\n    print(\"The number is zero.\")</pre\n  >\n\n  <h2>4. Nested if Statement</h2>\n  <p>\n    A nested if statement is when an if statement is placed inside another if\n    statement.\n  </p>\n  <pre>\nif condition1:\n    if condition2:\n        # Code if both conditions are True</pre\n  >\n  <h3>Example 4: Checking if a number is positive and even</h3>\n  <pre>\nnum = 8\n\nif num > 0:\n    print(\"The number is positive.\")\n\n    if num % 2 == 0:\n        print(\"It is also even.\")</pre\n  >\n\n  <h2>Real-Life Example: Age Verification System</h2>\n  <pre>\nage = int(input(\"Enter your age: \"))\n\nif age >= 18:\n    print(\"You are eligible to vote.\")\nelse:\n    print(\"Sorry, you must be at least 18 years old to vote.\")</pre\n  >\n</div>','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What is the purpose of conditional statements in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To perform arithmetic operations\",\n        \"To execute different code blocks based on conditions\",\n        \"To define loops in a program\",\n        \"To declare variables dynamically\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is the correct syntax for an if statement in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"if condition { }\",\n        \"if (condition):\",\n        \"if condition:\",\n        \"if condition then\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"What will be the output of the following code?\\n\\nnum = 10\\nif num > 0:\\n    print(\\\"Positive\\\")\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Positive\",\n        \"Negative\",\n        \"Error\",\n        \"No output\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"What will be the output if num = -5 in the following code?\\n\\nif num > 0:\\n    print(\\\"Positive\\\")\\nelse:\\n    print(\\\"Negative\\\")\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Positive\",\n        \"Negative\",\n        \"Zero\",\n        \"Error\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"Which statement is used for multiple conditions in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"if\",\n        \"else\",\n        \"elif\",\n        \"switch\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"What will be the output of the following code if num = 0?\\n\\nif num > 0:\\n    print(\\\"Positive\\\")\\nelif num < 0:\\n    print(\\\"Negative\\\")\\nelse:\\n    print(\\\"Zero\\\")\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Positive\",\n        \"Negative\",\n        \"Zero\",\n        \"Error\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"What is the purpose of a nested if statement?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To execute a single condition only\",\n        \"To allow multiple conditions inside another condition\",\n        \"To stop execution of a program\",\n        \"To print nested loops\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following correctly checks if a number is both positive and even?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"if num > 0 and num % 2 == 0:\",\n        \"if (num > 0, num % 2 == 0):\",\n        \"if num > 0 then num % 2 == 0:\",\n        \"if num > 0 or num % 2 == 0:\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"What will be the output of the following age verification program if the user inputs 17?\\n\\nage = int(input(\\\"Enter your age: \\\"))\\nif age >= 18:\\n    print(\\\"You are eligible to vote.\\\")\\nelse:\\n    print(\\\"Sorry, you must be at least 18 years old to vote.\\\")\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"You are eligible to vote.\",\n        \"Sorry, you must be at least 18 years old to vote.\",\n        \"Error\",\n        \"No output\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following statements about the if-elif-else structure is true?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Only one condition can be True at a time.\",\n        \"All conditions are checked regardless of the first True condition.\",\n        \"elif is mandatory in every if-else structure.\",\n        \"It can only be used inside loops.\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"Conditional statements in Python allow a program to make ________ based on conditions.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"loops\",\n        \"decisions\",\n        \"assignments\",\n        \"imports\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"The if statement executes a block of code only if a given condition is ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"False\",\n        \"Undefined\",\n        \"True\",\n        \"Zero\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"The syntax of an if statement starts with the keyword ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"elif\",\n        \"if\",\n        \"else\",\n        \"while\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"If the condition in an if statement is False, the code inside the if block is ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"skipped\",\n        \"executed\",\n        \"repeated\",\n        \"stored\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"The if…else statement provides an ________ in case the condition is False.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"alternative block\",\n        \"input\",\n        \"iteration\",\n        \"import\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"In an if…else statement, if the condition is False, the code inside the ________ block executes.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"if\",\n        \"else\",\n        \"elif\",\n        \"loop\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"The if…elif…else statement is used when we have ________ conditions to check.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"no\",\n        \"multiple\",\n        \"only one\",\n        \"looping\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"The elif statement is short for ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"if else\",\n        \"looping condition\",\n        \"while loop\",\n        \"else if\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 4\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"If none of the conditions in an if…elif…else statement are True, the ________ block executes.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"if\",\n        \"elif\",\n        \"else\",\n        \"while\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"A nested if statement is an if statement placed ________ another if statement.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"outside\",\n        \"inside\",\n        \"below\",\n        \"without\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"Nested if statements help in checking ________ conditions inside another condition.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"single\",\n        \"multiple\",\n        \"one\",\n        \"zero\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"The if condition is followed by a ________ before the block of code.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"comma\",\n        \"semicolon\",\n        \"colon\",\n        \"period\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"Indentation is important in Python because it defines the ________ of the statements.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"order\",\n        \"syntax\",\n        \"block\",\n        \"loops\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"In Python, an if statement can check for conditions using ________ operators.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"arithmetic\",\n        \"comparison\",\n        \"assignment\",\n        \"logical\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"The real-life example of an if…else statement is checking a person\'s ________ for voting eligibility.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"height\",\n        \"age\",\n        \"weight\",\n        \"name\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"The condition in an if statement must return a ________ value.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Boolean\",\n        \"String\",\n        \"List\",\n        \"Integer\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 17,\n      \"question\": \"A number is checked for being even or odd using the ________ operator.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"+\",\n        \"-\",\n        \"%\",\n        \"/\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 18,\n      \"question\": \"The if statement allows a program to execute a code block only when the condition is ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"False\",\n        \"Undefined\",\n        \"True\",\n        \"Skipped\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 19,\n      \"question\": \"An if…elif…else statement is useful for handling ________ possibilities.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"only one\",\n        \"multiple\",\n        \"no\",\n        \"zero\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 20,\n      \"question\": \"The following syntax is incorrect: if condition then:\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"True\",\n        \"False\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 21,\n      \"question\": \"The output of `if 5 > 3: print(\'Yes\')` is ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Yes\",\n        \"No\",\n        \"Error\",\n        \"Nothing\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 22,\n      \"question\": \"The else block is ________ if the if condition is True.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"executed\",\n        \"skipped\",\n        \"repeated\",\n        \"printed\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 23,\n      \"question\": \"Python\'s indentation rule ensures that the code is structured in a ________ way.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"readable\",\n        \"complex\",\n        \"unordered\",\n        \"confusing\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 24,\n      \"question\": \"An if statement without an else block will execute if the condition is ________.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"False\",\n        \"True\",\n        \"Zero\",\n        \"None\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 25,\n      \"question\": \"The elif keyword in Python is used to check ________ conditions.\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"one\",\n        \"nested\",\n        \"multiple\",\n        \"single\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    }\n]\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conditional statements in Python allow a program to make decisions based on conditions.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conditional statements in Python do not allow decision-making.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if statement executes a block of code only if a certain condition is True.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if statement executes code regardless of whether the condition is True or False.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if … else statement allows two possibilities based on a condition.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if … else statement can only execute one block of code.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if … elif … else statement checks multiple conditions.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if … elif … else statement can only check one condition at a time.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that nested if statements are used to check multiple conditions inside another condition.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that nested if statements cannot be used for checking multiple conditions.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conditional statements can be used to check if a number is positive or negative.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conditional statements cannot be used for checking whether a number is positive or negative.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if statement requires a condition to be specified.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if statement does not require a condition to execute.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 15,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if … else statement provides an alternative action if the condition is False.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 16,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if … else statement does not provide an alternative action when the condition fails.\",\n      \"answer\