uestion\": \"It is true that conditional statements are not necessary for decision-making processes.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 29,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if statement checks for one specific condition at a time.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 30,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if statement can check multiple conditions simultaneously.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 31,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conditional statements can be used to determine voting eligibility based on age.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 32,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conditional statements cannot determine eligibility based on user input.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 33,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if … else statement provides two distinct paths based on a condition.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 34,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if … else statement does not provide distinct paths.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 35,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that elif statements are used to handle multiple conditions sequentially.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 36,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that elif statements are not used for sequential condition checking.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 37,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that nested if statements can be used to check complex conditions.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that nested if statements cannot be utilized for complex condition checks.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conditional statements are used to execute different blocks of code based on conditions.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conditional statements do not execute different blocks of code.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 41,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if statement is used to check a single condition.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 42,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if statement is not used for checking a single condition.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 43,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conditional statements can be used to handle different scenarios based on user input.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 44,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conditional statements cannot handle different scenarios based on user input.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 45,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if … elif … else statement can handle more than two conditions.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 46,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the if … elif … else statement cannot handle more than two conditions.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conditional statements are crucial for making decisions in Python programs.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conditional statements are not crucial for decision-making in Python.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conditional statements help in managing different paths of execution based on conditions.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that conditional statements do not help in managing different paths of execution.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    }\n]\n  ',15,16),(65,'2.4-Looping in Python','<div>\n    <h2>2.4 Looping in Python</h2>\n    <p>Loops are used in Python to execute a block of code multiple times without writing the same code again and again. Instead of writing repetitive instructions, loops allow us to repeat actions efficiently.</p>\n    <p>Python provides different types of loops:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>while loop</li>\n      <li>for loop</li>\n      <li>Nested loops (A loop inside another loop)</li>\n    </ul>\n  \n    <h3>1. while Loop in Python</h3>\n    <p>The while loop executes a block of code as long as the condition is true. When the condition becomes false, the loop stops.</p>\n    <pre>\n      <code>\n  while condition:\n      # Code to execute\n      </code>\n    </pre>\n    <p>Example 1: Printing numbers from 1 to 5</p>\n    <pre>\n      <code>\n  num = 1\n  while num &lt;= 5:\n      print(num)\n      num += 1  # Increases num by 1 in each loop\n      </code>\n    </pre>\n  \n    <h3>2. for Loop in Python</h3>\n    <p>A for loop is used to iterate over a sequence (like a list, string, or range of numbers).</p>\n    <pre>\n      <code>\n  for variable in sequence:\n      # Code to execute\n      </code>\n    </pre>\n    <p>Example 1: Printing numbers from 1 to 5</p>\n    <pre>\n      <code>\n  for num in range(1, 6):\n      print(num)\n      </code>\n    </pre>\n  \n    <h3>3. Nested Loops in Python</h3>\n    <p>A nested loop is a loop inside another loop.</p>\n    <p>Example: Printing a Pattern</p>\n    <pre>\n      <code>\n  for i in range(1, 4):   # Outer loop (rows)\n      for j in range(1, 4):  # Inner loop (columns)\n          print(\"*\", end=\" \")\n      print()  # Moves to the next line\n      </code>\n    </pre>\n  \n    <h3>When to Use Which Loop?</h3>\n    <table border=\"1\">\n      <tr>\n        <th>Loop Type</th>\n        <th>Best For</th>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>while loop</td>\n        <td>When the number of iterations is unknown (repeat until a condition is false)</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>for loop</td>\n        <td>When looping through a sequence (like lists, strings, or a range of numbers)</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>Nested loops</td>\n        <td>When working with tables, patterns, or multi-level structures</td>\n      </tr>\n    </table>\n  \n    <h3>Conclusion</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>&#9989; <strong>while</strong> loop runs until a condition is false.</li>\n      <li>&#9989; <strong>for</strong> loop runs for a fixed number of times.</li>\n      <li>&#9989; <strong>Nested loops</strong> allow looping inside another loop.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p>Python loops make programming efficient by reducing repetition. ?</p>\n</div>\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What is the purpose of loops in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To store multiple values\",\n        \"To execute a block of code multiple times\",\n        \"To create functions\",\n        \"To define variables\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Which of the following is NOT a type of loop in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"while loop\",\n        \"for loop\",\n        \"do-while loop\",\n        \"Nested loop\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Which loop executes a block of code as long as a condition is True?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"for loop\",\n        \"while loop\",\n        \"nested loop\",\n        \"jump loop\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"What will be the output of the following code?\\n\\nnum = 1\\nwhile num <= 3:\\n    print(num)\\n    num += 1\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"1 1 1\",\n        \"1 2 3\",\n        \"1 2 3 4\",\n        \"Infinite loop\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"Which statement is used to stop a loop immediately?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"continue\",\n        \"break\",\n        \"pass\",\n    