imers.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 38,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the while loop is not used for countdown timers.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 39,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the for loop can iterate over lists.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 40,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the for loop cannot iterate over lists.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 41,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that nested loops can be used to create multiplication tables.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 42,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that nested loops cannot be used to create multiplication tables.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 43,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the break statement stops a loop immediately.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 44,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the break statement does not stop a loop immediately.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 45,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the continue statement skips the current iteration.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 46,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the continue statement exits the loop entirely.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 47,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that loops in Python are efficient for repetitive tasks.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 48,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that loops in Python are not efficient for repetitive tasks.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 49,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the while loop is used when the number of iterations is unknown.\",\n      \"answer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 50,\n      \"question\": \"It is true that the while loop is used when the number of iterations is known.\",\n      \"answer\": false\n    }\n]\n  ',15,16),(66,'2.5-Loop Manipulation using continue, pass, break, and else in Python','<div>\n    <h2>2.5 Loop Manipulation using continue, pass, break, and else in Python</h2>\n    <p>Loops in Python help us repeat tasks without writing the same code multiple times. But sometimes, we may want to skip some steps, stop the loop early, or do something when the loop finishes completely. This is where <strong>continue</strong>, <strong>pass</strong>, <strong>break</strong>, and <strong>else</strong> come into play.</p>\n    \n    <h3>1. break Statement (Stops the Loop Immediately)</h3>\n    <p>The <strong>break</strong> statement is used to stop a loop completely when a certain condition is met.</p>\n    <pre>\n      <code>\n  for num in range(1, 10):  # Loop from 1 to 9\n      if num == 5:\n          print(\"Number 5 found! Stopping loop.\")\n          break  # Stop the loop when num is 5\n      print(\"Current number:\", num)\n      </code>\n    </pre>\n    \n    <h3>2. continue Statement (Skip to the Next Iteration)</h3>\n    <p>The <strong>continue</strong> statement skips the current iteration and moves to the next one.</p>\n    <pre>\n      <code>\n  for num in range(1, 10):  \n      if num == 5:\n          print(\"Skipping number 5\")\n          continue  # Skip the rest of the code and move to the next number\n      print(\"Current number:\", num)\n      </code>\n    </pre>\n    \n    <h3>3. pass Statement (Do Nothing, Just a Placeholder)</h3>\n    <p>The <strong>pass</strong> statement is used when a statement is required syntactically, but we don’t want to do anything.</p>\n    <pre>\n      <code>\n  for num in range(1, 6):  \n      if num == 3:\n          pass  # Do nothing when num is 3\n      print(\"Current number:\", num)\n      </code>\n    </pre>\n    \n    <h3>4. else Clause in Loops</h3>\n    <p>The <strong>else</strong> statement in loops runs only when the loop completes normally (i.e., it is not stopped by break).</p>\n    <pre>\n      <code>\n  for num in range(1, 6):\n      print(\"Current number:\", num)\n  else:\n      print(\"Loop finished without a break.\")\n      </code>\n    </pre>\n    \n    <h3>Summary Table</h3>\n    <table border=\"1\">\n      <tr>\n        <th>Statement</th>\n        <th>What It Does</th>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>break</td>\n        <td>Stops the loop completely</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>continue</td>\n        <td>Skips the current iteration and moves to the next one</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>pass</td>\n        <td>Does nothing (just a placeholder)</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>else (in loop)</td>\n        <td>Runs only if the loop completes without break</td>\n      </tr>\n    </table>\n    \n    <h3>Real-Life Example: Password Checking</h3>\n    <p>We allow 3 attempts for password entry. If correct, we stop using <strong>break</strong>. If all attempts fail, we use <strong>else</strong>.</p>\n    <pre>\n      <code>\n  correct_password = \"python123\"\n  \n  for attempt in range(3):  # Allow 3 attempts\n      password = input(\"Enter password: \")\n      if password == correct_password:\n          print(\"Access granted!\")\n          break  # Stop the loop if password is correct\n      print(\"Incorrect password. Try again.\")\n  else:\n      print(\"Too many incorrect attempts. Access denied!\")\n      </code>\n    </pre>\n    \n    <h3>Conclusion</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>break</strong> stops the loop.</li>\n      <li><strong>continue</strong> skips the current iteration and moves to the next.</li>\n      <li><strong>pass</strong> does nothing (used as a placeholder).</li>\n      <li><strong>else</strong> runs only if the loop completes without break.</li>\n    </ul>\n</div>\n  ','[\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"What does the break statement do in a Python loop?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Skips the current iteration\",\n        \"Stops the loop immediately\",\n        \"Does nothing\",\n        \"Continues to the next iteration\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"What is the purpose of the continue statement in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To stop the loop\",\n        \"To skip the current iteration and move to the next\",\n        \"To do nothing\",\n        \"To restart the loop\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"What does the pass statement do in Python?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It stops the loop\",\n        \"It skips the current iteration\",\n        \"It does nothing\",\n        \"It restarts the loop\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"question\": \"When does the else clause in a Python loop execute?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"When the loop is stopped by break\",\n        \"When the loop completes normally without break\",\n        \"When the loop is skipped by continue\",\n        \"When the loop is paused\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 5,\n      \"question\": \"What happens if a break statement is encountered in a loop?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"The loop continues to the next iteration\",\n        \"The loop skips the current iteration\",\n        \"The loop stops immediately\",\n        \"The loop does nothing\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 6,\n      \"question\": \"What is the purpose of using pass in incomplete code?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"To stop the loop\",\n        \"To skip the current iteration\",\n        \"To prevent syntax errors\",\n        \"To restart the loop\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 7,\n      \"question\": \"How does the continue statement affect the loop?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It stops the loop\",\n        \"It skips the current iteration and continues\",\n        \"It does nothing\",\n        \"It restarts the loop\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"question\": \"What happens if a loop completes without encountering a break statement?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"The else clause does not execute\",\n        \"The else clause executes\",\n        \"The loop restarts\",\n        \"The loop skips to the next iteration\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"question\": \"What is the difference between break and continue?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"Break stops the loop, continue skips the iteration\",\n        \"Break skips the iteration, continue stops the loop\",\n        \"Break does nothing, continue skips the iteration\",\n        \"Break restarts the loop, continue stops the loop\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 1\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"question\": \"When should you use the pass statement?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"When you want to stop the loop\",\n        \"When you want to skip an iteration\",\n        \"When you need a placeholder in incomplete code\",\n        \"When you want to restart the loop\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 3\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"question\": \"What happens to the else clause if a loop is stopped by break?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It executes normally\",\n        \"It does not execute\",\n        \"It skips to the next iteration\",\n        \"It restarts the loop\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"question\": \"How does the break statement affect the loop\'s else clause?\",\n      \"options\": [\n        \"It causes the else clause to execute\",\n        \"It prevents the else clause from executing\",\n        \"It skips the else clause\",\n        \"It restarts the loop\"\n      ],\n      \"answer\": 2\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"question\": \"What is the purpose of the else clause in a loop?\",\n  